title: zucchini custard
directions: Salt zucchini, then steam until tender.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Mix together eggs, sour cream, seasoned salt, pepper and half of grated cheese.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until set.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix all together. Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until golden.

title: low-fat banana split cake
directions: Tear angel food cake into pieces and place in large bowl. Prepare Jell-O according to the directions on box and pour over cake.
Place bowl in refrigerator until Jell-O sets.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix room
temperature
cream
cheese and pimento cheese spread; grate
Cheddar
cheese
into mixture; add garlic.
Mix all except a few of the nuts into mixture.
Shape and decorate with remaining nuts.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate with butter over low heat, stirring until blended.
Remove from heat.
Gradually blend in milk.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt well in a separate bowl.
Beat in eggs and vanilla with sugar mixture.
Gradually add to chocolate mixture. Pour into pie shells.

title: pineapple cool whip cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions (use 9 x 13 pan) and bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Blend 1 cup milk, cream cheese and pudding. Add second cup of milk and beat until creamy. Spread over cool cake. Spread pineapple. Top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate overnight.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and flour.
Add milk, vanilla, melted butter and coconut.
Pour into 2 greased 9-inch pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: nacho chicken
directions: Set chicken and tortillas aside.
Mix all other ingredients together in a large bowl.
Cut or tear tortillas in 2-inch pieces and line a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been wiped with oil first. Spread chicken pieces on top of tortillas; pour mixture over chicken and tortillas.
Do not stir.
Cover with 1 cup shredded cheese and bake covered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Grate lemon rind; squeeze juice.
Cream sugar, shortening and rind.
Add beaten eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan 1 hour at 350°.
When baked, turn out onto platter and while hot, brush with juice of lemon, combined with 1/4 cup sugar.
(Add sugar to juice and stir occasionally while bread is baking.)
Cool before slicing.

title: seafood leg salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender (8 to 10 minutes) in water, salt and oil; drain and cool.
Mix with remaining ingredients and chill.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: egg biscuits
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Knead mixture on a clean, floured surface.
Cut into slices and twirl.
Place on ungreased pan, sprinkled with flour.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: taffy
directions: Combine ingredients; cook until syrup forms a hard ball (265°) when dropped into cold water.
Pour into buttered plates; cool until it can be pulled.
Butter hands lightly and pull until stiff.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix the apples, sugar, oil and eggs together.
Mix the flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and pecans; add to the apple mixture.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam (no need to flour it).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: marinated zucchini
directions: Mix all ingredients together and marinate at least 6 hours. Store in refrigerator.

title: cherry casserole
directions: Spread cherries first, then pineapple in bottom of dish.
Pour cake mix over pineapple.
Then slice 1 stick butter over cake mix. Spread pecans over butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ugly cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on package.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Drop this mixture by spoonfuls on top of cake batter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage pasta soup
directions: Take sausage out of casing and brown with onion.
Drain excess grease.
Add stewed tomatoes, water and salami.
Let cook 15 minutes.
Add rotini and cook 15 minutes more.
The best.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add sauce and simmer for a few minutes. Add cottage cheese and set aside. Boil the noodles for a few minutes.
Drain.
Layer in a 13 x 9-inch dish as follows:
sauce, noodles and cheese until all gone. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: imitation crabmeat spread
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix well.
Chill 1 hour.
Serve in bowl surrounded with assorted crackers or breads.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.	Place potatoes on paper towels in a circle in the microwave.
Microwave on high, 12 to 14 minutes, turning once during cooking time.
Cut potatoes in half.
Scoop out pulp into a large bowl.
Mash potatoes.
Mix in milk, and add yogurt.
Stuff potato shells with mixture.
Top with cheese and a dash of paprika.
Put in microwave for 30 seconds more.
Serve immediately.

title: quick spoon rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fill greased muffin pan half full with roll mixture.
Preheat oven to 400° and bake until brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
Dough will keep for several days, covered, in the refrigerator.
Do not stir; just put into pans.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli as package directs.
Mix in soup and chicken. If dry, add a touch of milk.
Place in casserole dish.
Place Velveeta (sliced or cut into cubes) evenly on top of broccoli. Melt butter and mix with crushed Ritz crackers.
Spread evenly on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour appetizers
directions: Mix beef, onion and salt.
Form into small meat ball.
Fry or bake and drain.
Mix preserves and barbecue sauce in large pot and heat until thoroughly mixed.
Add meat balls and franks to sauce and simmer 20 minutes.
Add pineapple and heat.
Serve about 60 appetizers.

title: hickory-grilled amberjack with grilled salsa(alfresco summer dinner with leslie and bob e.)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large heavy-duty, zip lock bag.
Add amberjack steaks, seal bag and shake gently until steaks are well-coated.
Marinate in refrigerator 30 minutes.
Soak hickory chips in water 30 minutes -- very important before placing them on the grill -- this keeps them from burning too fast.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill a deep dish 2/3 full of apples.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon of sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Melt and cool butter.
Beat together the egg, 2/3 cup sugar, salt, flour and walnuts.
Add melted butter to the mixture and pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini walnut bread
directions: Beat eggs; mix with sugar, oil and vanilla.
Stir together flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Mix egg mixture and flour mixture together.
Stir in zucchini and walnuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes after baking, then remove from pan.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a medium size bowl.
Great served with apples, grapes, strawberries or bananas.

title: rotel dip
directions: In large saucepan, melt cheese.
Place in bowl and add Ro-Tel. Mix and serve with corn or tortilla chips.

title: nanny dickard's dumplings
directions: Beat egg with fork.
Mix flour, salt and egg with fork; add hot broth,
cup
at a time, until dough forms a ball. Roll out
very thin on a well floured surface.
Cut into small squares. Drop
into
very
hot
broth,
one
at
a time.
Add chicken pieces,
salt,
pepper
and
2 tablespoons margarine. Cover and let simmer 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix in bowl sugar, salt, milk and eggs.
Mix well.
Stir in rice, raisins and vanilla.
Pour in baking dish and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place in pan of warm water and bake about 50 minutes.

title: baptist wassail
directions: Dilute grape juice as directed on can. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 10 minutes. Strain. Garnish with orange slices. Great for Christmas open house. Yields approximately 14 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: zucchini banana bread
directions: In a large bowl mix zucchini, sugar, mashed banana and brown sugar.
Let stand.
In another bowl, beat eggs, oil and vanilla. Combine with first mixture and mix well.
Then add dry ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Bake in two large loaf pans for 50 minutes at 325°.

title: very creamy potato-cheese soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter.
Add chopped potatoes and carrot; saute for 10 minutes.
Add stock (water) and dill; simmer until vegetables are cooked.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs, apples and nuts.
Mix dry ingredients and add to apple mixture; mix well.
Bake for 45 minutes at 300° or until cake is lightly brown and crusty on top, about 1 hour.

title: chicken and spinach salad
directions: Shred chicken in strips about 2 inches long.
Arrange on spinach leaves on individual plates, alternating with apple, orange and onion rings.
Sprinkle apple slices with lemon juice to prevent darkening.

title: old witches nut cake
directions: Beat first four ingredients together and add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Simply mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Best when baked on a low fire and slowly. Example: 250° for 2 hours.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and soda; set aside.
Add sugar gradually to shortening, creaming well.
Blend in eggs, beating well after each.
Stir in bananas.
Blend in sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts.
Turn into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan, well-greased on bottom.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: dottie's dinner under a dollar per serving
directions: Brown sausage (I use a little more sausage sometimes).
Add vegetables; continue cooking 5 minutes.
Drain.
Set aside to cool about 10 minutes.
Stir together sausage mixture, Velveeta cheese and bread cubes.
Place in a greased 8-inch square baking dish. Beat milk and eggs.
Pour over sausage mixture.
Cover; refrigerate several hours.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove cover; bake 50 to 55 minutes, until golden brown.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Arrange layer of asparagus tips in bottom of greased baking dish, then layer of egg slices.
Repeat layers.
Combine soup and seasonings and pour over asparagus and eggs.
Grate cheese over top and sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 300° for about 25 minutes.

title: sage, garlic and olive focaccia(heart healthy)
directions: Mix water, yeast and sugar. When the yeast foams on the top of the water, knead in the flour and the remaining ingredients. Proof until double in size. Fold over to remove gasses (punch down). Roll out onto a greased sheet pan. Cover and let rise slowly. Brush with olive oil; sprinkle with kosher salt and bake in a preheated 400° oven for approximately 25 minutes. Allow to cool slightly before serving.
Yield: 1 Focaccia.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Cook ground beef in skillet in a little water, crumbling meat as it cooks, drain.
Add seasonings, ketchup and pureed beans. Add water; simmer for at least 30 minutes.

title: orange sherbet gelatin
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add sherbet.
Cool, then add remaining ingredients.
Allow to set until firm.

title: tomato bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix tomato sauce, sugar, salt and 3/4 cup boiling water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole and place the bread cubes in it.
Pour the butter over the bread and toss to coat bread. Pour hot tomato sauce over the bread and bake 30 minutes.
Garnish with parsley before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: quick lunch
directions: With a whisk or blender, combine eggs with tomato and cook in a double boiler.
Stir occasionally (more often if in a saucepan) just until thick.
Serve on the hot rice or toast.

title: reese's cups
directions: Mix all 5 ingredients until smooth.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan greased with butter.
Cover with chocolate chips until you can't see the mixture and melt under broiler in oven until spreadable.
Let cool and cut into 1-inch squares.

title: kolaches
directions: Mix cream cheese and butter.
Add flour.
Refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
Cut in squares (6-inch).
Add filling (canned apple pie filling is good).
Fold corner over to make squares.
Bake at 400°.
Glaze with powdered sugar and milk mixture.

title: pink party dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling drained juices; chill until slightly thickened.
Meanwhile, cream sugar and cream cheese; blend in fruit.
When jello is thickened, blend into stiffly beaten Milnot; fold in fruit mixture.
Blend wafer crumbs with oleo and add pecans.
Press all but 1 cup in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex.
Spread jello fruit mixture over crumbs.
Sprinkle reserved cup of crumbs on top.
Chill.

title: salted pecans
directions: Spread nuts on 15 x 10-inch pan.
Drizzle butter over nuts. Sprinkle with salt.
Mix.
Bake in 300° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Stir often.

title: yellow chicken and rice
directions: Broil chicken breast until done and tear apart.
Add rice and 3 1/3 cups broth from chicken.
Cut sausage into pieces and add to rice.
Add cream of chicken and bring to boil on high. When boiling, cut on low and cook for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Slice tomatoes in half.
Arrange in baking dish; top with seasoned bread crumbs, snip of bacon or bacon bits or pat of butter.
Add a dash of sugar and oregano.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan and flour.
Layer all ingredients in order given in pan, then melt 2 sticks or 1/2 pound oleo or butter and pour over top of "cake."
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: shrimp and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter and saute vegetables.
Add shrimp, cream of mushroom soup and water.
Put all of the ingredients in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese and bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hearty bean stew
directions: In a Dutch oven, combine all ingredients, except cheese, with 2 1/2 cups water and 1 teaspoon salt.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Top each serving with 1/3 cup cheese cubes.
Serves 6.

title: pork chop dumplings(butter bean pie)
directions: Mix flour, shortening, salt and enough water to make dough that can be rolled out for the dumplings.
Cook pork chops in large kettle covered with water until almost done.
Add tomatoes and butter beans.
Bring to a good boil.
Roll out the dumplings as thin as possible.
Cut into strips about 2 x 6-inches.
Take up (remove from kettle) 4 chops.
Drop in part of the dumplings.
Add 2 more chops to kettle and then more dumplings.
Add the last 2 chops and the remainder of the dumplings.
Alternating layers will keep the dumplings from sticking together.
Cook until dumplings are done.
If you like dumplings, you will love this!

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs to butter and sugar and mix one egg at a time.
Measure together bourbon and vanilla.
Then sift dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with bourbon and vanilla to egg, butter and sugar mixture.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine soup, water and cheese.
Over low heat, heat until cheese is melted.
Stir occasionally.
Add spaghetti, pepper and parsley.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: five layer meal
directions: Thinly slice potatoes.
Brown meat and onion on top of stove. Add salt and chili powder.
Make in layers of meat, potatoes, sprinkle with uncooked rice, green pepper and can of corn (drained).
Add water and catsup and pour over mixture.
(Do not stir.)
Place lid on skillet and heat until steam comes out, then turn heat to low and cook 30 minutes.
This recipe will serve 8 people.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine and bake 1 hour at 350° in 3 small pans that have been greased and floured.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place frozen potatoes in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Mix 1/2 cup margarine, salt, pepper, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Pour over potatoes.

title: texas chili
directions: In large pan, brown ground beef and onion.
Add chili powder and garlic powder.
Stir in tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Add kidney beans and diced tomatoes.
Simmer until all ingredients are hot and serve with shredded cheese and crackers.

title: chef henri's scampi
directions: Add spices to softened butter; let set several hours or overnight.
Saute shrimp in butter mixture.

title: nana's pie crust
directions: Combine flour, salt and shortening; work in.
Put egg in measuring cup and beat.
Add water and vinegar.
Gradually add to flour mixture.

title: iron skillet stew
directions: Brown hamburger in iron skillet; drain and remove hamburger to a bowl.
Wash and dice potatoes.
Melt margarine in skillet and cook potatoes in it for 5 minutes.
Add sliced carrots, celery and chopped onion.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Add chopped cabbage over all.
Put cooked hamburger on top.
Add seasoning salt.
Cover tightly.
Turn heat to low.
Cook 30 minutes without stirring.

title: molasses cake
directions: Place eggs, sugar, molasses, cloves, cinnamon and oil into deep bowl and beat well.
Dissolve baking soda in 1/8 cup boiling water.
Add to beaten mix.
Stir.
Add flour.
Beat well.
Add 1 cup boiling water and beat lightly.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mr. mac's chili
directions: In a large pot, cook together meat, onion and garlic until gray in color.
Add chili powder, salt, oregano, cumin and hot water. Mix well.
Simmer half hour, skimming fat as needed.
Add beans and simmer another half hour.
Add red pepper to taste.
Yields 2 1/2 quarts.

title: fretia green's rolls
directions: Mix yeast, warm water and salt.
Set aside.
Mix next four ingredients.
Cool.
Add two eggs, beaten, to the cooled mixture which also includes the yeast mixture.
Add 3 cups flour.
Mix, then add 3 more cups of flour.
Knead 5 minutes.
Roll out 1/2 at a time.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: posole
directions: Place pork roast, water and broth in a large soup kettle. Heat to boiling, add onions and salt.
Cover and simmer for 4 hours.
Remove pork from broth and allow to cool.
Cover and refrigerate broth.
Cut pork into small pieces and discard bones. Skim grease from broth.
Stir garlic, chili powder and paprika into bacon grease over low heat just until blended.
Stir a small amount of broth into mixture, add mixture to broth.
Add hominy and pork and heat to boiling.
Lower heat, cover, and simmer gently for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Then add oil and cream thoroughly. Add apples and
nuts.
Add
dry
ingredients,
then
add vanilla. Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies in blender.
Mix cool whip and cream cheese. Melt oleo and mix with powdered sugar. Then mix the instant pudding, milk, and vanilla.
Alternate layers, starting with cookies, then cool whip mixture until all ingredients have been used with cookies on the top.

title: pot roast
directions: In a 6-quart pan, in hot oil, cook roast until brown on all sides.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup, onion soup and 1 cup of the water.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and let simmer 2 hours or until meat is tender, turning occasionally.
Add vegetables, cover and cook for 40 minutes more or until vegetables are tender.
Remove roast and vegetables.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients in 1-quart size Ziploc bag.
Seal bag and shake.
Place quart size bag into gallon Ziploc bag.
Fill outer bag with ice and rock salt.
Close outer bag.
Mash bag slowly turning over and over.
Should be ready to about 15 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook in casserole or pan at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Wash and peel carrots, slice carrots, cook to firm, but tender.
Drain; cool.
Mix dressing.
Chop onion and green pepper. Add to carrots, toss gently.
Refrigerate until time of service. Makes six 1/2-cup servings.

title: velveeta dip
directions: Melt a block of Velveeta cheese.
Add 1 large can of Ro-Tel drained and the ground beef, cooked and drained.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream and soften the cream cheese.
Boil shrimp and chop finely.
Add to cream cheese.
Mix in onion, celery and mayonnaise.
Add Worcestershire sauce and seasonings.
Mix until well blended.
Chill.

title: bacon wrap scallops
directions: Mix all ingredients together except bacon, scallops and cheese.
Wrap scallops in 1/2 slice bacon.
Pin with toothpick. Pour spices, butter and wine ingredients into baking dish.
Place bacon wrapped scallops in baking dish.
Cover and marinate for at least 5 hours. Bake until almost done. Take from oven. Sprinkle with cheese.
Place back in oven for 5 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: barbecue bacon crisp
directions: Wrap water chestnuts with bacon and secure with toothpicks. Put on baking rack over pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 425°.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins until water is almost gone.
Cool completely. Add remaining ingredients; mix well and bake at 350° until done.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs, flour and vanilla; beat well.
Blend all together before adding buttermilk. Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Cook 35 minutes at 250° or 300°.

title: apple cinnamon muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix milk, juice concentrate, oil and egg whites in a bowl or blender.
Add apples. Line muffin tins with paper baking cups and fill with batter. Store in a plastic bag in refrigerator.
May be heated in oven or microwave.
Makes 12.

title: scandinavian salmon cheddar pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In large mixing bowl, beat eggs until smooth.
Add milk, parsley, butter, green onions, lemon juice, Worcestershire and mustard.
Mix well.
Fold in cheese and salmon. Pour into cooled pie shell.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until just set and crust is golden brown.
Serve with Topping recipe.

title: no bake pumpkin pie
directions: In medium bowl with electric mixer on high speed, beat cream to stiff peaks.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Cook almonds with sugar in heavy skillet. Stir constantly until sugar is melted and almonds are coated. Cool on waxed paper and break apart. Set aside. Mix rest of ingredients and serve with Sweet-sour Dressing.

title: new mexico spoon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except chilies and cheese.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan, half the mixture.
Top with half the chilies and cheese.
Pour rest of mixture and top with chilies and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Minced onion can be added to mixture.

title: amish bread starter
directions: Or get a starter from friend.

title: no-bake brownies
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine milk and chocolate bits.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth.
Mix in honey graham crumbs and nuts on medium speed of electric mixer until smooth.
Spread in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: bean dip
directions: Put in layers with beans on the bottom.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes, or until hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cut broccoli and cook until tender.
Saute onion in butter. Drain broccoli; add onion and butter.
Add rice; mix in cream of mushroom soup.
Mix all ingredients good.
Pour into baking dish. Cook for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven to melt cheese.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: *Fresh or canned tomatoes can be used.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and butter until smooth. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well with hand.
Do not use mixer.
Add flour and milk.
Stir in vanilla and lemon, mixing well.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Start with a cold oven.

title: lemon delight cake
directions: Pour over cake as soon as it comes from oven.

title: mustard onions
directions: Pour butter over squares.
Add boiled ingredients, and bake 1/4 to 1/2 hour in a moderate (350°) oven.
Serve with main course.

title: cool peach delight
directions: Mix jello with hot water.
Add marshmallows, crushed pineapple (drained) and bananas.
Put in icebox and let set.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Cut margarine into flour mixture.
Add soda to buttermilk and stir into flour mixture. Roll out dough on lightly floured board, cut and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until browned.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg; mix.
Add dry ingredients and milk; mix well.
Add rhubarb.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup hot water with 1 teaspoon sugar and salt.
Let set in warm place for 20 minutes.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Wash raisins in hot water and drain.
Cream shortening with sugar, then add beaten eggs and milk.
Combine with oatmeal and raisins and mix well.
Add flour, sifted with soda, salt and cinnamon.
Beat thoroughly.
Add nuts, if desired.
Drop onto greased cookie sheets and bake about 12 minutes in a moderate oven (350° to 375°).
Makes about 3 dozen medium-sized cookies.

title: cheese grits
directions: Prepare grits according to package directions.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well and pour into greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until set.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Make creamed potatoes out of the potatoes.
Boil ground beef. Place in baking dish.
Alternate layers of ground beef, corn and cheese.
Top with creamed potatoes.
Cook in 400° oven for about 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: hamburg barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Pour off grease.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 30 to 45 minutes.

title: easy taco salad casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain well.
Add beans, olives, pepper, tomato sauce, cumin and salt and pepper.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir in broken corn chips.
Serve with rest of ingredients (optional). Serves 8.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: *Chips can be fresh or stale.

title: party mushrooms
directions: Marinate about 1 hour in ovenproof dish.
Bake 1 hour at 325° to 350°.
Taste sauce and season to taste.
Put in chafing dish.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Simmer onion and garlic with olive oil in pan until onions are soft. Put in remaining ingredients and bring to boil. Reduce to simmer. Stir occasionally and simmer for 1 hour.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Mix together and pour into a 12-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crab casserole
directions: Toss ingredients lightly.
Place in greased casserole. Refrigerate overnight, covered.
Bake, covered, at 350° for one hour.

title: the black eyes of texas(black-eyed pea casserole)
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic.
Mix next 4 ingredients into meat.
Layer meat and sauce and tortillas.
Add cheese last.
Cook in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot green pepper jelly
directions: Put vinegar and chopped peppers in blender; chop very fine. Put peppers and vinegar in a saucepan and bring to a rolling boil; stir in sugar, continue boiling until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat and strain.
Put strained mixture back in a saucepan and add Certo and food coloring.
Bring back to a boil, stirring constantly; boil for 1 minute.
Put in jars and seal.

title: beth's apple dip
directions: Blend well.
Delicious for dipping any fresh fruit.

title: veggie dip
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: olive-cheese ball
directions: Blend cream cheese, Swiss cheese, Parmesan cheese, olives and chives.
Form into ball and chill well.
Press pecans onto ball. Serve surrounded by crackers.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly. Put in baking dish which has been sprayed with oil.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and put on topping.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Prepare cookie mix as package directs.
Spread in pizza pan and bake until golden brown.
Cool completely.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes; take off stove while still quite firm.
Put onion, eggs and cucumber together with potatoes while they are still warm.
Pour French dressing sparingly over mix; let stand 1/2 hour.
Mix in Miracle Whip, mustard, brown vinegar and sugar to taste.
Add more according to your taste.
Mix all together.

title: chicken jalapeno
directions: Saute onion in oleo; add soup and heat slowly with milk and jalapeno relish.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, line the bottom with Tostitos chips.
Pour soup mixture over chips.
Add chicken and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with Spanish rice and corn.
Muy Bueno!

title: old-fashion egg custard pie
directions: Cream butter, 3/4 cup sugar and flour.
Add egg yolks, milk, vanilla and nutmeg.
Blend well.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Beat egg whites; add 6 tablespoons sugar, dash of salt and cream of tartar.
Spread on pie and bake at 400° until brown.

title: blueberry muffins(fat-free)
directions: Mix applesauce, sugar, orange juice and egg together.
Add flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix well, then add wheat germ and grated orange peel and stir.
Add blueberries last.
Mix lightly.
Use muffin liners or sprayed muffin pans with Pam. Place muffin mix in each one, filling to half.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate caramel apples
directions: Insert skewers into apples part way through.
Divide nuts into 6 mounds onto wax paper.
Heat chocolate chips, water and caramels in a pot on low heat until mixture is smooth.
Stir occasionally. Dip each apple, one at a time, into chocolate mixture until evenly coated.
Then roll into nuts.
If chocolate mixture hardens before you are finished, just reheat on a low flame.
Let apples stand until firm.

title: date nut pie
directions: Mix crackers, dates, nuts, sugar, baking powder, salt and flavoring.
Fold dry mixture a teaspoon at a time into well-beaten egg whites.
Bake in well-greased 9 x 9-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: simple chicken
directions: In large skillet combine chicken and about 1/3 of the dressing.
Saute until chicken starts to brown.
Add vegetables and rest of Italian dressing.
Cover; simmer 7 to 9 minutes, until vegetables are crisp, stirring frequently.
Serve over hot pasta.

title: cheesecake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, sugar and butter.
Cover bottom and part way up the sides of a 9-inch pie pan.
Press lightly and chill.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix flour and sugar together, then add cream and pineapple. Cook over medium heat until thick.
Add butter.
Let sauce cool. Mix apples in cooled sauce.
Top with cherries for color.

title: east point salmon loaf
directions: Add bread crumbs, melted butter, onion flakes, parsley flakes, pimento, seasoning salt and pepper to salmon.
Toss together lightly.
Add egg yolks, mix and then fold in beaten egg whites. Put in a greased loaf pan.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: hot turkey & cheddar casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Coat a 9 X 13 inch baking dish with butter. In a medium bowl, combine turkey, celery, water chestnuts, bell pepper, mayonnaise, onion, lemon juice, 1 cup cheddar cheese and 1/2 cup mozzarella cheese; mix well.

title: orange sherbet(for ice cream freezer)
directions: Mix sugar and Jell-O with hot water.
Add condensed milk and orange soda.
Pour into ice cream freezer.
Proceed as you would when making ice cream.

title: banana pudding pie
directions: Cook pudding according to directions on box; set aside.
Layer pie shell with sliced bananas, the vanilla wafers.
Pour pudding over bananas and wafers after each layer until shell is full. Sprinkle crushed wafers on top.
Chill and serve.

title: diet banana split cake
directions: Slice or pinch off pieces of cake and line the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour pineapple over cake.
Layer the slices of bananas and then the pudding.
Top with Cool Whip. Garnish with fruit if desired.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Simmer
first 5 ingredients for 15 minutes.
In a 2-quart casserole, layer taco chips, chicken mixture and cheese; repeat layers.
Heat in microwave or oven until bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook the onion in margarine in a large saucepan until tender but not browned.
Stir in biscuit mix, pepper and thyme. Add chicken broth and evaporated milk. Cook and stir until mixture is thick and bubbly. Cook and stir for 1 minute more. Add chicken and vegetables.
Heat until mixture is bubbly. Reduce heat; keep warm.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: After boiling potatoes, peel skins off and then cut up in 1/2 to 1-inch pieces.
Put in oven-proof bowl and set aside.
Cut bacon into small pieces and fry to crisp.
Take bacon from grease and put bacon on potatoes; return the grease to fire.
Add cut up onions; fry in the grease until done or transparent.
When done, add cup of vinegar slowly into onions in pan until mixture is hot.
Pour on potatoes.
Add 1/2 cup water into pan.
Heat until water bubbles. Pour this over potatoes and mix well.
Cut 2 slices bacon in halves and place on top of mixture.
Heat in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli hot dish
directions: Saute onion in butter or margarine.
Add Cheez Whiz, cream of mushroom soup and milk.
Heat together.
Remove from heat and add Minute rice and mushrooms.
Pour over broccoli and bake 40 minutes in 350° oven in 9 x 12-inch buttered dish.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Remove avocado meat from skin and mash.
Combine with other ingredients and mix well.
Chill.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion.
Add soups, sauce, chilies and milk. Place Doritos in bottom of large casserole dish.
Pour meat sauce over chips.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Alternate in layers, ending with cheese.
Bake at 400° until bubbly.

title: bacon and tomato dip
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
Chop tomato.
Mix sour cream and Miracle Whip.
Add bacon and tomato.
Chill.
Toast bread and slice in quarters.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add flour slowly.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Roll in powdered sugar before completely cool.

title: rocky road bars
directions: Add chocolate to milk in small saucepan and cook, stirring constantly, over low heat until chocolate is melted and sauce is smooth.
Mix nuts, marshmallows, crumbs and sugar in a large bowl. Pour chocolate over crumb mixture.
Mix until all crumbs are moistened.
Turn into a well buttered 9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch pan. Press down and chill until firm.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place on cookie sheet; bake at 300° until dry.
Stir every 10 minutes.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Cover raisins with hot water and simmer 10 minutes; reserve 1/3 cup raisin liquid.
Sift flour with soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves. Gradually add sugar to shortening in mixing bowl.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla; beat well.	Stir in raisins and raisin liquid; add sifted dry ingredients, rolled oats and nuts.	Mix thoroughly.
Drop by rounded teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: caramel layer chocolate squares
directions: Melt
caramels in 1/3 cup evaporated
milk
(either
in double boiler or microwave) until smooth.
Set aside.
Combine cake mix, butter, remaining 1/3 cup milk
and
nuts
together. Press half mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Sprinkle morsels on top and pour caramel evenly over morsels. Crumble remaining dough over top.
Bake
for 15 to 18 minutes more.
Cool. Cut in squares.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage, cheese, celery, onion and Bisquick mix together. Form balls and bake at 350° until done.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots for 8 to 10 minutes; drain.
Put in onions and peppers.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over vegetables. Marinate overnight.

title: apple crisp(serves 16)
directions: Arrange apple slices in greased 4-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle rinds and liqueurs on top of apples.
In separate bowl, mix sugars, flours, salt and butter with pastry blender until crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with cream, whipped cream or ice cream.

title: josh's basic barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and simmer until thickened, about 15 minutes.
Let cool and discard chilies.
Add Tabasco to taste.
Use over chicken or beef.

title: apple crumb dessert
directions: Butter and flour a 9-inch baking dish.
Mix all ingredients except apples and apple cider.
Place apples in dish.
Pour mixture on top of apples.
Sprinkle apple cider on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: marinated eye of round
directions: Pierce roast.
Season lightly with first 3 ingredients.
Place in a large, plastic bag; set in deep bowl.
Mix all liquid ingredients.
Pour over roast in bag.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight, turning occasionally.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Boil (unopened) can of Eagle Brand milk in a saucepan filled with water for 2 hours.
Slice bananas in crust; add pecans. Spread Eagle Brand milk over top.
Frost with Cool Whip.

title: three week salad
directions: In large bowl, shred cabbage and onion.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon sugar over all and let set.
Bring to boil vinegar, oil, 3/4 cup sugar, celery seed, salt and prepared mustard.
Pour over cabbage. Cover and put in refrigerator.
Leave several hours, then stir and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crush crackers (1 package) and spread on bottom of the cake pan.
Mix both soups and sour cream.
Add chicken and chestnuts. Spread out in the cake pan and crumble other package of crackers on top.
Melt oleo and drizzle over top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: slumgullion
directions: Place roast, soup bones and salt in large kettle.
Barely cover with cold water.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Simmer for 3 to 3 1/2 hours or until tender.
Remove meat and bones from kettle.
Strain liquid (there should be about 5 or 6 cups; if not, add water). Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 20 minutes, until vegetables are just tender.
Meanwhile, cut meat into bite-size pieces.
Add meat to kettle, stirring gently.
Add hot water if thinner stew is desired.
Heat through.
Serve piping hot in bowls. Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken and sausage jambalaya
directions: In large pot, melt butter and saute onions until translucent. Add all seasonings, including worcestershire sauce.
Cook another 2 minutes.
Add sausage, chicken, rice, and diced tomatoes with 4 cups of water.
Stir well.
Cover and cook until rice is done. Rice will soak up most of liquid.
If appears to be getting too dry before rice is done, just add more water.

title: hot nacho dip
directions: Layer the ingredients in a 9-inch pie plate in the order given.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until bubbly.
Garnish with chopped onion and chopped tomatoes. Serve with nacho chips.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Prepare spaghetti as directed and let it cool.
Add bell pepper, tomatoes and cucumber.
Add entire bottle of Italian salad dressing.
Sprinkle half of bottle of Salad Supreme.
Toss so all ingredients are coated.
Cover the bowl and refrigerate overnight. Toss and shake well before serving.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain pineapple and cherries.
Heat juices.
Pour over Jell-O and gelatin; dissolve.
Add cream cheese and dissolve.
Add Coke. Chill.
When almost set, add cherries, pineapple and pecans.
Chill until set.

title: do ahead brisket
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with foil in both directions.
Place meat in center, fat side up.
Sprinkle onion soup and salad dressing over meat.
Cover with 1 jar of gravy.
Fold foil to envelope meat.
Bake at 300° for 5 hours.
Remove from oven.
Slice meat across grain and return to gravy.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken with dumplings
directions: In large pot, place chicken, water, onion, celery, salt and pepper.
Cook chicken until done.
Remove from broth and allow to cool.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, cream butter, brown sugar, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Immediately move to wire racks to cool.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash and slice tomatoes 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.
Beat egg and milk in bowl; set aside.
In another bowl, mix flour and meal. Dip tomatoes (salted and peppered) in milk mixture, then in meal mixture.
Place into skillet of hot oil and fry (not too fast) until browned on both sides.

title: jessie's easy pizza
directions: Spread oil over pizza pan.
Form dough on pan, leaving enough to raise the edge.
In blender, mix tomato paste, 4 tablespoons water and garlic.
Spread this mixture over dough.
Add cheese, minced garlic and the toppings you choose.
Bake in 425° oven for 20 minutes or until bottom of pizza is golden brown.
Slice and enjoy.

title: buffet meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape in balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake in oven for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: soy sauce chicken wings
directions: Sprinkle chicken wings with garlic salt and coat with cornstarch and flour mixture.
Heat oil and brown chicken on both sides.
Drain and place in casserole dish.
In a medium saucepan, heat soy sauce, sugar, cayenne pepper and ginger root.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken wings.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 325°. Serve with rice.

title: rice pilaf
directions: In skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon to paper towels.
Set aside.
Pour off all but 1/4 cup bacon drippings from skillet.
Add onion to skillet.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir rice, peas, water, broth, salt and pepper into mixture.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes until rice is tender.
To serve, toss rice mixture together with bacon.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni, rinse with cold water and drain.
Add chopped tomatoes, onion, green pepper, olives and cheese.
Mix well.

title: okie guacamole dip
directions: Mash avocados (about 1 cup when mashed) until smooth, combine with all ingredients except bacon.
Chill.
Just before serving, add bacon and stir well, top with a few bits of remaining bacon. Serve with tortilla or corn chips.

title: spring chicken pasta
directions: Boil 2 cups chicken broth with 1 1/2 cups sliced chicken.
Add vegetables and cook until tender.
Cook pasta and toss vegetables and chicken with cheeses.
Toss all together.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: onion dill bread for bread machine
directions: Follow instructions for Bread Menu.
Insert mixing blade in bread pan.
Measure ingredients into bread pan.
Place pan in bread maker.
Select bread setting.
Push start button.
When cycle is completed, beeper sounds.
Remove pan and bread.
Good with soups and stews.

title: holiday string bean casserole
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons butter, flour, salt, pepper, sugar, sour cream, grated onion and garlic salt in saucepan.
Cook until thickened.
Mix sauce with beans and pour into buttered casserole. Cover with grated cheeses.
Top with crushed cornflakes.
Drizzle melted butter on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: smoked sausage
directions: Mix together chili sauce and grape jelly in saucepan.
Add sliced smoked sausage.
Cook down until thick.

title: country-style beef roast
directions: Combine flour and seasonings.
Rub roast with seasoned flour. Place on rack in baking pan.
Add water to depth of 2 inches. Bake in 350° oven until tender.
Add additional water as needed to prevent sticking.
Add onion during last hour of cooking.
Remove roast to serving platter.
Make gravy using pan drippings.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: bacon 'n' veggie pasta
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the first 7 ingredients. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes or until broccoli and carrots are tender.

title: vanilla buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Fold in flavoring by hand.
Bake in greased tube pan for 1 hour and 45 minutes at 325°.
Start cake in cold oven and do not open door while baking.

title: christy's green beans with buttered pecans
directions: Wash beans; trim ends and remove strings.
Bring water and salt to a boil in a medium saucepan.
Add green beans.
Cook, uncovered, 10 minutes or just until crisp-tender.
Drain and set aside.

title: mushroom-onion rice(my own recipe)
directions: Melt butter in frypan.
Cook mushrooms, onions and dry rice in butter until mushrooms are tender (6 to 8 minutes).
Add 2 cups of water and soup mix to pan.
Cover and cook over low heat for 25 minutes.
Remove from heat; let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain; add 1/2 cup dressing-toss and chill. Steam pea pods for 3 minutes. Combine vegetables and 1 cup dressing and chill. Cook chicken.
Add chicken and 1/2 cup chopped basil and 1/4 cup chopped parsley.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix together and form into balls.
Place in a baking dish and spoon your favorite spaghetti sauce over balls.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle parsley flakes on top and serve.
Makes 24 meat balls.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter and cocoa in small bowl.
In another bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar, soda and flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in cocoa-butter mixture.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cook at 80% power for 11 to 14 minutes.
Cover.
Put marshmallows on top of cake.
Let stand until melted, then frost.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream cheese and sugar.
Add bananas, strawberries, pineapple and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip and freeze.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add remaining ingredients together.
Line a baking dish with taco flavored Doritos.
Pour meat mixture over Doritos and top with grated cheese.
Bake until hot and bubbly.

title: robert's chicken n' dumplins
directions: Boil chicken breasts and bouillon cubes in water in a 5-quart kettle until tender.
Take out the chicken and shred with fork. Return to kettle.
Mix 2 cups of chicken broth with 4 cups of flour, salt and pepper until dough forms.
Roll out on a floured surface until 1/8-inch thick.
Cut dough into 1 x 2-inch strips. Put dough strips back into kettle individually all across kettle. Cook until dumplins are done (approximately one hour on medium). Stir occasionally.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: hot jalapeno rice
directions: In a large skillet, saute onions, bell pepper and jalapeno pepper in butter.
Add rice, chicken broth, salt and mushrooms. Cover and simmer until liquid disappears.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Butter	baking	dish.
Add
dry rice and pour hot water over rice.
Place pieces of uncooked chicken on top.
Sprinkle paprika over
chicken.
Add
mushroom
soup, then dried onion soup mix. Bake
covered at 375° for 1 1/2 hours and uncovered 1/2 hour.

title: artichoke rice salad
directions: Cook rice as directed and cool.
Mix everything together. Chill.
Makes 8 servings.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Cook Veg-All, corn and onion in a pot for 5 minutes, then drain.
Add the cheese, mayonnaise and 2 tablespoons Ritz crackers (crumbs).
Mix real good.
Melt stick of butter; crumble more Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top.
Pour margarine over it.
Bake in casserole dish for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: irish bread
directions: Bring
raisins	to
boil in enough water to cover.
Add margarine, cool and add beaten eggs and remaining ingredients. Divide
into
greased
loaf
pans
and
bake
at 300° about 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: chow mein
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat slowly until done in 1 tablespoon of oil. Remove from heat.
In another pan, simmer the onions in 1 tablespoon oil briefly.
Add meat.
Saute the bamboo shoots and mushrooms and add to meat.
Saute the celery slightly. All vegetables should be a bit crunchy. Add to meat.
Finally, add the bean sprouts.
Make a mixture of the sugar, cornstarch, soy sauce and soup stock and add to meat mixture, beating thoroughly and stirring. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: hamburg bean pot
directions: Place beans in a large pot.
Add water and bring to a boil. Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand for 1 hour. Return to heat and cook until almost tender.
Add all other ingredients but the ground beef.
Brown ground beef in a skillet until crumbly.
Add to bean mixture.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until the vegetables are tender.

title: krispie kubes(crispy, crunchy and light!)
directions: In a large bowl, combine fruit sweetener and peanut butter. Microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add mashed potato flakes and vanilla; cool slightly.
Stir in rice cereal.
Press into 9 x 9-inch Teflon coated pan.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
When cool, cut into squares.
Makes 20 bars.

title: peanut butter cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownie mix as directed. Spoon into muffin pan cups.
Place a candy on top of each cupcake. Bake 20 to 25 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center of candy comes out clean.
Cool cupcakes for 10 minutes.
Remove cupcakes from muffin pan cups.
Makes 18 cupcakes.

title: lona's chalupas
directions: Put all ingredients into a crockpot, cover to simmer for about 5 hours until roast shreds and beans are done.
Remove any bones and fat. Shred the meat. Return to the pot uncover and cook for a further 30 minutes or more.
Serve with any of the following toppings; olives, corn chips, shredded lettuce, onion, cheddar cheese, avocado, taco sauce or salsa, sour cream or tomato.

title: lazy man's peach pie
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Mix flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add milk and spread over butter.
Pour peaches over this, leaving juice for last ingredient to be poured over all. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift flour; reserve 1/4 cup for dredging raisins and nuts.
Sift remaining flour with soda and spices.
Add to creamed mixture along with buttermilk. Stir in jam and orange juice.
Fold in dredged raisins and nuts. Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: slush punch
directions: Mix in a large bucket.
Freeze until ready to use.
Thaw partly and add 2 or 3 bottles of ginger ale to serve.

title: chinese chicken slaw
directions: In a small bowl, whisk together dressing and soy sauce.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, toss the remaining ingredients except the noodles.
Pour the dressing mix over the salad and toss well to coat.
Chill until ready to serve.
Sprinkle noodles over salad before serving.
Makes 12 cups.

title: apricot candy roll
directions: Combine sugar, milk, apricots and butter in saucepan.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil.
Stirring occasionally, boil until soft ball in water or 236°.
Cool to 120°; add vanilla and nuts. Beat until stiff enough to knead; place on a board and knead until smooth.
Shape in a small roll and refrigerate for several hours.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 stick margarine in 9 x 11-inch or 10 x 13-inch pan. Layer trimmed pieces bread in pan.
Place 1 slice American cheese on bread.
Layer 1 to 2 pounds fried sausage, bacon or ham on top of cheese.
Repeat layer of bread.
Repeat layer of cheese.
Repeat layer of meat.
(For all layers use same amount as first layer.) Pour beaten eggs, milk, salt and pepper over layer of meat. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spicy glazed pecans(sweet, salty, spicy)
directions: Spread a 24 x 12-inch sheet of aluminum foil on flat surface. Coat lightly with vegetable oil.
Combine sugar, butter, pepper and water in saucepan over medium-low heat.
When butter has melted, add pecans.
Continue to cook 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour pecan mixture over prepared foil.
Quickly spread mixture out, separating pecans.
Sprinkle with salt; let cool 30 minutes.
Glazed pecans can be stored in airtight container in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: easy apple kuchen
directions: Combine dry cake mix, margarine and coconut.
Mix as for pie crust.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: goose stuffed with fruit
directions: Sprinkle goose inside and out with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Melt butter or margarine in a large saucepan.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in apple, apricots, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Spoon stuffing lightly into cavity.
Truss bird. Cover breast with bacon slices and cheesecloth soaked in melted bacon drippings.

title: quick apple bars
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except confectioners sugar. Bake in a greased jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/4 x 1-inch) for about 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle top with confectioners sugar after removing from oven.

title: caribbean turkey wings
directions: Place all ingredients, except turkey, in food processor or blender and process until thoroughly mixed.
Pour mixture over wings and marinate for 1 hour in refrigerator.
Bake in 375° oven about 1 hour, basting occasionally, turning once, or until no longer pink on the inside.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and salt.
Mix well.
Add pineapple and vanilla.
Stir in. Pour into tube or oblong pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine 1/4 cup soup with remaining ingredients except water; mix thoroughly.
Shape into 6 patties; place in 14 x 10 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spoon off fat. Combine remaining soup and water; pour over meat and bake 10 minutes more.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix per directions on box. Add in 1 package of frozen coconut. Cook in 13 x 9 x 2 pan according to the time on the box. While cooking, mix the sugar into the evaporated milk. After the cake is removed from the oven and slightly cooled, stick it with a fork all over to create drain holes. Spoon the milk/sugar mixture all over the cake. Mix the second package of coconut into the Cool Whip and spread over the top of the cake. THIS IS IMPORTANT.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 days before eating.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Chop shrimp very fine (blender does a good job of chopping). Mix in rest of ingredients.
Serve with Wheat Thins, Triscuits, etc.

title: banana salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and milk.
Add pineapple, pie filling and bananas.
Nuts are optional.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add well beaten eggs.
Add flour and mashed bananas alternately.
Add soda, salt, nuts and vanilla. Bake in loaf pan at 350° until brown.

title: applesauce pork chops
directions: Put pork chops in baking dish or pan.
Add about 1/2 cup water to pan or dish.
Bake about 1 hour at 350° in oven.
Take out of oven and spread applesauce mixture over pork chops.
Bake for another 30 minutes.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: chicken mousse
directions: Bring 2 cups broth to boil.
Dissolve gelatin and salt in broth.
Add cold broth, cayenne and vinegar.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Mix whipped topping, mayonnaise, chicken, celery and pimento.
Chill.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes without paring them.
When tender, drain and remove skins.
Cut in half lengthwise and arrange in buttered baking dish.
Season with salt.
Heat butter, honey and orange juice; add to potatoes.
Bake in oven at 400° until potatoes are brown.

title: trifle(large bowl)
directions: Tear cake into small pieces.
Put in a large bowl.
Mix dry jello with strawberries and pour over cake.
Mix pudding and pour over sliced bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: chicken manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti shells according to package directions. Drain and set aside.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Open hot dog or hamburger buns; butter.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Broil for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Good with spaghetti or lasagna.

title: carrots ala orange(serves 5)
directions: Combine ingredients in covered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes; stir occasionally.

title: ice tea
directions: Boil sugar and 1 cup water to make a syrup.
Boil 3 quarts of water and pour over loose tea. Let stand 3 minutes. Strain over 3 sprigs mint.
Add syrup to tea. When cold, add juice of 3 lemons.

title: pudding in a cloud
directions: Spoon whipped topping evenly into a bowl or into 6 dessert dishes. Using back of spoon, spread topping on bottom and side of bowl or dishes. Pour milk into medium bowl. Add pudding mix. Beat with wire whisk for 2 minutes and let stand 5 minutes. Spoon pudding into center of whipped topping and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: best peanut brittle
directions: In a heavy saucepan, stir together the sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved and mixture comes to a boil.
Cook, without stirring, until temperature reaches 280° on candy thermometer or until small amount dropped into cold water separates into a thread that is hard, but not brittle.
Stir in peanuts so mixture continues to boil.
Cook, stirring often, until temperature reaches 300° or until dropped into cold water separates into threads that are hard and brittle.
Remove from heat.
Pour into buttered pan without spreading.
When cool, bread into pieces.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: heavenly orange fluff
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add undrained pineapple and orange juice concentrate.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in oranges and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chil until firm.
Beat pudding and milk until smooth; fold in Cool Whip. Spread over jello and chill.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well; divide batter into 2 greased pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Saute butter and onion in baking dish.
Lay asparagus in butter.
Pour mushroom soup over asparagus.
Sprinkle cheese over mixture.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 20 minutes.

title: stuffed apple treats
directions: Combine mayonnaise or cream cheese, nuts and raisins, cranberries or dates; set aside.
Core each apple.
Stuff cavity with mixture.
Yields 2 servings.

title: new york cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat together cream cheese and sugar until light and smooth.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and cornstarch only until thoroughly mixed.
Stir in sour cream until well blended. Pour into crust which has been pressed into 9-inch springform pan and prebaked for 8 minutes.
Bake cheesecake 45 minutes.
Allow to cool in oven with door propped slightly open for 3 hours.
Chill.

title: rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Prepare Bundt pan by wiping inside with shortening and dusting with flour.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped pecans in bottom of pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour into prepared Bundt pan.
Bake about 1 hour until toothpick comes out clean.
When cake comes out of oven, poke lots of holes in hot cake with toothpick.
Do not remove cake from pan yet.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix all except crackers.
Mix well.
Let stand several hours. Stir often.
Store in an airtight container.
Can be frozen.
For a large crowd, double.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Place the sugar, milk, butter and cocoa in a saucepan.
Stir them over quick heat until the sugars dissolved.
Permit the syrup to boil.
Cook it slowly without stirring for 6 minutes.
Stir in the vanilla and peanuts slowly.
Drop the candy by the spoonful onto waxed paper.

title: light rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup of the quart of warm water.
Add all the other ingredients and enough flour to work dough easy; let rise.
Work down good each time you take off rolls.
Keep extra batter in refrigerator.
Roll out like biscuits, about 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter, place in greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Brush tops with melted butter; let rise.
Bake in 400° oven until light brown.

title: flaky pie crust
directions: Blend
flour,
salt
and
Crisco thoroughly with pastry blender.
Add
liquid and mix with fork.
Toss 1/2 of dough on well-floured
pastry
cloth.
Roll lightly outward from center until right size of pie tin.
Dough should not stick either to pastry
cloth or rolling pin.
Use sufficient flour to prevent this.

title: low calorie chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in casserole dish (2-quart size).
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crab rangoon
directions: Mix the cream cheese, crabmeat and onions. Place 1/2 teaspoon of mixture in center of wrapper. Wet the inside lip of wrapper with a wet finger (having a bowl of water nearby helps). Fold diagonally and seal with fingers by pressing together. Cook in hot oil until edges are golden (10 to 15 seconds). Serve with sweet and sour sauce or hot Chinese mustard.

title: golden crab puffs
directions: Drain crab and break apart.
Combine Bisquick, cheese, green onions and crabmeat.
(Several baby shrimp added here adds a nice touch.)

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Dab a 9 1/2 x 11-inch glass dish generously with 1/4 cup of margarine.
In separate bowl, mix soups, water and onions together.
Pour half the soup mixture into greased glass dish. Top with chicken.
Salt and pepper lightly.
Top with remaining soup mixture.
Cover and bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: indian taco
directions: Make your dough or have store bought.
Roll it out into pancake shape.
Put it in pan or skillet until crispy.
Have your hamburger cooked and mixed with beans.
Put it over your fry bread with your chopped tomatoes, lettuce, cheese and sauce.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Whip with electric mixer.
Hollow and fill a round sourdough bread.
Bake at 350° for 3 minutes.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook and drain shells, set aside.
Make sure spinach is thawed and drained very well.
Mix green onions, spinach, ricotta cheese, sour cream and 8 oz. of grated cheese, salt & pepper to taste, together in a large mixing bowl.
Take each shell and stuff with spinach mixture.
Place in bottom of 13x9 baking dish.
Each pan holds about 15 shells.
Add ground beef to marinara sauce.
Usually 2 jars are needed, spread evenly over top of shells.
Sprinkle top with the other 8 oz. bag of grated cheese.
Bake for about 30 mins. at 350 degrees.
Remove and let cool about 5-10 mins. before serving.
Makes two 13x9 in. baking pans.
Great for large family gathering.

title: cherry-cheese brownie bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Prepare brownie mix as directed on package except-bake 20 min. Beat vanilla, egg, milk and softened cream cheese in large bowl until smooth. Pour over baked brownie layer. Bake until topping is set, 25 min. Cool 2 hours; spread with pie filling. Store in refrigerator.

title: mushroom onion soup
directions: Trim mushrooms stems level with the caps.
Finely chop the stems and thinly slice caps.
In a large saucepan, melt butter. Add mushrooms and onions.
Cook and stir over low heat for 5 minutes.
Blend in flour.
Add broth, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Reduce heat.
Add rice; cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until the rice is tender. Yields 4 servings.

title: candy-date roll
directions: Cook sugar and milk to 258° (soft ball stage).
Immediately add dates from which the seeds have been removed.
Beat until the dates are dissolved.
When stiff, add nuts and place in a cold wet towel.
Make a roll.
Put in refrigerator until chilled.
Slice as desired.

title: cheese frosted cauliflower
directions: Trim leaves and stem from base of medium head of cauliflower. Wash, cook whole head in boiling salted water for 12 to 15 minutes. Drain and place in ungreased shallow pan.
In shallow bowl, combine salad dressing and mustard; spread over cauliflower.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until cheese bubbles and melts.

title: mexican coffee
directions: Place cinnamon and vanilla in coffeepot.
Brew coffee according to coffeepot manufacturer, using the cold water. Discard grounds.
Whip the cream, adding brown sugar to taste until stiff.
Pour coffee into cup; top with whipped cream.

title: miniature cheese cakes
directions: Beat the cream cheese, sugar and eggs until soft and fluffy. Place one vanilla wafer cookie in each greased cupcake pan (or paper lined cupcake pan), flat side of cookie on the bottom. Place 2 tablespoons of mixture on top of each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Don't let them overbake!
Cool before they are removed from pan.
Top with small amount of canned pie filling.
Store in refrigerator.

title: christmas lime salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients with 1 cup boiling water.
Stir until marshmallows melt.
Refrigerate until partially congealed. Blend in whipped cream, pineapple cream cheese and pecans.
Chill until set.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together by hand cake mix, butter and 1 egg until soft dough forms.
Press into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Mix cream cheese and eggs with beater until smooth.
Add sugar, a little at a time until mixture is creamy.
Pour over first mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° until brown all over (approximately 40 to 45 minutes).
Cool and cut into squares.
Better if refrigerated overnight.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix together jello and pineapple.
Heat until hot, but do not boil.
Set aside to cool. Add the cottage cheese.
Before serving, add the Cool Whip. Chill until ready to serve.

title: venison mushroom chops
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Brown chops lightly on both sides. Put in ovenproof dish; set aside.
Using same butter in frying pan, saute mushrooms, onion and egg together with salt and pepper. Spoon equal amounts on top of each chop.
Bake in preheated 350° oven, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake for another 10 minutes, or until cheese has melted.
(This recipe also works with pork chops.)

title: taco casserole
directions: Layer rice, chili beans, cheese, browned hamburger meat and taco mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Top with Doritos, diced tomatoes and lettuce after baking.
Makes a 9 x 13-inch pan very full.

title: quick yeast bread
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water with 1 teaspoon sugar.
Scald milk; stir in 1/3 cup sugar and salt.
Cool until lukewarm.
(Pour milk into mixing bowl and it will cool faster.)
Put butter in warm milk pan to melt.
When cool, combine milk mixture and yeast mixture; combine beaten eggs.
Add about 4 cups of the flour and beat well until smooth.
Add butter and beat smooth.
Beat in enough flour to make smooth elastic, but not too stiff, dough. Place in a lightly greased bowl; turn dough over.

title: pizza lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain. Heat oven to 350°. Grease 9 x 13 glass baking dish. In medium saucepan, combine pizza sauce and tomatoes; cook until heated through. In medium bowl, combine Ricotta and Italian seasoning.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Drain cherries and measure liquid.
Add water, if necessary, to make 1 cup liquid.
Heat liquid and add to gelatin in a medium-sized bowl.
When gelatin is dissolved, add Coca-Cola and juice drained from crushed pineapple.
Chill until consistency of egg whites.
Add halved cherries, pineapple and pecans.
Pour into dish to congeal.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine in pot and add rest of ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: johnstown spuds
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and 1/2 stick of margarine.
Add one package of cheese.
Spread over potatoes in 9
x 13 pan.
Add remaining cheese and margarine on top.
Bake one hour at 350 degrees.

title: jello rainbow cake
directions: Mix and bake two 8 or 9-inch layers from white cake mix, using directions on box.
Put cake layers in clean cake pans.
Put a bunch of holes in cake with a pencil (eraser end).
Mix together Jell-O and water; pour evenly over cake.
You may use different flavors for each layer.
Put in refrigerator.
Cool until firm. Frost with Cool Whip and serve.

title: guiltless brownies
directions: Combine cocoa powder, oil and bananas in food processor or blender.
Puree until smooth. Combine sugar, eggs, flour and pureed cocoa mixture in a mixing bowl and beat until blended. Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares. Makes 24 brownies.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slice onions and bell peppers.
Mince garlic. Drain tomatoes. Cook beef in large frying pan until no longer pink.
Remove with slotted spoon. Add onions, bell peppers, garlic, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Cook until soft, about 15 minutes.
Remove with slotted spoon and return meat to the pan. Drain tomatoes and add with vinegar, cumin, oregano, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Break up tomatoes. Simmer 10 minutes.
Slice jalapenos and grate cheeses. Line bottom and sides of 2-quart baking dish with 4 tortillas.
Put half the meat and top with half the onion mixture.
Cover with 2 tortillas. Repeat layering. Top with cheeses and sprinkle with jalapeno peppers.
Cover loosely with foil.
Bake 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes.

title: very best pierogi dough
directions: Melt butter in warm milk.
Add egg yolks.
Pour flour and salt over warm milk and mix well.
Cover and let dough rest for 10 minutes or more. Knead for 2 minutes.
Let rest again.
Roll and fill with your favorite fillings.
(Can also be used for homemade noodles.)
Drop in boiling water.
Cook for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Add cheese and soup.
Stir until melted.
Place broccoli in casserole dish; pour in soup mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes and serve.

title: cereal balls
directions: After grinding cereal, add honey and peanut butter. Blend. Add milk until mixture can be rolled into balls. Refrigerate in a covered container.

title: pork sausage meat loaf
directions: Blend milk, ketchup and mustard thoroughly.
Mix all ingredients together with hands.
Form into loaf and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Drain fat before serving.

title: chocolate marbled cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease & flour two 9 inch round cake pans. Cream the butter, then slowly add the 2 cups sugar, beating until thoroughly blended. Add the eggs, beating thoroughly, then mix in the vanilla. Combine the flour, 1 tsp of the baking soda and the salt and mix in a separate small dish. Add to the creamed mixture along with the buttermilk and beat until the batter is smooth.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crumble crackers and put raisins, pecans and cherries in crackers; melt margarine and marshmallows.
Pour mixture over crackers; mix well.
Mold as desired.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate.

title: chicken-n-wine
directions: Combine ingredients and pour over 2 to 3 pounds of chicken. Cover and bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: cheesy corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a 1-quart saucepan, melt butter on a simmer setting, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Gradually add flour, then milk, stirring as you add.
Cook on a simmer setting, stirring frequently until sauce thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: cinnamon plate
directions: Combine yeast and warm water.
Stir and set aside.
Combine milk, butter, 2 tablespoons sugar, salt and stir to melt butter. Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in yeast mixture.
Add flour gradually to form a stiff dough.
Knead to smooth.
Put in greased bowl, cover and raise 1 hour.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar, cinnamon and brown sugar with chopped nuts.
Pinch off pieces of risen dough.
Roll into strips in palms of hands, dip the strips into the butter, then into the cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Wind into
flat coil on a greased pizza pan.
Let raise 45 to 60 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and drizzle with a powdered sugar glaze.

title: baked rutabaga
directions: Wash rutabaga, peel and cut up in small pieces.
Boil in small amount of water until tender.
Put in blender all remaining ingredients.
Blend and then gradually add cooked rutabaga.
Blend until smooth.

title: macaroni and franks dinner
directions: Heat all ingredients in large saucepan. Serves 6.

title: diabetic chocolate nut squares
directions: Melt chocolate with shortening over hot water.
Add sucaryl, then beaten eggs.
Beat well, adding sugar gradually.
Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into chocolate mixture. Stir in walnuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 8 x 8 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 36 squares.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and blend well.
Add Karo, melted butter and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and cook at 350° until brown and firm.
No meringue is needed.

title: modena pork
directions: Place butter and oil in saute pan on medium-high heat. Lightly coat both sides of chops with flour, shaking off excess. Place in saute pan; careful not to overlap, along with sage leaves.
Cook chops to rich brown each side (about 2 minutes per side).
Add salt, pepper and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer slowly with lid slightly ajar for about 1 hour or until chops are tender. Turn chops occasionally while cooking.
Place chops on serving platter.
Reduce pan drippings to slightly thickened consistency by heat.
Tip and spoon off fat.
Pour remaining drippings over chops.
Serve with small whole potatoes and carrots.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, salt, pepper and onions in a 2 quart casserole dish.
Mix beef, milk, cracker crumbs and ketchup pour evenly over potatoes and bake in 350 degree oven for 1 hour.

title: cheese soup
directions: Prepare cream sauce with butter and flour; slowly add milk, salt and cheese.
Saute celery, onion and carrots in butter.
Cook until crunchy, but not soft.
Add chicken broth.
Combine with cream sauce.
Cook until well blended.
Can be frozen.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Place in 2 greased loaf pans or muffin pans. Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken scalapini
directions: Saute mushrooms, green peppers and onion in oil and butter; remove this after 10 to 15 minutes.
Use meat tenderizer to pound meat.
Dust the chicken in flour and add to juices in pan; brown these.
After browning, reduce flame to simmer or a bit higher and add Marsala cooking wine frequently as it evaporates (you should use 3/4 to 1 bottle).
Add mushrooms, green peppers and onions after 15 minutes.
Cook on simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mom's creamy peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook first 3 items to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and stir in last three ingredients.
Set to cool several minutes, then beat with spoon unti it begins to smartly thicken, then put mixture out onto a greased plate.

title: pretty christmas mold
directions: Grind
cranberries and oranges together.
Add sugar and let stand
while preparing gelatin mixture.
Mix gelatin with orange juice
and
set
aside.
Dissolve
cherry jello in hot water
and add orange juice/gelatin mixture.
Add lemon juice and
stir well.
Pour
over
cranberry/orange
mixture.
Mix thoroughly; add nuts and mix again.
Pour into oiled mold and chill until firm.
Make at least one day ahead.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine macaroni, shrimp and French dressing.
Toss and chill.

title: sheet cake
directions: Sift flour in a bowl.
Add sugar.
In a pan, melt 2 sticks butter, water and cocoa; heat to boiling.
Pour over flour. Beating on low speed, add eggs and buttermilk with soda in it. Add vanilla.
Bake on greased cookie sheet lined with wax paper. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Frost while hot.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: grilled dijon chicken
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine all ingredients, except chicken; stir until thoroughly combined.
Add chicken; turn to coat with mayonnaise mixture.
Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate overnight or at least 4 hours.
Arrange chicken on broiling rack, being sure to coat chicken well with mayonnaise mixture.
Broil for 10 minutes per side and serve.

title: sweet sour relish
directions: Drain and rinse sauerkraut in a colander; drain well.
Cut finely the celery, onions, green peppers and pimentos.
Mix all together.
Add sugar and white vinegar.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Pour other ingredients, mixed all together, into cooled pan of butter.
Pour fruit over batter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ranch casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in skillet with meat; heat through.
Place in baking dish.
Put cheese on top of mixture; top with Fritos. Bake at 350° until cheese has melted.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix together and spoon over chicken (or dip chicken in mixture and place in baking dish).
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: standard muffins
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 20 minutes, until golden brown.
You may add to this blueberries, raspberries or apples, or choose one of these:
1 teaspoon grated citrus peel, 1 teaspoon vanilla, 1 teaspoon grated cheese or 1 teaspoon ground spice.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up bread and put in casserole or baking dish. Brown sausage and drain.
Put over bread.
Sprinkle cheese over it. Beat eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper together.
Pour over other mixture. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 40 minutes. Cheese will rise to top during baking.
Best to let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cranberry orange nut bread
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Cut margarine into dry ingredients with a pastry blender until it resembles fine crumbs. Combine orange juice and beaten egg.
Stir into dry ingredients. Stir grated orange rind, nuts and berries into mixture.
Grease a 1 pound coffee can or loaf pan.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
(Doubled recipe makes 3 (1 pound) coffee cans.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients
and
mix well.
Makes a little better than a 1/2 quart; keep chilled.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix lightly and add salad dressing to moisten.

title: quickie cobbler
directions: Prepare fruit; place in baking dish.
Beat egg, sugar and cornstarch; mix thoroughly.
Add milk and vanilla; pour over fruit.
Make batter of 1/2 cup flour, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 stick softened margarine.
Sprinkle over cobbler.
Bake at 375° until brown on top.

title: creamy crab spread
directions: Mix in small saucepan.
Heat over low heat until cheese melts and ingredients are mixed well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix flour in at low speed first.
Fold in blueberries.
Bake at 350° in a tube or Bundt pan for 1 hour.
