Put a light dusting of 10x sugar on top of cake after baking.

title: sweet potato surprise
directions: Add the cream to the potatoes, being careful not to use too much; add the sugar, salt, beaten egg and coconut.
Let stand until cool.

title: spaghetti(less) casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and tomato sauce.
Heat to bubbling.
Pour into 2-quart casserole. Cool slightly.
Spread sour cream over meat mixture.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over sour cream.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put into 2 greased bread pans and top with mixture of 1 tablespoon soft oleo and 1/2 cup white sugar. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: southern chicken pie
directions: *May use mushroom soup instead of celery soup.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and place into a greased casserole dish.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef and sausage.
Put through a grinder until fine. Brown onion separately and add together.

Add the tomatoes and baking soda. Cook with water for about 40 minutes. Add spices for the last 15 minutes of the 40 minutes and adding the beans for the last 5 minutes of the 15 minutes. Skim off any grease that forms from the meats.
Serve hot. Can be cooked ahead and reheated easily.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Boil until tender.
Drain and place in electric mixer bowl with stick of butter.
Beat at high speed until smooth.
Add eggs and sugar.
Beat until ingredients have the consistency of cake batter.
Season with flavoring and spices. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: *To make use 1 tablespoon vinegar and enough milk to equal 1 cup.

title: cheese chess
directions: Mix together cake mix, 1 egg and margarine.
Press into greased pan.
Mix together 2 eggs, cream cheese and sugar.
Pour over first mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, syrup and salt.
Boil for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add soda; stir.
Pour caramel over popped corn.
Spread on baking sheet.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cool and store.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice green tomatoes and lay on a plate; smear each slice with a layer of honey, then cover each slice well with flour.
Lay these slices with covered side down in a well oiled pan.
Treat other side same as first.
Fry slowly until well browned, then turn over and brown other side.
May require a bit of oil on top before turning.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 400° until top is light brown.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Beat peanut butter and butter with a fork until light.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt.
Add peanut butter mixture and mix until coarse crumbs.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Just before serving, add 1 quart ginger ale and 1/2 gallon orange sherbet.

title: potato refrigerator rolls
directions: Though pie fillings typically bake in an unbaked shell, it's best to partially bake the pastry before adding most milk-based custard fillings.
If these are poured in an unbaked crust, you may end up with soggy pastry.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Toss chicken pieces in egg.
Sprinkle with cornstarch and toss to coat.
In wok, brown chicken in oil, remove and set aside.
Add enough water to pineapple liquid for 1 cup liquid.
Stir in vinegar, sugar, chicken base and green pepper.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer for 2 minutes. Blend water and cornstarch; stir in wok.
Heat until thick.
Add chicken, pineapple and carrots.
Serve over hot rice.

title: crunchy sweet pickles
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, mustard seed and celery seed in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; be sure the sugar melts.
Set aside for 30 minutes or longer.
Pour pickles from jars into a strainer; drain juice and rinse well.
Slice into 1/4-inch slices and rinse 2 or 3 more times.
Drain and pack pickle slices into jars. Reheat the syrup and pour over pickles.
Refrigerate 12 hours before eating!

title: round steak with rich gravy
directions: Cut steak into serving sizes.
Place in slow cooker.
Add soup mix, water and soup.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: pasta with sausage and creamy tomato sauce
directions: Remove casings from sausage. Crumble meat. Melt butter in deep, heavy frying pan. Add sausage and onion and cook SLOWLY until meat is lightly browned. Stir in garlic, tomatoes, tomato sauce and wine. Increase heat to medium and boil. Cover. Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes. Mix in peas and cream and cook until thickened. Spoon over cooked pasta. Mix lightly. Top with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: bisquick cornmeal cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add eggs and mix. Add cornmeal, baking powder and Bisquick with milk.
Bake until toothpick tester comes out clean.

title: butter bean casserole
directions: Put beef and water in frying pan.
Cover and cook slowly for 2 minutes.
Add onion and pepper and cook 3 minutes more.
Pour off drippings.
Blend in flour, beans, tomatoes and salt.
Put in 2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake for 20 minutes, then remove cover and bake 20 minutes more at 350°.

title: yellow rice casserole
directions: Cook yellow rice as directed; cut onion and bell pepper into small pieces.
In a fryer, brown beef; drain.
In a large dish, mix yellow rice, beef, onion and bell pepper; put into a glass dish and top with several pieces of cheese to cover the top.
Put into oven for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: big caramel corn
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in brown sugar and corn syrup.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil, without stirring, for 5 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour over top of corn.
Mix well.
Turn on cookie sheet, pressing down.
Bake at 250° for 30 to 45 minutes, turning after 15 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Break up and store in tightly covered container.

title: chicken a la king
directions: In a medium saucepan over medium heat, combine margarine, onions and bell peppers.
Saute until tender and add cream cheese, mushroom soup and chicken soup.
Cook over low heat until well blended and saucy.
Add pimento, mushrooms, chicken and wine. Blend well.
This may be frozen.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: custard pie
directions: Heat milk and sugar to boiling point.
Beat eggs until foamy; add nutmeg and beat for 12 minutes.
Add hot milk to egg mixture. Put in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until set.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute beef and onions in butter until brown.
Add flour and seasonings.
Cook five minutes.
Add soup and simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat, but do not boil.
Serve over warm noodles.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Scald milk in saucepan.
Combine flour, sugar and salt and add slowly to milk, stirring constantly.
Continue stirring and cook over low heat until thickened.
Beat egg yolks, then add a little of the hot mixture and cook another 2 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool.
Add bananas before mixture is cold.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Use 1/2 of tomato mixture. Mix well with meat.
Put in microwave bowl with glass in the middle.
Use other half of tomato mixture on top.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Chill the dough before cutting.
Brown sugar may be put on if you wish.
Bake in a 400° oven.
You will need a large container to make this in.
The dough needs to be stiffer than biscuit dough.
Dough doesn't have to be chilled if you prefer not to.

title: rice and mushrooms
directions: Melt margarine in a 2 qt. casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Easy & tasty.

title: stuffed crabs
directions: Microwave butter in a 2-quart dish for 1 minute on High. Saute onion, bell pepper, celery and garlic on High for 5 minutes. Stir once or twice.
Add onion tops, parsley and lemon juice. Saute on High for 3 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, Tabasco, Worcestershire sauce, water, bread crumbs and crabmeat.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Add all ingredients except tomato.
Marinate overnight.
Add tomato before serving.

title: easy pickled peaches
directions: Mix peach syrup, sugar, vinegar and spices in a saucepan. Bring to a boil. Add peaches and cool. Refrigerate 24 hours and serve cold. Serves 6 to 8.

title: cinnamon sauce
directions: Bring cider, sugar and cinnamon to a boil.
Mix cornstarch with water to form paste. Mix with the cider mixture to thicken. Cook until clear or the consistency you wish.

title: marinated raw vegetables
directions: Marinate vegetables overnight in the dressing.
Keep refrigerated.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients and blend. Add oatmeal, nuts and raisins. Roll into balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: orange juice cooler
directions: Combine buttermilk or yogurt and orange juice in blender and mix well.
Pour into chilled glass and garnish with orange slice. Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: chicken bake
directions: Sprinkle chicken pieces with seasoned salt; let stand 1/2 hour at room temperature.
Grease 3-quart casserole and spread rice over bottom.
Layer with mushrooms and chicken.
Pour soups over mushrooms, rice and chicken.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix and savory over mixture.
Pour broth around sides.
Cover tightly and put in 350° oven.
Bake 1 1/4 hours.
Garnish with parsley.

title: easy strawberry ice cream
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and pour into ice cream canister. Fill to fill line with milk.
Freeze and enjoy!

title: meat loaf
directions: Using only 1/2 of the tomato sauce, mix all the ingredients. Place in large or 2 smaller loaf pans.
Microwave for 12 to 14 minutes on High.
Or, can bake at 350° for 3/4 to 1 hour.

title: canned homemade salsa
directions: Peel and core tomatoes.
Add other ingredients.
(Use as much pepper to make it as hot as you want it.)
Cook until onion is done.
Drain juice and put into pint jars.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Pour all ingredients into pie shell and top with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cheese should be completely melted and crust brown.

title: hot wings
directions: Grill your wings slowly to get them good and done.
This is for about 12 wings, so just double as needed.
In a large bowl, mix the hot sauce, butter, red pepper and garlic salt.
After wings are cooked, put in this sauce and stir around good to get sauce on all of them.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix with fork. Pour in unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in salt water until tender.
Drain.
In large skillet mix soup, onion and cheese until cheese is melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cabbage.
Pour into an ungreased 2-quart baking dish.
Lightly brown crumbs in butter.
Sprinkle on top. Bake uncovered at 350°
for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: crumb pie
directions: Put flour, sugar and lard in bowl and mix to a crumb.
Save out 1/4 cup crumbs.
Add 1 cup buttermilk to beaten eggs.
Beat into crumb mixture until smooth.

title: peach cobble-up
directions: Mix all ingredients except peaches.
Spread in an ungreased square pan.
Drain peaches, reserving 1 cup syrup.
Arrange peaches on mixture in pan; pour reserved syrup over peaches.
Bake until golden, about 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Makes 9 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, onion, green pepper, pimento, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice in bowl; mix well. Shape into ball.
Roll in pecans.
Chill for several hours.
Place on serving plate.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 15 servings.

title: commander's chow hall catfish
directions: In a large, doubled grocery bag, mix dry ingredients.
Place damp, not dripping wet, catfish in the bag.
(You can put 2 whole catfish or 4 to 5 fillets in the bag at one time.)
Close bag and shake it until fish is thoroughly coated.
Remove fish and lay it on wax paper to allow it to air dry.

title: buttermilk pecan pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in flour, lemon juice and vanilla.
Stir in buttermilk and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes or until set.
Cool on a wire rack.
Stor in the refrigerator.
Yields 8 servings.

title: party chili
directions: Heat oil in 8 to 10-quart kettle.
Lightly saute onions and garlic.
Add meat, breaking up and stirring with wooden spoon until color changes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: chicken soup
directions: In a saucepan with water, onion, garlic, oil and salt you cook the chicken and the chorizo.
When it is all cooked, you add the potatoes and the chopped carrots.
You take the chicken and the chorizo out and cut it in small pieces and then you add it again.

title: lime pound cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mom's popovers
directions: Whisk together all ingredients.
Fill greased Pyrex cups or muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 450° about 20 minutes.
Turn oven down to 350° and bake another 40 minutes, until golden brown.
Do not open oven door during baking or they will fall.
Coat immediately with butter.
Makes about 9 popovers.

title: jambalaya
directions: In a heavy pot or Dutch oven, heat oil; add onions, peppers, celery and garlic.
Cook until vegetables are tender, about 5 minutes.
Add ham and sausage.
Cook over medium heat about 8 minutes or until brown.
Stir occasionally.
Add rice.
Cook and stir 5 minutes or until rice is lightly brown.
Add tomatoes, beef broth and Cajun seasoning.
Mix well.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer covered until rice is tender.
Stir in shrimp and parsley.
Cook until the shrimp turn pink, about 5 minutes.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Simmer hamburger and spaghetti sauce for 15 minutes.
Add onion if desired.
Mix all 3 cheeses together.
Cook noodles according to box.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch baking dish, hamburger, 3 noodles and cheese.
Layer this 3 times. Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 400° for 1 hour or until cheese has melted.

title: cheesy ham casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese and croutons.
Spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and croutons.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pizza burger
directions: Combine
meat
and
seasonings.
Shape
into	6
oval patties;
broil both sides to desired doneness.
Heat together tomatoes,
tomato sauce,
mushrooms
and
oregano;	simmer	15 minutes.
For each sandwich, top bread half with patty; spread with sauce. Top with cheese, onion and additional sauce; broil until cheese melts.
Yield: 6 sandwiches.

title: mothers' hodgepodge
directions: Add 1 to 3 cans of water for desired consistency.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: viva la chicken
directions: Boil
chicken
or
turkey breast.
Cut in small pieces. Cut tortillas in small strips or spread Fritos in greased 9 x 13-inch pan,
starting
with
tortillas.
Layer with chicken, soup mixture, onion, salsa and finish layering with cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: low-fat ham ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into ball; serve with crackers, chips or pretzels.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt butter.
Add cocoa and stir until smooth.
Blend in sweetened condensed milk (stir constantly until mixture is thick, smooth and glossy, about 4 minutes).
Remove from heat, stir in vanilla.
Chill 3 to 4 hours or until firm.
Shape into 1/4-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Chill until firm (1 to 2 hours). Store, covered, in refrigerator.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: chess cake
directions: Beat until real stiff the cake mix (box), 1 egg and margarine. Press in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar (confectioners).
Pour on top of first mixture. Bake 50 minutes at 325°.

title: after brunch cheese n' cake
directions: Using greased and floured 10-inch tube pan, bake at package temperature 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool; remove from pan.
Slice in 3 layers.
Mix cream cheese with sugar and vanilla; add Cool Whip and sour cream.
Beat until smooth; spread on first layer.
Spoon jam on top; add second layer and third layer, repeating as for first.
Sprinkle with toasted coconut.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Boil oleo, cocoa and water.
Add flour and sugar.
Mix in soda, sour milk, eggs, vanilla and salt to first ingredients. Bake in jelly roll pan at 350° until done.

title: spiced party nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Set rack in center of oven.
Line cookie sheets with foil.
Cook all ingredients (except nuts) over low heat until sugar dissolves and butter melts.
Increase to medium heat; add nuts and toss until coated.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Put layer of crumbs in greased baking dish.
Cover with layer of apples.
Sprinkle with sugar mixture.
Continue until all ingredients are used.
Have layer of crumbs on top.
Pour melted fat over top.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Remove cover for last 10 minutes to brown top. Makes 4 servings.

title: pineapple muffins
directions: Stir together until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serve hot.

title: recipe for mothers
directions: Mix well and spread over a lifetime.

title: peppermint fudge
directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place butter in 4-quart microwavable bowl.
Cook at High for 30 seconds in microwave oven. Add sugar and milk; mix well.
Cook at High for 8 minutes, stirring well after each 2 minutes of cooking.
Remove from oven.
Add chocolate pieces; stir until melted.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Spread into prepared pan.
Chill several hours or until firm.
Cut into squares; store tightly covered in refrigerator.

title: drop donuts
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add butter and sugar.
Mix flour with baking powder and salt.
Mix together with milk.
Drop by teaspoon in deep fat (Crisco).
Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon or icing, whatever you prefer.

title: sandy's french dressing
directions: Blend all together in blender.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields 1 quart.

title: simple salsa
directions: You will need 1 hand blender or food processor.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Put first 4 ingredients into
a pan and bring to a boil.
Add vanilla.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes and remove from heat.
Add quick oats and pecans.
Drop in small amount onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: breakfast bread pudding
directions: Remove and discard crusts from bread; cut bread into cubes. Toss lightly with cream cheese cubes; place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish (pan).
In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add milk, syrup and salt; mix well.
Pour over bread mixture.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 30 minutes before baking.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean. Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry souffle
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 3/4 cup syrup drained from strawberries.
Gradually blend the mayonnaise and orange juice with cream cheese (I use electric beater).
Stir into gelatin.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Beat 2 egg whites, gradually adding 1/4 cup sugar, until stiff peaks form.
Fold into gelatin.
Add strawberries.
Pour into 1-quart souffle dish. Chill.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool.

title: easter egg
directions: Cook sugar, water, Karo and salt until it forms a soft ball. Don't stir while cooking. Add a little at a time to stiffly beaten egg white. Add vanilla. Beat until it gets a dull color and starts to set.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: sixty minute rolls
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
with
spoon;
let
rise
15 minutes.
Punch down.
Let rise 15
minutes.
Shape into rolls and place on baking sheet (9 x 12-inch);
let rise 15 minutes. Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: broccoli rice cheese bake
directions: Prepare two cups of instant rice (Minute) as described on box. After done, add 1/2 stick of oleo or butter.
Place in casserole, around sides.
Prepare chopped broccoli and drain well.
Mix Cheez Whiz and cream of celery soup (undiluted) and heat until warm. Place broccoli inside of rice ring and pour cheese soup mixture over.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly, about 15 minutes.
Makes a large casserole, which is excellent.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of glass baking pan (11 x 8-inch). Mix batter.
Pour over butter layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cinnamon biscuits
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in baking pan and melt in preheated oven (temperature shown on canned biscuits) until a little bubbly. Stir a little and add biscuits and bake according to biscuit directions on can.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Put in 2 1/2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese and bake one hour in moderate oven.

title: ranch oyster crackers
directions: Mix dry salad dressing with dill weed and oil.
Pour over crackers; stir to coat.
Place in 250° oven for 15 to 20 minutes. Stir gently halfway through.
Cool completely before serving.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in loaf pan.
Drizzle ketchup on top of meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix crackers and 4 tablespoons butter in bowl until well blended.
Press mixture on bottom and 1 inch up side of 8-inch pie plate.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch greased metal pan.
Cream together shortening, brown sugar and eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into pan and bake in 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Make crust for 2-crust pie.
Peel and slice apples; combine with sugar and sprinkle with flour, cinnamon and butter.
Put on second crust.
Flute edges and cut holes in top for steam to escape.
Melt butter and spread on top.
Bake in 375° oven until apples are tender.

title: party punch
directions: Make sure all juices and champagne or ginger ale are cold.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: In a heavy 2-quart saucepan combine semi-sweet chocolate, butter or margarine and 3 tablespoons whipping cream.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly; until chocolate is melted.
This should take about 10 minutes.
Remove saucepan from heat. Gradually stir about half of the hot mixture into the beaten egg yolk.
Return egg mixture to saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
This should take about 2 minutes.
Remove saucepan from heat.
Stir in desired liquor or 3 tablespoons whipping cream.
Transfer chocolate mixture to a small mixer bowl.
Chill about 1 hour or until mixture is completely cool and smooth, stirring occasionally.
Beat the cooled chocolate mixture with an electric mixer on medium speed until slightly fluffy.
This should take about 2 minutes.
Chill about 15 minutes or until mixture holds its shape.
Drop mixture from a level teaspoon onto a baking sheet lined with waxed paper.
Chill about 30 minutes more or until firm.
Melt dipping chocolate.
Dip candy into the melted chocolate.
Let stand until dry.
Store tightly covered in a cool, dry place.
Makes about 48 pieces.

title: peanut butter icing
directions: Blend butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients, except peanut butter.
Add peanut butter to taste.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake in 11 x 14-inch casserole.
Saute onions, celery and green pepper in margarine.
Add both soups and mushrooms to sauteed mixture and mix well.
Then all other ingredients except ripe olives and mix.
Pour into casserole. Garnish with black olives, if desired.
Bake, covered with foil for 15 minutes or until bubbles.
Serves 6.

title: grape and cottage cheese salad
directions: Whip cream stiff.
Fold in salad dressing.
Combine cottage cheese with cream and dressing; add the rest of the ingredients.

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Combine the ingredients.
Wash fresh spinach.
Add mushrooms, bacon and croutons.
Add dressing and serve.

title: special pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, spices and sugar.
Add eggs and milk.
Beat well. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: kentucky apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix rest of the ingredients; sprinkle over the apples.
Bake until apples are tender and topping is golden brown, about 30 minutes, at 375°.

title: meatballs with sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine meat, salt, pepper, Accent, chopped onion and eggs in a bowl and mix well.
Freeze for about 1 hour.
Form the mixture into balls about 3/4-inch in diameter.
Roll them lightly in flour and deep fry.
In a saucepan, saute garlic, quartered onion and bell pepper.
Add sweet and sour mix; stir and simmer for 5 to 8 minutes or until the sauce thickens.
Pour sauce over meatballs and serve.

title: mushroom clam sauce
directions: In butter, saute onions and mushrooms.
Add clams, sherry, basil, parsley, salt, pepper and cheese.
Stir to blend.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cream the butter and flour together.
Slowly add butter-flour mixture to sauce, stirring and incorporating well after each addition.
When sauce is thickened, add sour cream and stir to blend; do not boil. Serve over pasta.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cucumber tea sandwiches
directions: About 1 hour before serving or early in the day, in a small bowl, mix first 4 ingredients. Set aside.
With fork, score unpeeled cucumber lengthwise. Cut cucumber lengthwise in half, then crosswise into very thin slices.
With 1 3/4-inch round biscuit cutter, cut 4 rounds from each bread slice.
(Save trimmings to use for bread crumbs another day.)
Spread 1 side of each bread round with some cream cheese mixture. Top with 2 cucumber slices.
Line a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan with damp paper towels.
Place tea sandwiches in pan.
Cover with damp paper towels to keep bread from drying out.
Cover pan tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 24 tea sandwiches.
Contains about 30 calories each.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Chop strawberries and place in a 3-quart casserole dish with pectin.
Stir well.
Cover.
Place in microwave oven and heat at Full power for 8 to 10 minutes, until mixture reaches a full, rolling boil.
Let boil 1 minute longer.
Remove from oven and skim off foam with metal spoon, stirring jam for 5 minutes. Ladle into hot, sterilized glasses.
Seal.
Makes 8 cups.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Beat eggs and stir in water.
Bring stock to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium.
Stir in sherry, soy sauce and salt.
Pour in eggs slowly (little at a time, stirring all the time).
Make sure soup is still at a slow boil at all times.
Use a whisk so eggs are shredding while stirring.
Serve up with egg rolls.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 stick margarine.
Saute celery, bell pepper and onion. Add peas, pimentos, water chestnuts, soup, salt and pepper.
Place in casserole and cover with cracker crumbs and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: play dough(kids stuff)
directions: Mix salt and cornstarch with enough water to form a paste. Can color with small amount of food coloring.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple and jello.
Cool.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add buttermilk and pecans.
Place in 2 qt. casserole dish.

title: ham and pasta skillet
directions: In medium skillet mix soup, milk, mustard and broccoli.
Over medium heat, heat to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook 5 minutes or until broccoli is tender.
Add ham and macaroni and heat through.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Saute onions, green onions, and garlic in butter, oil, in pot until onions are browned and wilted. Stir in cream of celery and cream of mushroom soups. Increase heat and bring to boil stirring constantly. Reduce heat to medium and stir in crawfish and tony's seasoning. Cook for about 10 minutes. Reduce heat to medium. Sprinkle parsley on top. Serve over hot rice.

title: chicken imperial casserole
directions: Combine celery, chicken, rice, cheese, eggs and almonds. Blend broth, milk, mayo, soups and seasonings; pour over chicken mixture.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Pour into a greased shallow 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
I also add a little more grated cheese and paprika over all.
This dish can be frozen.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Saute garlic in butter. Add shrimp, salt and oregano. Cook on high heat 3 to 5 minutes or until shrimp are pink, stirring constantly. Stir in wine and serve.

title: lemon broiled chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in a casserole dish, skin side down. Pour lemon juice liberally over all chicken pieces.
Combine salt, pepper and paprika.
Brush chicken with half of melted butter; sprinkle with half of seasoning mixture.
Broil about 6-inches from heat, 15 to 20 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Turn chicken; brush with remaining butter and sprinkle with remaining seasoning mixture.
Continue broiling for 10 to 15 minutes or until chicken is tender and deep golden brown.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Melt bouillon cubes in hot water.
Combine all ingredients until creamed.
Chill and serve.

title: meal in a muffin(makes 12 large muffins)
directions: Beat brown sugar, oil or applesauce, egg, milk and bananas until well blended.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt all at once.
Fold in cereal, dates and nuts.
Spoon batter into paper-lined 4-inch muffin tins until 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 375°.
Serve warm or cold.

title: rotini macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni according to box recipe.
Rinse in cold water after they are cooked.
Mix mayonnaise with sugar and vinegar thoroughly, then add other ingredients. Pour over macaroni and mix.

title: corn dogs
directions: You will need 10 wooden skewers.

title: oniony mashed potatoes
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes according to package directions.

title: dill pickles
directions: Place stalk of dill in bottom of jar and add 2 cloves of garlic.
Place cucumbers in jar and top with another stalk of dill.
Add 2 more cloves of garlic.
Put teaspoon of salt in jar. Fill with cold water and cover tightly.
Place jar in cool, dark place for 1 week.
Shake jar once or twice to mix salt. Refrigerate and eat.

title: grandma billing's rivel soup
directions: Cook beef until done.
Pick meat off bone.
Combine egg, salt and flour until crumbly.
Drop by handfuls into boiling beef broth.
Stir while dropping in so that it doesn't get lumpy.
Add small can tomatoes to make a thick soup.

title: marinated pea salad
directions: Combine in small saucepan the vinegar, sugar, water, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, stir and cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Cool completely.
Combine vegetables in a large bowl. Pour marinade over vegetables, stir gently.
Cover salad and refrigerate.
Salad keeps well in refrigerator about a week.

title: fresh corn chowder
directions: In saucepan combine corn, water, onion and salt. Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer covered 15 minutes. Stir in 3 1/2 c. milk, butter and pepper. Blend together remaining 1/2 c. milk and flour. Stir into corn mixture. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Gradually stir 1 c.
of hot mixture with egg and return to soup. Garnish with snipped chives.

title: taco-stuffed potato
directions: Scrub potato and pierce both sides.
Place on paper towel in bottom of microwave oven.
Microwave at High for 4 to 8 minutes or until skin feels soft, turning potato over after 2 minutes. Remove potato from oven.
Let stand while meat sauce cooks.
Place beef and onion in small (2 cup) microwave bowl.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes or until beef loses its pink color and onion is tender, stirring and breaking up beef after 2 minutes.
Drain off fat.
Stir in taco sauce.
Cut cross in top of hot potato.
Fill with cheese and sour cream.
Cover with meat sauce.
Garnish with tomato, lettuce and cheese.

title: daria's dip
directions: Mix ingredients together; serve with crackers.

title: jam cake
directions: Grease 3 regular cake pans.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Stir raisins in this to coat them.
Add the "beaten" eggs.
Add the rest of the ingredients as you wish, then add "melted" lard and nuts.
Stir up real good and pour in pans (do not use mixer).
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes.

title: chicken doris
directions: Brown
chicken in 2 tablespoons of butter, then carrots and pearl
onions
in
tablespoons of butter.
Add chicken broth. Cover
and	bake
at
450°	for 15 minutes.
Add fresh mushrooms. Turn oven to 325° and bake an hour to 1 1/2 hours, covered.

title: sin in a pan
directions: Layer 1:
Mix flour, melted margarine and 1 1/4 cups finely chopped pecans.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oleo until light.
Add vanilla and buttermilk.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 30 minutes more or until firm in the middle.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Place chops in baking dish.
Combine jelly, soy sauce, ketchup and garlic.
Pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove chops.
Combine cornstarch and water.
Stir into pan juices.
Cook over low heat until it thickens.
Serve over pork chops with rice. Serves 6.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Brown chicken pieces in shortening.
Melt margarine.
Saute 1 cup chopped celery and onion until tender.
Mix well with 2 cups of white bread crumbs and cornbread crumbs.
Add seasonings.
Add enough water to make as moist as you desire.
Place dressing in a large baking dish.
Arrange chicken over dressing.
Make a gravy from drippings where chicken was browned.
Blend with remaining 1/2 can chicken soup.
Add water to make 2 cups.
Pour gravy over chicken and dressing.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheesy salmon patties
directions: Remove skin and bones from salmon. Flake salmon with a fork. Add egg, buttermilk, flour and Cheddar cheese, stirring well. Shape salmon mixture into 6 patties.
(Mixture will be moist.) Pour oil to a depth of 1/8-inch into large heavy skillet. Cook patties in hot oil over medium heat 8 minutes or until golden brown, turning once.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Toss the potatoes with salt, eggs and flour.
Heat the shortening in a heavy skillet and drop in spoonfuls of the potato mixture.
Fry until golden brown.
Turn and fry other side.
Serve hot with applesauce.
Serves 2.

title: easy cobbler crust
directions: *If self-rising flour is used, leave out salt and baking powder.

title: great cornbread
directions: Butter bottom and sides of an 8 to 9-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, stir together cornmeal, flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
In another bowl, beat together eggs, oil, melted and cooled butter, evaporated milk and skim milk until thoroughly blended.
Pour mixture into cornmeal mixture and stir until mixture is smooth.
Do not overbeat.
Spoon into prepared pan.
Bake in preheated oven 25 to 30 minutes or until top is golden and a pick inserted in the middle comes out clean.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes.

title: raspberry cake(bringebaer kake)
directions: Grease a round 9 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Blend dry ingredients and mix in butter and egg until flour is moistened.
Press dough evenly on bottom of pan.
Spread 1/4 cup jam over the dough.
Chill, covered, while making filling.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour it all in one bowl.
Mix it well.
Bake in greased and floured oblong pan (approximately 9 x 13-inches) in 325° oven for 50 minutes.
Test center with toothpick.

title: english toffee squares
directions: In large bowl, beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Add egg yolk; beat.
Reserve egg white.
Add flour, cinnamon and nutmeg to creamed mixture; blend thoroughly.
With your hands, spread batter on a greased 15 x 10-inch baking pan.
Beat egg white lightly. Brushing lightly, cover dough with egg white.
Sprinkle nuts on top, pressing into dough.
Bake at 275° for 45 to 50 minutes or until firm when touched.
Remove from oven immediately.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Blend together for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 50 or 55 minutes.
Makes 1 deep pie pan (9-inch pan).

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa and corn meal.
Add eggs, margarine, milk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: 7-layer squares
directions: Put in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish by layers in order listed. Do not mix.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: superb roast beef
directions: Use eye of round roast or almost any delicately marbled boneless roast will do.
Rub oil over entire surface of meat. Combine remaining ingredients; rub over roast.
Place in shallow dish or pan.
Bake 1 hour per pound, uncovered, at 250°.

title: fish sauces and marinade
directions: Combine and pour over fish.
Marinate 2 hours.
Grill, broil or bake fish.

title: cinnamon diamonds
directions: Mix well and pat into ungreased jellyroll pan the first 6 ingredients.
Brush dough with beaten egg white.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup of chopped walnuts and firmly pat down.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cut into diamonds while still warm.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cover the chuck meat with 2 quarts cold water and boil 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Use vegetables that take longer to cook (carrots, cabbage, onion, pepper and tomatoes).
When tender, add lima beans and yellow string beans.
Before cooking vegetables, add 1/4 pound butter or oleo and 1 1/2 teaspoons sugar.

title: chocolate almond cookies
directions: Cream almond paste and butter.
Add sugar and egg.
Gradually add flour and salt.
Shape dough into 2-inch fingers.
Place 1-inch apart on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly, mash beans with juice.
Add eggs and beans to other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie shells and bake 45 minutes at 300°.

title: cheese log
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into a log.
Roll in finely chopped pecans or chili powder.
Serve with crackers.

title: cream puffs(or chocolate eclairs)
directions: Melt butter in boiling water.
Add flour and salt. Cook, stirring constantly until mixture forms a ball that does not separate, approximately 7 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool for 10 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time beating after each addition until mixture is smooth and eggs are completely incorporated.
Drop from spoon 2 inches apart onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and continue baking for another 25 minutes.
Cool completely before filling.

title: jan's cherry supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients and let stand, covered, overnight in the refrigerator.
Delicious!
Easy to make!

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in large pot with 3 cups water, covered. Cook until tender. Drain. Add milk, soups and thinly sliced cream cheese. Let cook until melted. Add butter, salt and pepper until heated well. Place in individual bowls. Top with bacon bits, Cheddar cheese and green onions.

title: seafood pizza with puff pastry crust
directions: *Adjust to your taste.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix together melted butter, cake mix and 2 eggs.
Press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch greased pan.	Mix powdered sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese.
Spread on top of first layer.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: angel hair and broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli 3 to 4 minutes until crispy and tender.
Place in cold water; drain water.
In small saucepan heat oil and 2 tablespoons butter over medium heat and set aside.
In large skillet saute scallions and garlic in 2 tablespoons butter for 2 minutes.
Add wine and simmer 5 minutes.
Add melted oil and butter with blanched broccoli mix and heat thoroughly.
Serve over angel hair pasta cooked al dente.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top to taste.

title: creamy cheese nut spread
directions: In small bowl, combine cream cheese, syrup and cinnamon.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Spread on croissants, roll, bagel or toast.
Store in refrigerator.

title: orange glazed yamsspringfield, missouri
directions: Boil peeled sweet potatoes until nearly done.
Arrange in baking dish.
Cook the sugar, orange juice and cornstarch for 5 minutes.
Add the butter and pour over the potatoes.
Cover and bake in a moderate oven for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and put into pan.
Sprinkle chips and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fig cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, oil, sour cream and vanilla; stir well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture, then add 1 quart figs (mashed) and pecans.
Stir well.
Bake at 350° until done.
Use pan of your choice.
I use angel food cake pan sprayed with Pam.

title: yummy chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Preheat oven to 350°. Mix flour and sugar. Heat Crisco, margarine and water until melted. Add cocoa. Pour over flour and sugar and add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Bake for 30 minutes. Cover with Uncle Dan's Icing.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water until tender, but not mushy. Drain.
Cut onion into rings.
Cut pepper into rings, discarding seeds.
Combine onion and peppers with cooked carrots in heat-proof bowl.

title: skillet macaroni and beef
directions: Cook beef in large skillet until it loses its redness.
Remove from skillet and add macaroni, onions and pepper to meat grease. Cook a few minutes, add meat again, then add tomato sauce, salt, pepper, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring or until macaroni is cooked tender.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Dust each of the 16 wedges of apples in cinnamon.
Wrap each apple slice in a crescent roll triangle.
Arrange in a shallow baking dish, pointed side up.
In a saucepan, bring sugar, orange juice and margarine to a boil.
Pour over crescent wrapped apples. Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown.
The finished recipe looks great.

title: brenda's banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding up by the package directions but use 1 large can of milk and measure this out.
Add whole milk to make 3 cups.
Cook until thick.
Place a layer of cookies in a bowl.
Add part of pudding.
Place a layer of bananas.
Repeat until you have no ingredients left.
You can top with Cool Whip if you like.
Chill and serve.

title: old fashioned baked beans
directions: Stir together first 3 ingredients in bean pot or 1-quart casserole dish.
Top with bacon and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients in pan and let boil 1 minute after it starts to boil.
Line a cookie sheet with graham crackers and spoon mixture on top.
Bake 10 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: cottage cheese broccoli cornbread
directions: Beat eggs with a fork; add each ingredient and beat with a fork.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: okra gumbo
directions: Simmer beef, onion, tomatoes, water, broth and bouillon cubes for 1 hour, then add lima beans and cook for 20 minutes.
Then add okra, ham and chicken and cook for 20 minutes more.
Just before serving, add corn and cook for 5minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: crab dip
directions: Cream together mayonnaise, cheese and wine.
Add spices and crabmeat.
Cook in a chafing dish and serve hot.

title: "sneaky pete" punch
directions: Mix together and keep in freezer.
To serve, place in blender and blend; will be like a slush.

title: chocolate oil cake
directions: Mix all cake ingredients and spread in ungreased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost the cake while hot with frosting.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Add zucchini and peppers.
Cook 3 minutes over medium heat.
Stir in other ingredients.
Cover.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator up to 5 days.

title: pork chops and brown rice
directions: Brown pork chops lightly.
Wash rice. Drain and put in 2-quart casserole.
Prepare 1 package Lipton soup mix according to instructions.
Add bouillon cube to soup mix and pour mixture over rice.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
(Helps to stir once during baking.)

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese, almonds and potato chips; place in a large rectangular baking dish.
Top with cheese, potato chips and almonds.
Let stand overnight in the refrigerator; bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: venison pot roast
directions: About 4 hours before serving, trim excess fat from meat.
Coat meat with flour.
In 8-quart Dutch oven over medium heat with hot shortening, brown meat on all sides.
Add 1 cup water, onion, 1 teaspoon salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Simmer 3 hours, until fork-tender.
Add additional water if needed.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Melt the 3 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Add the sugar and rhubarb. Spread in an 8 x 10-inch pan. Combine the remaining ingredients.
Dot rhubarb with teaspoons of topping. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: irish potato candy
directions: Boil potato until tender.
Mash with fork until smooth.
Add sugar and work into a dry dough.
Roll out between wax paper that has been sprinkled with sugar.
Spread peanut butter, then roll up like a jelly roll.

title: bisquick brownies
directions: Combine chocolate bits and butter.
Oven low heat until melted.
Away from stove stir in milk, egg, and Bisquick Mix. Spread into a greased pan.
Bake 350°
25 - 30 minutes.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Heat 7-Up and cream cheese until dissolved.
Then dissolve Jell-O in this mixture; use blender or mixer.
Let cool until partially congealed in refrigerator or freezer.
Mix in nuts and pineapple with juice.
Mold until congealed, turn out and slice to serve.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice in 3 cups water.
Bring to a boil and turn to lower setting.
Cover and cook about 14 minutes.
Saute celery and onion in 3 tablespoons of oleo.
Microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes. Cook broccoli according to package.
Mix 1 can mushroom soup, Cheez Whiz, rice and broccoli.
Bake about 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cream cheese pastry turnovers
directions: Beat the butter, margarine or shortening and cream cheese together.
Add the flour and salt; blend with a pastry blender or with your fingertips.
Cover the pastry with waxed paper and place in the refrigerator to chill 1 hour or more.

title: chocolate peanut butter truffles
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chips with butter.
Stir in cocoa
until smooth.
Add sweetened condensed milk and vanilla. Cook and stir until thickened and well blended, about 4 minutes.

title: harvest casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and onion together.
Cook celery in a small amount of margarine over low heat.
Cook noodles as directed on package; drain grease from meat.
Add all ingredients together and put in 1 large casserole dish or several small ones.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
This casserole makes 1 gallon.
It freezes well.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream together first three ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into greased and floured stem pan or loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Test with straw.
This is very moist and keeps well.
Freezes well, too.
Baking time:
1 hour.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Place in well-greased crock-pot. Stir in remaining ingredients except eggs, milk and cheese.
Beat eggs and cheese together.
Pour over other ingredients; stir well. Dust with additional nutmeg.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: 5 cup fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight before serving.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine and mix well all ingredients and pour into buttered baking dish.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Cook beef in oven until done.
Let get cold; slice thin.
Mix wine, catsup and soup mix together.
Pour over beef; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Serve on buns or plain.

title: baked corn
directions: Melt butter or margarine, add flour and mix well.
Add milk gradually and bring to boiling, stirring constantly.
Add corn, sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir and heat thoroughly.
Remove from heat.
Add well beaten eggs and pour into greased baking dish (2-quart casserole).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until firm.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, chocolate chips and peanut butter in microwave. Pour over cereal and stir until coated.
Put sugar into a grocery bag and pour cereal mixture in.
Shake until coated.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: *Substitute cream of chicken soup.

title: asparagus leek soup
directions: In a saucepan, saute leeks and onions in margarine until tender.
Add potatoes, carrots, salt, chicken broth and rice. Cover and bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add spinach, pepper and cream; heat through.
Yield: 12 to 16 servings (4 1/2 quarts).
Best made the day before.

title: no-bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and mix well.
Pack firmly into ungreased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips.
Spread over mixture in pan. Chill. Cut into squares.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage.
Drain and crumble.
You can do this the night before or days ahead of time and freeze.
Place flattened crescent rolls in 13-inch Pyrex dish buttered side down.
Spread sausage over crescent rolls.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Put half of cheese in egg and milk mixture and pour over rolls and sausage. Sprinkle rest of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. Check when the rolls start peeking through the egg, sausage and cheese mixture and browning.
You're done.
Serves 8.

title: hamburger baked beans
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Mix desired ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pretzel strawberry salad
directions: Melt margarine, pretzels and 3 tablespoons of sugar.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Let cool.

title: christmas salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add cold water.
Add remaining ingredients, except sour cream.
Pour half of jello in oblong Pyrex dish.
Chill until firm.
Spread sour cream over mixture; add remaining jello.
Chill 4 to 6 hours or overnight.
Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: chocolate pie 2
directions: In a heavy skillet combine sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add egg yolks and 1 cup milk, stirring until blended.
Add remaining milk and salt.
Cook over low to medium heat until mixture is thick. Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into ready baked pie crust.

title: hot giant pecans
directions: In large skillet, melt butter; add pecans and celery salt. Stir well to coat.
Pour pecans into a shallow baking pan. Spread evenly.
Bake in preheated oven at 250° for 15 minutes. Stir once.
Turn pecans out onto paper towels.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Mix with spoon.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook rice until tender.
Brown sausage, pepper and onions. Add other ingredients.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: individual steak dinner
directions: Wrap all ingredients in aluminum foil. Place on cookie sheet. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: baked chicken in sherry
directions: Put chicken and butter in a 9x13-inch dish.

title: my favorite cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix together sugar, crumbs and butter. Line a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Refrigerate.
Cream sugar and cream cheese in mixer for 5 to 10 minutes.
When well creamed, add eggs and vanilla.
Beat entire mixture for 30 minutes on slow speed.
Bake 60 minutes.
Remove and cool 20 minutes.
Mix sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Spread on top of cake and return to oven for 10 minutes.
Turn oven off.
Open door a crack.
Leave in at least one hour until it is cool.

title: flounder roll-ups
directions: Cut broccoli into 4-inch stalks.
Steam 10 minutes or until tender.
Roll each fillet with a slice of Swiss cheese around a few stalks cooked broccoli.
Secure with toothpicks.
Allow heads of broccoli to extend past one side of flounder roll.
Place roll-ups in covered baking dish in oven for 20 minutes or until flounder is slightly steaming.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Pour over flounder and top with sliced mushrooms (optional).
Bake an additional 15 minutes.
Total time 35 minutes in a 350° oven. Serve with lemon wedges.
Garnish with parsley and sprinkle with paprika.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Cut a potato into 8 wedges.
Brush the wedges lightly with olive oil.
Place the wedges in a microwave-safe pie plate.
Cook on High for 10 to 12 minutes or until tender, turning once. Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese and paprika or chili powder.

title: strawberry orange jam
directions: Cut orange in half.
Remove seeds and core.
Do not peel. Grind oranges in blender along with strawberries.
Combine orange strawberry mixture, water and margarine in large kettle with heavy bottom.
Add Sure-Jell.
Stir well.
Place over high heat and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
When reaches a full rolling boil, add sugar, continuing to stir constantly.
Boil hard for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Skim and stir constantly for 5 minutes.
Pour into hot sterilized jars within 1/8-inch from top.
Seal with ball dome lids.
Place on rack in kettle, covered with boiling water.
Place lid on kettle and boil for 15 minutes. Take out, cool and store in cool place.

title: lemon pudding squares
directions: Mix together the flour and margarine and press in an ungreased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix together cream cheese and confectionary sugar and fold in 1 cup of the Kool Whip.
Spread over the cooled crust.
Mix the lemon pudding with the milk and beat until firm. spread over cream cheese mixture.
Spread remainder of Kool Whip on top. Refrigerate.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add zucchini last.
Pour into greased bread pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: smashing squash
directions: Butter a large casserole dish.
Cook squash until tender; drain.
Melt butter.
Add half the bag of stuffing.
Add soup, sour cream, vegetables and squash; put into the casserole.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: bacon cheddar muffins
directions: Line 12 muffin cups with papers.
Mix all ingredients except cheese and bacon just until moistened.
Batter will be lumpy. Fold in cheese and bacon.
Divide batter among muffin cups.
Bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes, at 400°.

title: 3 baked bean casserole
directions: Mix pork and beans with juice, kidney beans, butter beans, ground beef, bacon and onion.
In a small bowl, mix ketchup, sugar, brown sugar, molasses and mustard; add to bean mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Stir occasionally.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: a meal
directions: What To Do: Wash 4 pieces of chicken at a time.
Pat dry with paper towels.
Put chicken in pan, skin side up.
Pour 1 teaspoon oil on each piece of chicken and spread over them.
Salt and pepper each piece lightly, then shake paprika on each.

title: chicchi picchi
directions: Cut chicken into pieces.
Soak the pieces in the beaten eggs for at least 30 minutes.
Then coat the pieces with bread crumbs and saute in cooking oil until golden brown.
Then place in a greased baking dish and sprinkle mushrooms over the chicken.
Lay pieces of Muenster cheese over this.
Pour the chicken broth over all of this.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cherry salad supreme
directions: Dissolve
raspberry
jello in 1 cup boiling water; stir in pie filling.
Turn
into 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Chill until partially set.
Dissolve
lemon gelatin in 1 cup boiling water. Beat
together cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Gradually add lemon gelatin.
Stir in undrained pineapple.
Whip 1/2 cup Cool Whip. Fold
into lemon mixture with 1 cup tiny marshmallows.
Spread atop
cherry
layer;
top
with
chopped
nuts. Chill until set. Makes 12 servings.

title: chicken francesa
directions: Cut chicken into thin cutlets.
Soak in milk for 10 minutes. Mix bread crumbs, parsley and Parmesan cheese.
Cover each slice of cutlet with bread crumbs.
Add olive oil to large frying pan and brown cutlets (quickly).
(Do not overcook.)
Place cutlets in a lightly buttered dish, salt and pepper to taste.
Place one slice of lemon on each cutlet.
Remove all but 1 tablespoon of oil from frying pan, leave residue from chicken.
Add wine and lemon juice and chicken broth to skillet.
Boil slowly until liquid is reduced by 1/2 and pour over the chicken slices.
Drizzle Grand Marnier over each slice.
Bake at 350° until liquid begins to boil (20 to 25 minutes).

title: chicken and rice deal
directions: Place chicken, skin side up, in a large baking dish.
Pour rice over chicken.
In a saucepan, combine all three soups and margarine.
Use water to rinse out all three cans, then add to soup.
Heat to melt margarine, then pour over chicken.
Be sure rice is covered completely by soup mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for two hours.
Yields about eight servings.

title: chocolate bundt cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate chips, together well. Fold in chocolate chips.
Turn out into a greased and floured tube pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: pork chili verde
directions: Cook pork in 1/2 cup water until dry.
Discard garlic.
Brown meat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook, covered, 30 minutes.

title: old kentucky lemonade
directions: Wash mint and remove leaves.
Mix lemon juice, sugar and water; pour over mint leaves.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Just before serving, stir in ginger ale.
Serve over crushed ice.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Punch angel food cake up into small pieces and put in a cake pan.
Crush 3 Butterfinger candy bars and sprinkle over cake.
Mix egg yolks, Cool Whip, butter and powdered sugar.
Mix all together with mixer until well blended.
Pour over cake.
Crush 3 Butterfinger candy bars and sprinkle over cake.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: quick chick!
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry. Remove wing tips, if desired.
Do not stuff chicken. Put on microwave-safe plastic or glass pan.
A bacon pan with ridges drains the fat.
Microwave on High for about 7 to 8 minutes per pound depending on oven strength.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients together.
To serve, put 1/3 cup of mix into cup.
Add boiling water and stir.

title: broccoli cabbage salad
directions: In a large bowl mix broccoli slaw, green pepper, green onion, almonds and sunflower seeds.
Break or crush noodles and put on top of vegetables.
In a bowl mix oil, vinegar, flavoring pack from noodles and sugar; pour over vegetables.
Do not mix until 2 hours before serving.

title: clam chowder
directions: Drain juice from clams, pour over vegetables in saucepan and add enough water to barely cover.
Simmer over medium heat until potatoes are tender (about 20 minutes).

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix together in any order with mixer.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: hamburger dish
directions: Brown meat and put in casserole dish.
Put mushroom soup and layer with cheese, then layer with potato tarts.
Bake for 1 hour at 400°.

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: Saute bacon, onion and mushrooms until bacon is cooked.
Add wine and simmer 10 minutes.
Cook pasta and drain; toss with butter.
Stir in cream and add cheese and parsley.
Put bacon mixture on top of pasta.
Serve with extra cheese.

title: orange cream cheese frosting
directions: In a large bowl, beat together cream cheese, margarine or butter and apricot brandy or orange juice.
Gradually beat in enough powdered sugar to make frosting spreadable.
Stir in orange peel.
Makes about 2 3/4 cups.

title: potatoes brian(good!)
directions: Bake potatoes; cube or crumble.
Put half potatoes in baking dish.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and half cheese.
Then put remaining potatoes, cheese, salt and pepper in dish.
Put melted butter over top and soak with cream 1/2 hour before baking.
Bake until cheese melts and forms a golden crust.

title: fried rice from mindanao
directions: Cook sweet peas and corn together.
Scramble eggs. Place skillet on medium heat.
Coat with cooking oil.
After oil is hot, add garlic, onions and rice and mix.
After mixture is fried blend in soy sauce.
Add salt.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Add drained peas and corn, mixing thoroughly and let cook for a few minutes.
Place on serving dish and sprinkle with scrambled eggs on top and serve.

title: pickled squash
directions: Combine squash and onions, season with salt and set aside one hour.
Drain liquid from squash and add vinegar, sugar, celery seed, mustard seed and bell pepper and bring to boil, adding the squash.
Boil for approximately 2 to 3 minutes, place into hot jars and seal.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle with pecans and coconut in the bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix as directed and pour on top of pecans and coconut.
Mix margarine, cream cheese and sugar.
Dot on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream together first 7 ingredients. Mix in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls, 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 11 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: chicken liver and noodles
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water.
Cook livers in boiling water; drain each in separate pans.
There should be some moisture, then the soup will mix with noodles.
Put drained livers in noodles and soup and stir.
This should serve about 5 as a complete main dish. Tossed salad, bread and drink are an added treat.

title: pot au feu
directions: Combine first nine ingredients in large pot.
Cover with 1 1/2 quarts water.
Slowly bring to boil and skim off foam.
Simmer gently, covered, for 1 hour (add water to maintain level).
Add beans and chicken. Simmer 25 minutes; season with pepper and parsley.
Serve with crusty rolls.
Serves 6.

title: seven layer salad supreme
directions: Layer the first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Spread the Miracle Whip over all as a frosting.
Sprinkle the sugar and Parmesan cheese on top.
Let set 24 hours in the refrigerator. An hour before serving add the eggs, tomatoes and bacon.
Toss and serve.

title: puff pancake with summer berries
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 10 inch ovenproof skillet. With electric mixer beat eggs.
Add flour, milk, sugar, and salt; heat until smooth.
Pour batter into prepared skillet.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Continue baking 10 - 15 minutes or until puffed and golden brown.

title: pink cloud
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: cashew chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breast with seasonings until done.
Cube chicken and put in a large casserole dish with soup, cooked noodles, cashews and butter.
Sprinkle Chinese noodles on top and bake at 350° until noodles are crispy.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown meat with onions; drain and add soups and spices to meat.
Simmer for 15 minutes over low heat.
Cook noodles and drain.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer noodles on the bottom, then meat sauce, Cheddar cheese and sprinkle Parmesan cheese over that. Top with sliced mushrooms.
Cover with foil and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Take foil off and bake an additional 10 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: hot buttered rum batter
directions: In large bowl, whip softened butter.
Add softened ice cream, sugar and spices.
Freeze in large container.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix well; put in buttered casserole dish.
Cover with crushed Ritz crackers and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Clean and chop broccoli; cook and set aside.
Saute onion in butter.
Add broccoli and rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into prebuttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered with aluminum foil.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake 1 hour or until done at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix in the dry ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes; check.
This is a very easy recipe.
This is also an Amish recipe.

title: garden salad
directions: Mix all vegetables together.
Mix sugar (or diet sweetener), oil and white vinegar together well.
Pour over mixed vegetables.

title: pasta with fresh sauce
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add onions and pepper. Then add garlic. Saute until onions are tender and clear.
Add tomatoes last and cook until heated through.
Serve over pasta.
Can add more ingredients to your taste or quantity.
This is a low-fat dish.

title: citrus punch
directions: Mix part of ice cream or sherbet with juices.
Then add rest. Very tasty!

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add flour and sugars.
Beat until well blended.
Blend in butter.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for one hour.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Process until smooth. Serve in small bowls or cups.
Makes four 1/2 cup servings.

title: blueberry buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour baking sheet, shaking off excess flour.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda and sugar in large bowl.
Using a pastry blender or fork add 1 stick butter (do not substitute margarine) until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Form a well in the mixture and add buttermilk.
Mix well with fork.
Fold blueberries in gently with wooden spoon. Turn onto floured surface and lightly knead 10 to 12 turns.
Cut with biscuit cutter or mold by hand into 10 to 12 biscuits.
Place on baking sheet and place in center of oven on 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together in thick boiler.
Let come to a boil and boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat. Add vanilla and beat until smooth.
Spread on cake.
Makes enough for a large cake.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Marinate meat 4 to 5 hours before cooking.
Use for beef or chicken breast.

title: german chocolate squares(makes 13 x 9-inch cheesecake)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs, pecans, sugar and margarine; press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: chili
directions: Cook beef, onion and garlic in 3-quart saucepan over medium heat 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally until beef is brown and drain. Stir in remaining ingredients except beans. Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Stir in beans. Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until desired thickness.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Heat soup in medium saucepan.
When warm, add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese; when melted, remove from heat. Add remaining ingredients.
Chill at least 4 hours.

title: glazed strawberry pie
directions: Arrange strawberries on top of baked pie crust.
In saucepan, mix water, cornstarch and sugar.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O and red food coloring. Cool 5 minutes; pour over berries in shell.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix chilies, cream cheese and green onions.
Add Tabasco sauce and garlic powder to taste.
Spoon onto tortilla and roll up. Refrigerate for two hours, then cut into 1/2-inch rings and serve with hot sauce.
Covers 5 (8-inch) tortillas.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa.
Bring to a good hard boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Take off heat and add oatmeal, peanut butter, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper on cookie sheet.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: audrey's corn casserole
directions: Add butter, sour cream, creamed corn and whole kernel corn. Combine eggs and muffin mix and add to the above ingredients. Pour into a greased 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: jiffy salad
directions: Mix jello, oranges and crushed pineapple together.
Add marshmallows and then Cool Whip.
Put in refrigerator until it is set.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Lightly grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle cheese and onion in pie plate.
Beat milk, Bisquick, eggs, salt and pepper in a medium bowl with electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in any meat. Pour into pie plate.
Bake until brown and knife inserted comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: presbyterian punch
directions: Mix juice and ale. Add frozen raspberries to serving bowl. Serves 15.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugars, zucchini and vanilla together, then add dry ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 2 medium loaves.

title: chiffon cake
directions: Mix and sift first four ingredients.
Make a well and add in order; Mazola oil, egg yolks, water, lemon rind and vanilla.
Beat with spoon until smooth.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites.
Beat until egg whites form very stiff peaks.
Gently fold first mixture into egg whites until well blended.
Fold, do not stir!
Turn batter into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in moderate oven (325°) 70 to 75 minutes or until cake springs back when touched lightly with finger.
Immediately invert pan over funnel to cool. Remove from pan, loosening sides with spatula.
Frost with berry icing or whatever you prefer.
For 9-inch tube pan use 1/2 of mixture.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix everything except cornflakes and margarine together.
Place in a casserole dish.
Cover with the crushed cornflakes and melted margarine.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bean casserole
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Serve piping hot!

title: hot mushroom dip
directions: Fry bacon, drain and crumble.
Saute mushrooms, onions and garlic over medium heat for 6 to 8 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add cream cheese, worcestershire sauce, and soy sauce.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until melted. Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream and crumbled bacon.
Pour into a serving bowl and serve with crackers or bread.

title: spicy cranberry pork chops
directions: Sprinkle pork chops lightly with salt and pepper.
Place in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish; cover with plastic wrap (do not vent). Cook at Medium-low (30% power) for 16 minutes, turning chops over and rotating dish half turn after 10 minutes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar together.
Cook all at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.
Take from oven and pour syrup over.

title: thelma's lemon pie
directions: Note:
I don't bother making the lemon filling.
I take a package of Jell-O lemon pie filling.
Fix according to box.
Let cool.
Fold in whipped topping and use that.
I like it better and it saves time.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet.
Drain tomatoes and reserve liquid.
Chop up tomatoes.
After meat and onion are browned, add taco seasoning, tomatoes and rice.
Add water to tomato juice to make 2 1/2 cups liquid.
Add liquid to skillet and mix together. Bring to a boil, then simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
To serve, place casserole on plate, then top with shredded lettuce, then grated cheese.

title: low-fat french fries
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray cookie sheet with nonstick spray. Mix together in bowl, potatoes, egg whites and Cajun spice.
Be sure potatoes are coated well.
Pour all out on baking sheet and spread out evenly.
Bake until brown on one side and turn over. Bake until done.
Contains approximately 1 gram of fat per serving.

title: back-to-school pencil cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix margarine and cream cheese in a large bowl.
Stir in sugar and vanilla.
Stir in flour.
Shape rounded teaspoonfuls of dough into 3-inch logs, tapering one end slightly to resemble pencil points.
Place two inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake approximately 10 minutes or until set but not brown.
Cool.

title: lentil soup
directions: Wash lentils and put in large kettle with water and spices. Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Saute sliced onions and carrots in 1/2 cup olive oil.
Add parsley, tomatoes and sauteed onions and carrots to soup.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours (several is okay).
Can be served with grated cheese.
Delicious meal with garlic bread and tossed green salad.

title: jiffy peanut butter cookies
directions: In large mixer bowl cut peanut butter and shortening into dry cake mix using low speed of electric mixer.
Add eggs and water, mix well to form dough.
Using 1 tablespoon for each cookie, shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten each with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool thoroughly. Makes approximately 4 1/2 dozen.

title: skillet fruit betty
directions: Brown bread cubes in butter.
Add honey and fruit.
Cover; cook until fruit is tender, about 8 minutes.
Serve hot or cold with cream.
Serves 4.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add alternating with milk.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour in floured and greased 8 inch pan.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine shrimp, cream cheese, cottage cheese and Good Seasons|; mix in blender.
Blend until mixed well.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: lady baltimore cake
directions: Sift flour once; measure.
Add baking powder and salt and sift together 3 times.
Cream the butter well.
Add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add flour alternately with liquids, a small amount at a time.
Beat after each addition until smooth.
Add flavoring; fold in egg whites.
Bake in 2 greased 9-inch layer pans at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: meatless zucchini lasagna
directions: Mix together cottage cheese, egg, garlic powder and oregano. Slice zucchini in 1/4-inch slices and fry on both sides until brown.
Spread 1/3 of sauce in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer with 1/2 of zucchini, 1/2 of cottage cheese mix and 1/3 of Cheddar cheese.
Continue with 1/3 of sauce, 1/2 of zucchini, 1/2 of cottage cheese and 1/3 of Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until bubbly and brown on top.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken, bone and reserve broth.
Cook spaghetti in reserved chicken broth.
Saute onion and pepper in oil.
Add tomatoes and simmer.
Mix in separate bowl the soup and milk. Combine chicken pieces and spaghetti with all other ingredients, adding more chicken broth, if needed.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Makes a large amount.

title: kidney bean and sausage chowder
directions: Cook sausage until brown, breaking up.
Pour off fat.
Combine all ingredients, except potatoes and green pepper.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add potatoes and green pepper.
Cook 20 minutes more. Remove bay leaf before serving.
Tastes best done a day or two ahead.

title: bing cherry mold
directions: Drain juice from fruit.
Use juice and add water to make 2 cups.
Bring to boil; add jello.
Add fruit and Coke.
Pour in bowl; chill.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook broccoli in microwave for 5 minutes.
Melt butter then add to other ingredients, then put into 13 x 9 (lightly sprayed) baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix pork, beef, onion, potatoes and zwieback.
Mix all the ingredients well and refrigerate until ready to cook.
Shape into small balls and brown in hot fat.
Simmer for 1 hour.
May be refrigerated and reheated in the oven the next day.

title: apple spiced chicken
directions: Just before serving, sprinkle lots of cut-up parsley.
This gravy or sauce poured generously over plain boiled rice with butter-fried chicken and fresh vegetables is my favorite of all meals.
And if there is any milk or gravy leftover it's great when warmed the next day and poured over buttered bread in a soup plate.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix crackers and other dry ingredients together in clean brown grocery bag.
Pour oil over cracker mixture and quickly shake until evenly coated.
Bag absorbs excess oil.
Store in airtight containers.

title: harvest apple soup
directions: Cut apple into quarters.
Place in blender with milk and cinnamon.
Blend at medium-high speed until smooth.
Add apple butter and sour cream.
Blend well.
Add apple cider and blend until smooth and creamy.
Pour into bowl and cover.
Chill thoroughly before serving.
Garnish with apples when served. Serves 4.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine all ingredients and sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger and macaroni casserole
directions: Cook hamburger, pepper, celery and onion.
Add soup, sauce and cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted and blended.
Then add cooked macaroni and stir until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt oleo in a 13 1/2 x 9 1/2-inch pan.
Over this put graham cracker crumbs, then coconut, chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Pour over this the can of condensed milk.
Sprinkle top of this with nuts.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni according to package directions.
Mix in rest of ingredients except cheese, crumbs and paprika.
Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: english toffee
directions: Melt and heat butter and brown sugar to 300° (hard crack). Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Put Hershey bars on top.
Spread. Sprinkle with nuts.
Let cool; cut into squares.

title: beet pickles
directions: Wash and cook beets until tender.
Slip off skins.
Slice or leave whole as you desire.
Mix water, sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Add beets and when heated through, put in jars.
Cover with the water, sugar and vinegar mixture.
Seal jars.
May add spices if you desire.
I don't.

title: pork hocks or knuckles
directions: Place in heavy pot.
Cover about 1/2 to 3/4 height of meat with cold water.
Season quite a bit.
Place on medium to low flame. Simmer about 2 hours.
