Test with fork for tenderness.
After about 1 1/2 hours, pull heavy skin off and return to water.
Water should cook down to a jelly like substance.
Take pork out and cut in big chunks, discarding bone.
Trim off most of fat.
Place in casserole and cover with gravy.
Heat in covered casserole in very low oven. Serves 2 to 3. Enjoy.

title: homer's baked beans
directions: Brown meat, onion and bell pepper; drain fat.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chex party mix
directions: Melt butter in a 15 x 10 x 2-inch pan in a 250° oven.
Remove and stir in seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add Chex cereals and nuts.
Mix until all pieces are coated.
Bake for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on paper towel to cool. May be stored or frozen in airtight container.
Recipe can be doubled. Makes about 9 cups.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine whole kernel corn, cream-style corn and eggs.
Add mixture of sugar, flour, seasoned salt, dry mustard and minced onion.
Stir in milk and margarine.
Pour mixture into greased 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake in 400° oven for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Combine bread crumbs, onion, sage and eggs.
Add chicken broth.
Cut chicken in small pieces and spread on top of casserole.
Pour chicken soup on top and bake until golden brown.

title: tater toast
directions: Beat together milk, eggs and salt.
Dip bread in mixture. Dredge in potato flakes.
Fry in hot, well buttered pan; turn once.
Good with salad!

title: corn bread skillet casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Crumble ground beef into a large skillet and brown evenly.
Drain it and stir in eggs, cornmeal, corn, milk and vegetable oil.
Pour half the batter into a greased 10 1/2-inch cast-iron skillet or 10-inch deep dish (pie) plate. Top evenly with browned ground beef followed by the cheese, onions and pepper.
Pour remaining batter over the top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before cutting into wedges to serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: marshmallow frosting
directions: Put Marshmallow Creme in bowl.
Add Cool Whip; beat together. Top with coconut or pineapple.

title: pineapple souffle
directions: Warm butter and blend with sugar.
Whisk in eggs.
Whisk in nutmeg, lemon, pineapple and bread.
Bake in muffin tins at 325° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Garnish with maraschino cherry.
Serves 12.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place cut up chicken in casserole dish.
Mix chicken broth with celery soup and pour over chicken.
You may put in 2 boiled, chopped eggs and a small can of mushrooms.
In a small bowl, mix flour, milk and margarine together.
Pour this over the chicken. Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: oysters rockefeller
directions: Arrange oysters in single layer in a shallow baking dish.
Mix rest of ingredients, except cheese, with cooked spinach.
Spread on top of oysters.
Sprinkle 2 to 2 1/2 tablespoons of cheese on top.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until oyster edges curl.

title: filled pineapple pots
directions: Preheat oven according to box directions.
Line 2 (12-cup) muffin pans with paper bake cups. Make cake batter according to box directions, but use juice and water in place of liquids on box.
Drop half a cherry and 1 chunk of pineapple into each cup. Fill each cup 3/4 full with batter.
Bake according to box directions for cupcakes.
When cooled, dust with confectioners sugar or frost with frosting.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion in skillet.
Use medium heat.
Drain meat; add salt and pepper.
Spread in plate.
Beat milk, eggs and baking mix until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes and serve.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together first 7 ingredients.
Then mix in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by teaspoon 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: robbie's chicken chasseur
directions: Roll
breast in flour; brown quickly in small amount of hot oil
in
nonstick
pan.
Add the remaining ingredients and simmer until tender, 45 to 60 minutes.
Low in fat, cholesterol and calories and moderate in sodium.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix well.
Pour in greased casserole dish.
Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for one hour.
Serves 4.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer first four ingredients in large bowl.
Sprinkle sugar over layers.
Then add Parmesan cheese.
Seal top with mayonnaise. Cover and let set overnight.
Drain off excess water before tossing.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: bean chalupas
directions: Layer all the ingredients listed.
Pour bean mixture over all. Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: corn concoction
directions: Mix the Rice-A-Roni as directed on the box.
Add and mix remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes (cooked, peeled and mashed), margarine, eggs (beaten), sugar, milk, salt and vanilla.
Add topping for casserole, place in oven and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rondele
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Chill several hours.
Serve with fresh vegetables or crackers.

title: pineapple ginger roll-up
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Line a 10x15x1 inch jellyroll pan with aluminum foil.
Melt the butter in the pan and spread evenly. Pour the pineapple into a wire strainer and drain well, reserving syrup.

Combine the drained pineapple, pecans and coconut in a small bowl. Stir to mix. Spoon this mixture evenly into pan. Drizzle the condensed milk over the mixture. In medium bowl, sift together the flour, ginger, soda, and salt. In a large bowl, beat the eggs until light and fluffy, about 2 minutes. Add sugars and beat until well blended. Add the flour mixture, pineapple syrup and vanilla. Beat for 1 to 2 minutes or until smooth.
Pour evenly into pan.

Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched. Remove from oven and sprinkle generously with the confectioners' sugar. Cover with a clean dish towel and invert. Remove the foil.
Roll the cake jellyroll fashion, starting with the 10 inch side. Wrap the towel around the roll until cool.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pan.
Beat oil, sugar and
eggs
until
smooth.
Add flour, soda and vanilla. Fold in apples
and
nuts.
Bake
45 minutes at 350° in Bundt cake pan.

title: frankfurter kabob
directions: Alternate sliced frankfurter, pickle slices and onion slices on skewers.
Brush with desired amount of mustard.
Grill until frankfurters are well browned.
Push from skewer onto an open roll.
Baste with barbecue sauce while cooking, if desired.

title: microwave crustless quiche lorraine
directions: Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in bottom of 9-inch glass pie plate or quiche dish.
Beat together remaining ingredients and pour over bacon mixture.
Microwave at 50% power (Medium) for 20 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Boil hen, remove from bone.
Boil spaghetti in chicken stock. Cook tomatoes, onions, garlic, celery , bell pepper, stuffed olives and mushrooms for 2 hours.
Grate cheese.
Layer baking dish with spaghetti, cheese and sauce.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: apple dumplin
directions: Halve apples.
Melt butter in a very large bowl or 2 separate bowls.
Wrap butter biscuit around each half apple.
Place in dish in the butter.
Dissolve sugar in water.
Pour around apples. Sprinkle cinnamon to taste on apples.
Cook 40 to 50 minutes on 350°.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain grease.
Mix next 5 ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Top with grated cheese and sour cream.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, then add milk to make a soft dough. Roll out 1/4-inch thick. Spread with cheese and pimento. Roll up like jelly roll and slice. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tortilla pie
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add Ro-Tel and tomato sauce.
Stir.
Place 1 tortilla in bottom of casserole and add a layer of sauce and grated cheese.
Place another tortilla on top; continue, alternating layers, until dish is filled.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.
Serves 6.

title: chicken supreme
directions: In skillet, in 1 tablespoon hot oil, cook chicken for 10 minutes, or until browned.
Remove and pour off fat.
In skillet, combine soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover; cook over low heat until chicken is no longer pink.
Stir often.
Serve with rice; garnish with parsley, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: rhubarb-raspberry pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, stir together the sugar and flour.
Stir in rhubarb, raspberries and apple.
Transfer to a pastry-lined 9-inch pie plate.
Trim pastry even with the rim of pie plate. Cut slits in the top crust.
Place top crust over filling.
Seal and flute edge.
Cover edges with foil.
Bake in 375°
oven for 25 minutes.
Remove foil.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes more until top is golden and fruit tender.
Cool and eat.

title: zesty seafood stew
directions: Put onions, garlic and oil in dish.
Cover with plastic wrap and vent.
Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Add next 9 ingredients; cook 10 minutes, stirring often.
Add snapper and scallops and cook 2 minutes.
Cook mussels and shrimp in another dish, covered and vented, 2 minutes.
Remove shrimp and peel and add to snapper. Continue to cook mussels until open, about 1 minute, and add with juices to snapper.

title: seven-up pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar well.
Add eggs and continue beating.
Add flour gradually, add vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Slowly add Seven-Up.
Pour in large tube pan.
Bake one hour and 10 minutes at 325°.

title: crab or shrimp rangoon
directions: Mix cream cheese, shrimp or crab and celery together in a bowl.
Mix flour with a little water to make paste.
Heat up 3-inches of oil in a deep pan.
Put one teaspoon of cheese mixture in the center of one won ton wrapper.
Use the paste to glue it together like a pillow with wings.
Deep fry each rangoon until golden.
They only cook a short time, once the oil is hot.
Serve with sweet and sour sauce.

title: chinese chicken wings(for appetizers or meals)
directions: Disjoint chicken wings, discarding tip ends.
Stir together the soy sauce, vinegar, sugars, ginger and garlic for marinade. Place in bowl; cover and marinate at least 2 hours or best overnight.
To cook, place in 13 x 9-inch oblong pan and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 10 to 12 appetizers.

title: brown bread
directions: Grease and flour several empty soup and/or vegetable cans. Preheat oven to 350°.
Add soda to boiling water; soak raisins in soda water.
Add butter and salt to raisins and water.
Soak for approximately 10 minutes.
Cream sugar with well beaten eggs.
Add flour alternately with liquid from raisins.
Add raisins, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into cans (about 2/3 full).
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: nanny's lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix well together.
Beat 2 egg whites until stiff; fold in. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°; then bake at 350° about 35 minutes.

title: "chicken enchilada casserole"
directions: Cut chicken in cubes or into pieces.
Brown chicken in frypan. (Add dash of seasonings, garlic salt and pepper.)
Mix in large bowl the mixture of chicken soup, milk, green chilies, chicken and cheese.
(Save at least 1 cup of cheese for the top of casserole.) Spray dish with Pam.
In casserole dish, layer stripped uncooked corn tortillas, covering the entire bottom of dish.
Cover tortillas with the mixture.
Repeat layers at least 3 to 4 times (depending on how high casserole dish).
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
(If you have an electric oven, it's longer time.) The last 5 minutes, cover top of casserole dish with grated cheese.

title: chicken a la king
directions: In a large skillet, cook and stir mushrooms in margarine for 5 minutes.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring until bubbly.
Remove from heat; stir in cream and broth and heat to boiling. Stir constantly for 1 minute.
Stir in chicken.
Serve over rice, noodles, mashed potatoes or toast.

title: waikiki chicken
directions: In paper or plastic bag combine flour and salt.
Add 2 or 3 chicken pieces at a time; shake to coat.
In large skillet cook chicken pieces in hot cooking oil over medium heat about 15 minutes, turning as necessary to brown evenly.
Meanwhile, combine undrained pineapple, barbecue sauce, cornstarch, brown sugar and dry mustard.
Pour mixture over chicken pieces in skillet.
Cover and cook over low heat 35 to 40 minutes or until tender, turning once.
Arrange on serving platter; garnish with green pepper rings.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt with 1/4 cup cold milk.
Add to scalded milk; cook over low heat (or cook in a double boiler) until thick.
Add beaten yolks and cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and coconut.
Cool and pour into baked pie shell.

title: crock-pot beef burgundy
directions: Trim meat and flour; simmer in skillet to brown, then put in crock-pot. Saute mushrooms and add to crock-pot.
Add onion soup mix, mushroom soup and Burgundy.
Cook all day, if possible. Serve with rice or noodles.

title: english pasties
directions: Sift flour and salt. Cut in lard until crumbly. Add water gradually to make soft dough.
The less handling, the better.
On floured board, roll dough into 12 circles, dinner plate size.
Cut meat into small pieces. Cut onion, potatoes, rutabaga and carrots into separate dishes.
Place even amounts of vegetables and meats on each circle, beginning with onion, then meats with salt and pepper, potato, rutabaga and carrot.
Add a dab of butter to each. Fold over and seal with water.
Cut slits in top. Bake on greased baking sheet, don't crowd, at 450° for 45 minutes until browned.

title: baked devil's float(in honor of "the senator")
directions: Sift first 5 dry ingredients together.
Add milk, vanilla, butter and nuts.

Pour into a well-greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Mix the 1/2 cup white sugar, 1/2 cup light brown sugar, 5 tablespoons cocoa and the cup of hot (boiling) water together and pour over the batter in the baking dish.
Bake in a 350°
oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve upside down.
Can be served slightly warm or completely cooled.
Good topped with whipped cream, or served with ice cream.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix well and pour into 2 oiled and floured 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool completely.
Freezes well.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Cut chicken to bite size.
Brown lightly.
Slice onions.
Put in with chicken.
Toss lightly.
Add 1 cup cashews, soy sauce to taste.
Cook until onions are done.
Cashews are better without oil or salt.

title: lemon cake
directions: Bake lemon cake as directed.
Let cool and slice layers in half.
Mix Eagle Brand milk, frozen lemonade and Cool Whip together.
Spread between layers.
Refrigerate.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix ingredients with meat; blend well.
Heat to boiling point. Pour over spaghetti and serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: bibb salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate in closed container.

title: baked stuffed chicken breasts
directions: With meat mallet, lightly pound chicken breasts to 1/2-inch thickness. In large skillet over medium heat in 1 tablespoon hot butter, cook mushrooms and onions until tender and liquid is evaporated, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat. Stir in cream cheese, dill, salt and pepper. Spread 1/4 cup mushroom mixture on each chicken breast. Fold into lengthwise halves. Secure with toothpick.

title: house special soup
directions: Cut vermicelli into 1-inch pieces and set aside.
In large pan bring broth to boil.
Stir in vermicelli, shrimp, lettuce, mushrooms and scallions.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in dissolved cornstarch and teriyaki sauce.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Serves 8.

title: naki's greek cookies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together, then add all the liquid and peel.
Mix until smooth ball of dough is formed.
Take a piece of dough about the size of the inside of your palm and roll into a "worm".
Place on undreased cookie sheet and cross ends twice. Bake 350° for 20-25 minutes.

title: baked carrots
directions: Halve carrots lengthwise and place in shallow baking dish. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 400°.
Sprinkle with 2 teaspoons snipped parsley (optional) and serve.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix flour, yeast, sugar, milk and salt together.
Add warm water, oil and egg.
Mix by hand; spoon into greased muffin tins, filling half full.
Bake at 400° for about 12 minutes or until brown.
This dough will keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: bettie's best lasagna
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef.
Drain fat.
Stir in Romano cheese and tomato sauce.
Add oregano, garlic juice and salt.
Let cook for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile boil lasagna noodles.
Mix egg with cottage cheese.
Layer ingredients as follows in 9 x 13 pan:
Meat sauce, noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese, meat sauce, noodles, etc.

title: shrimp gumbo with rice
directions: Cook bacon in frying pan to extract fat.
Add onion and cook 5 minutes.
Add flour, stirring until browned.
Put tomatoes, water, okra and shrimp in soup kettle.
Add bacon-onion mixture, bay leaf, salt and pepper to taste.
Add cayenne pepper.
Simmer 1 hour.
Serve in large soup plates over cooked rice.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter in baking dish.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into baking dish and swirl in melted butter. Spoon in favorite fruit.
(Be sure fruit is fixed and seasoned the way you desire before spooning into mixture.)
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: southern cornbread
directions: Mix together and pour into greased pan.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: christmas salad
directions: Dissolve 1 package lime Jell-O as directed and put in 8 x 8-inch dish.
Let stand until firm in refrigerator.
Dissolve 1 package lime Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water and cool.
Soften cream cheese and mix with salad dressing.
Drain pineapple and Cool Whip.
When gelatin is cool, mix together with cream cheese mixture.
Put on top of first layer of gelatin.
When this is set, dissolve cherry Jell-O and let cool.
Pour on top and refrigerate.

title: glazed pork spareribs
directions: Cut ribs and place in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Pour off fat.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over ribs.
Bake 1 hour longer until done or tender.

title: chocolate whipped cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and salt; stir in milk and heat to boiling.
Remove from heat.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Stir into hot mixture.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Add vanilla.
Fold in cream and pour into pie shell.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with whipped cream, if desired.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix margarine; add beaten eggs and sugar, then add pecans and raisins.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes or until done.
Very good.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: The night before:
Cook and drain sausage.
Beat the eggs and evaporated milk.
Add sausage, bread and cheese.
Put in a 9 x 9-inch casserole.
Cover with foil; refrigerate overnight.

title: purple lady
directions: Add 1 1/2 cups boiling water to Jell-O; stir in blueberry pie filling and pineapple.
Let thicken.
Whip Dream Whip and fold in or Cool Whip.

title: herbed buttermilk chicken
directions: Dry chicken pieces well and dredge in seasoned flour.
Heat butter and oil in a large skillet.
Add shallot and chicken.
Cook until golden brown.
Stir in tomatoes, buttermilk, salt, pepper and sugar.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Blend in chives, dill and parsley.
Continue cooking, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Serve immediately over rice or noodles.

title: egg salad spread
directions: Stand in hot water 5 minutes more.
Peel and chop.
Add mayonnaise,
sweet pickle relish, mustard, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix together.
Yields about 3 cups.
May add cheese.

title: egg rolls
directions: Saute all vegetables separately in a teaspoon of oil until glossy.
Cook chicken pieces in oil.
Mix soy sauce with vegetables and chicken.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done.
In a large bowl, mix soup, tomatoes, cheese, and taco mix.
Line bottom of pan with Doritos. Shred chicken and add to bowl with soup mixture.
Add chicken broth to the mixture.
Pour the mixture over the Doritos.
Bake at 350 until the cheese has melted.
Serve with Doritos, sour cream, and salsa on the side.

title: stuffed eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash.
Mix all ingredients together. Re-fill egg whites.
Chill until serving time.

title: best cornbread dressing
directions: Bake cornbreads as directed.
Cool and break into crumbs. Place margarine and seasonings in microwave bowl and microwave on High 5 minutes or saute on stove.
Crumble sausage and cook thoroughly.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Best way is to use your hands.
If dressing is too dry, use another can of chicken broth.
Best when cooked inside a large turkey according to directions.
If baked in a casserole, dot with butter and bake, covered for 1 1/2 hours at 275°.

title: shrimp fondue
directions: Flake crabmeat and toss with mayonnaise and onion.
Spoon onto canape bases (above).
Sprinkle generously with cheese.
Broil 3 inches from source of heat 1 to 2 minutes, until cheese is melted and slightly browned.
Serve hot.
Makes 20 to 24 canapes.

title: meatballs and sauce
directions: Mix and roll into meatballs.
Then fry or bake.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Follow directions on back of stuffing mix.
Add 1 cup of chicken broth (retain from stewing chicken) instead of 1 cup water.
Spread half the stuffing in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add chopped chicken.
Mix together soups and milk and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle onion over mixture.
Spread remaining stuffing over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: untossed salad
directions: Break up lettuce.
Put sliced celery and sliced onion rings on top.
Mix sour cream and sugar; drizzle over top.
Mix mayonnaise and wine vinegar; drizzle over top.
Crumble cooked bacon on top. Cover with cheese.
Chill, uncovered, for 3 hours.
Do not toss.

title: doris' potato pancakes
directions: Peel large potatoes.
Cover with cold water.
Soak several hours before using.
Drain and grate.
Stir in sieve to release most of water.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful into hot, well greased skillet; brown on both sides.
Good served with applesauce.

title: dark chocolate cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix brown sugar, butter and vanilla. Mix in eggs one at a time.
Smooth mixture together.
Melt semi-sweet chocolate and unsweetened chocolate; then add to mixture. In a separate bowl sift together flour, unsweetened cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add to mixture and stir well.
Add butterscotch chips and mix thoroughly.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make cookies the size you want.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Add cherries.
Fold in. Pour into 11 x 7 x 15-inch oblong baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Serve warm with milk and sugar or cold as a snack cake.

title: south of the border cheese dip
directions: Brown burger and sausage together; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, paste, chilies and peppers.
Add cheese and stir until blended and cheese is melted.
Serve in tortillas or with chips.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Cut in shortening, then yeast and buttermilk.
Mix with a large spoon real good.
You can pinch off each day just the amount you want.
It will keep a week to 10 days, covered in refrigerator.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: bowl of the best(servings:  6)
directions: Bring broth to boil; add beans, chicken, chili peppers, Liquid Smoke, paprika and oregano.
Cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Add avocado slices.
Mound rice and chunks of cheese in soup bowls.
Ladle in hot soup.
Serves 6.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Mix flour in about 1/8 cup cold water and add to chicken broth.
Cool a minute or so to thicken.
Add chicken, pimentos, mushroom soup, salt, pepper and red pepper, all to taste.
Add eggs.
Crush crackers and add to mixture.
Add sauteed vegetables. Mix well.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Put crumbled crackers (about 15) on top.
Bake at 325° or 350° for 45 minutes.
Make gravy with 3 cups of broth.

title: hamburg bologna
directions: Mix hamburg and Tender Quick together; refrigerate overnight. Add garlic powder, liquid smoke and pepper.
Shape into 4 rolls. Bake at 225° for 4 hours.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Soak sliced cucumbers in salt for 4 hours.
Drain and rinse off.
Make mixture of the sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Pour over cucumbers and refrigerate.
Can add an onion with cucumbers for flavor, if desired. Store in glass container; keeps for weeks.

title: chicken with sour cream sauce
directions: Place a slice of cheese and a slice of ham on each chicken breast and roll up.
Place chicken rolls in a greased casserole dish and cover with mushrooms. Combine undiluted soup, sherry and sour cream. Stir until blended.
Pour over chicken and dust with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Mix all together and bake until bubbly in the oven or microwave.
Dip with crackers or corn chips.
May be done in a crock pot.

title: chocolate krispies(a delicious chewy blend of chocolate and peanut butter)
directions: Heat sugar and Karo until sugar dissolves.
Add peanut butter. Stir until melted.
Add Rice Krispies and cool slightly.
Spread this mixture in a buttered cookie sheet pan (12 x 8-inch).

title: baked tacos
directions: Fry tortillas until soft in small amount of oil; drain on paper towels.
Put strips of cheese and chilies in center of tortillas.
Roll up tortillas.
Place 1 layer deep in 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain off fat.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Flavor with salt and pepper.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream the
butter
and peanut butter.
Add and mix well the remaining
ingredients.
Put
large
scoops
of
dough
on ungreased baking
pan (6 per sheet) and flatten each slightly. Bake at 350° for 10
to
minutes.
Do not overbake.
After you remove cooked cookies from
the oven, let them rest on the sheets for 10 minutes before removing.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with a spoon.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Ice while hot.
Let cool and refrigerate until serving.

title: mexican deep dish pizza
directions: Quarter the biscuts. In large bowl, combine biscuts, salsa, green pepper & olives. Mix gently. Add about 1-handful of the chopped green onions. Add the garlic. Add 1/2 the cheese. Stir well. Spread the mixture in a 13x9 pan. Sprinkle remaining cheese and green onions on top. Bake at 350 for 40-45 min. Serve with sour cream.
Enjoy!

title: baked apples
directions: Core apples and peel skin from top 1 inch of each apple.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and bread.
Pile lightly into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread cubes and cheese. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: stewed chicken creole style
directions: Place chicken in kettle of water; add salt and simmer 20 minutes, then add lima beans, tomatoes, onions, okra, corn and rice.
Cook until done.
Mix flour and butter into a paste.
Stir into the liquid; add Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil once more and serve.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Sprinkle all spices over crackers.
Add oil.
Stir.
Mix often.
Let set for 24 hours, stirring often as you can.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt together.
Combine with mixture.
Add nuts and apples and mix well.
Pour in greased and floured pan. Sprinkle butterscotch chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until done.

title: baby beets in sour cream
directions: Combine ingredients except beets.
Mix well and add sauce to beets slowly.
Stir to coat.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: rich and meaty macaroni
directions: Cook and drain macaroni according to package.
Heat milk in saucepan.
Add cheese so it can melt, stirring constantly.
Add oleo, onion, salt and pepper.
Keep turning heat down.
Stir hot macaroni into sauce.
Spray 1 1/2 to 2-quart dish with nonstick spray. Pour in macaroni with sauce mix. Add Ragu sauce as a layer on top of macaroni.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Crush Ritz or Hi Ho crackers and layer on top of meat sauce.
Bake 10 more minutes before serving.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except milk.
Add enough milk to form balls.
Drop from teaspoon into hot fat in which fish has been fried or cook along with fish.
Cook until well browned and cooked throughout.
Serves 4.

title: onion ring batter
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Dip sliced onion rings in batter and fry in hot grease.
Fry until golden brown or floating.

title: lydia's fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let set overnight.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken in water for 1 hour with bay leaf and salt.
When cooked, debone and cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Skim fat off broth, then cook spaghetti in broth.
Drain spaghetti and save 3 cups broth.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onions and garlic in melted butter.
Then add all other ingredients.
Cook for 1 hour or until thick.

title: cherry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sift dry ingredients together, except for 2 tablespoons sugar.
Mix together the egg, milk and melted butter.
Sprinkle the chopped cherries with the reserved 2 tablespoons of sugar and mix.
Add cherries to the dry ingredients to the wet and combine quickly.
Do not overmix.
Lumps are okay. Immediately turn batter into greased muffin tins, filling each cup 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool muffins on a rack before serving.

title: tropical carrot cake
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg and allspice.
Set aside.
In large bowl of mixer, beat eggs slightly.
Gradually beat in sugar until mixture is thick and lemon colored.
With rubber spatula, gradually stir (fold) in oil.
Add flour mixture, carrots, pineapple and coconut.
Stir until well mixed.
Divide among three greased and floured 9-inch layer pans or 15 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes for layers, 55 to 60 minutes for sheet cake or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
For layers, cool longer than usual to prevent sticking and tearing when removing.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Fry chicken wings. Mix other ingredients. Dip wings in mixture and bake 10 min. at 350°.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in boiling water until tender; drain and set aside.
Mix melted margarine and bread stuffing and mix well.
Pat half of bread stuffing on bottom of 8 x 12-inch casserole dish. Save the other half of stuffing for topping.

title: molded vegetable salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add cold water, vinegar and onion.
Chill until firm.
Fold in vegetables.
Chill.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Make pudding with 3 cups milk.
Beat until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place whole graham crackers in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer pudding and crackers, ending with crackers on top.
Melt butter and mix cocoa, vanilla and powdered sugar with 3 tablespoons hot water.
Spread on top of graham crackers.
Chill and serve.

title: burrangas
directions: Chop beef in small pieces.
Mix with green chilies, cheese and onions.

title: german chocolate bars(cream cheese brownies)
directions: Grease and flour 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Mix German chocolate cake mix as directed on box.
Pour into prepared pan. Mix cream cheese, egg and sugar and drizzle mixture on top of cake mix.
Take knife and swirl mixture through cake mix.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and pecans over the top.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: polenta
directions: Boil water, salt and oil.
Add corn meal into thin, steady stream.
Stir continuously until mixture comes away from sides of pan.
Remove from heat.
Stir in onions, (4 ounces; 1 cup) Mozzarella, Parmesan cheeses and eggs.
Spread in oiled 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove and immediately spread with a thin layer of tomato sauce.
Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella over tomato sauce.
Serves 8.

title: ham and swiss rolls
directions: Mix margarine, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, onion and cheese.
Slice rolls in half. Spread mixture on rolls. Top with ham. Replace tops of rolls. Wrap in foil.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: blue ribbon pound cake
directions: Sift together flour and baking powder.
Set aside.
Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Add sugar gradually, creaming all the time.
Add eggs one at a time, beating just to mix.
Combine milk and vanilla.
Add the dry ingredients alternately with the milk, beginning and ending with the dry ingredients.

title: hot cereal mix
directions: Sift together to blend evenly.
Store in a tightly covered jar. For a crumb coating, combine 1 1/2 tablespoons of the base seasoned flour with 1 cup of fine dry bread crumbs.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans.
Form a ball and roll in pecans.

title: peanut butter treats
directions: Mix all but chocolate and wax together and form into balls. Using a toothpick, dip balls into melted chocolate and wax.
Put on wax paper to cool.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; mix well into loaf pan.
Combine last 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour over meat loaf and bake in a 350° oven for 60 minutes.

title: heavenly delight
directions: Break cake in bite-sized pieces in one bowl.
Mix milk and lemon juice in another bowl.
Pour over cake.
Add strawberries and Cool Whip; toss lightly.
Refrigerate 6 hours.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Mix soups, chili salsa, onion and olives.
Tear tortillas into small pieces (4 to 6 pieces).
In baking dish, put layers.
Start with tortillas, then chicken, then sauce, then cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let sit before cutting.

title: wine cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake in tube pan about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: icebox cheese cake
directions: Roll out graham crackers.
Cut in butter and powdered sugar. Press in 9 x 13-inch pan (glass preferred).
Save 3/4 cup for topping.
Mix jello into 1 cup boiling water; set aside to cool, not jell.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease two 10-inch pie plates. Toss hot spaghetti with olive oil or butter.
Combine eggs and 1/2 cup Parmesan; stir into spaghetti.
Divide spaghetti mixture and place equal portions into pie plate.
Form into a crust.
Spread 1/2 cup Ricotta over bottom of each crust.
Top with spaghetti sauce.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes.
Top with Mozzarella. Bake 5 minutes more, until cheese melts.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle each with remainder of Parmesan.
Cool 10 minutes before cutting into wedges.

title: no-fuss meatballs
directions: In a skillet, cook meatballs in soy sauce until heated through.
Combine the chili sauce, jelly and mustard; pour over the meatballs.
Cook and stir until jelly is dissolved and mixture comes to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 to 2 minutes.
Yield: about 2 dozen.

title: tinting coconut
directions: You will need a lidded jar and paper towels.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together well sugar and margarine.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cream of onion soup
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, saute onions in butter over low heat until they are transparent.
Stir in flour and cook for an additional 3 minutes.
Add hot milk slowly to onion mixture, using a wire whip.
Allow soup to gently simmer for 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Mix the egg yolks and heavy cream in a medium bowl; add a small portion of hot soup to the egg mixture, then stir mixture back into the soup.
Cook for 1 minute; don't allow soup to simmer.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour soup into individual bowls and serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: spicy yogurt dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium bowl; mix thoroughly.
Serve with raw veggies of your choice.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour or longer.

title: pumpkin or sweet potato bread
directions: Mix together and put into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer lettuce 1/2 inch deep in pan.
Sprinkle with onion over top of lettuce, in layers, add celery and peas.
Cover with mayonnaise so no air can get to lettuce.
Sprinkle with sugar. Sprinkle cheese and crumbled bacon (can use bacon bits).
Top with additional cheese.
Let set, well covered, in fridge 12 to 24 hours before serving.
Will keep for one week if kept covered and refrigerated.

title: no-fail coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and margarine.
Add coconut and pineapple. Pour into pie shells and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: microwave coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch; slowly add milk.
Beat egg yolks; add a little milk mixture to eggs.
Beat, then add eggs to milk. Add salt and butter.
Cook in microwave on High approximately 8 minutes.
Stir often to keep it from getting lumpy.
When almost thickened, add vanilla.
Cook another minute.
Stir in coconut. Put in baked pie shell; top with meringue.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Peel, cube and toss with onions, pimento, pepper and celery seed.

title: witches' brew
directions: Heat all ingredients and remove cinnamon sticks before serving.

title: summer dip
directions: Put in bowl; mix and eat with chips.
Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: camphouse stew
directions: Cook venison in cast-iron Dutch oven on top of stove over medium heat until tender.
Add water as needed.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until done.
Make sure the stew has sufficient amount of liquid to cover meat and vegetables.
Make gravy base and add to the stew.
Liquid base will thicken.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve with warmed buttered rolls.

title: sweet and sour saucelubbock, texas
directions: Mix vinegar, 1 c. water and sugar and bring to a boil in saucepan.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix two packages lemon gelatin, 2 cups boiling water, 7-Up, pineapple (save juice) and sliced bananas.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and let chill until firm.
Then cook until thick 1 cup pineapple juice (if not enough, add water), sugar, flour, slightly beaten egg and 2 tablespoons butter; let cool.
Fold in whipped topping and coconut.
Spread pecan pieces over the top.

title: microwave chicken parmesan
directions: Pound 2 chicken breasts until thin.
Bread chicken.
Dip in beaten egg and water and bread again.
Put 1 tablespoon of oil in the bottom of the pan; place chicken.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon of oil.
Cook 2 to 2 1/2 minutes at High.
Turn.
Cook 2 to 2 1/2 minutes on High.
Top with tomato sauce.
Cook 3 1/4 to 4 1/4 minutes on High to heat sauce.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and let stand until cheese melts.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Melt margarine.
Add milk.
Add sugar, coconut and pecans. Mix and shape into small balls.

title: pizzelle(italian waffles)
directions: Mix all ingredients to form a dough.
If dough is sticky, sprinkle with more flour.
Roll into balls about the size of a fifty-cent piece.
Bake in pizzelle iron, making sure not to let them get too dark.
Tip:
Before using iron, roll wax paper into a ball, rub with oil and then using wax paper ball, rub oil onto pizzelle iron.
This will help prevent sticking.
Also, when storing pizzelle iron, leave a sheet of wax paper in machine.

title: bean burrito bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Cook ground beef, stirring frequently, until brown; drain.
Mix beans, Bisquick mix and water.
Spread in bottom and halfway up sides of pie pan.
Top with beef, avocado, salsa and cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Top each serving with dollop of sour cream if desired. Makes 8 servings.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add dry ingredients, bananas and buttermilk.
Mix until all flour is dampened.
Beat vigorously for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and beat 2 minutes longer.
Fold in nuts. Pour into sprayed pan(s).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Place cooked potatoes in a lightly greased baking dish. Combine tomatoes, soup and oregano.
Pour over potatoes.
Top with pepperoni slices or browned hamburger and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans until crumbly.
Pat into glass dish and bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1/2 container of Cool Whip.
Pour on top of crust.
Mix pudding and milk together.
Pour in a dish on top of cream cheese layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with pecans.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain grease and add other ingredients.
Bake at 400° in oven 20 to 30 minutes.

title: bacon pancakes or spekpannekoeken(a dutch recipe)
directions: Put the flour and salt in a bowl.
Make well in the center. Add the diluted (with a little milk) yeast.
Add 2 cups milk and mix to a smooth batter.
Add the rest of the milk.
Leave to rise for 3/4 hour.
Meanwhile, fry the bacon in the skillet until crisp. Divide into as many portions as pancakes required.
Also pour dripping out of pan.
Use for frying next pancake.
Put the bacon on the bottom of the pan.
Pour batter on top.
Bake the pancakes until crisp at the sides and golden brown.
Toss (turn) once or twice.
Serve with brown sugar or molasses, treacle or golden syrup.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: diet bread pudding
directions: Scald milk.
Mix together egg, sweetener and vanilla.
Add egg mixture to milk.
Break bread into small chunks in baking dish. Pour egg and milk mixture over bread, allowing a few pieces to float on top.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes in a pan of water. Serve hot, warm or cold.
Serves one.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and nutmeg; add eggs and stir well (when mixed this way, eggs don't need prior beating).
Add milk and mix; then add rhubarb.
Put into pie shell; dot with butter and cover with top crust.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: window washing
directions: Run this through the full perk-cycle and serve hot.

title: cranberry relish salad
directions: Grind together the first 5 ingredients.
Add sugar and pineapple.
Mix jello and hot water.
Add jello to other ingredients and chill in refrigerator overnight.
It will keep for two weeks in refrigerator.

title: chocolate speckled cake frosting
directions: Mix on low butter, cocoa and salt, then add vanilla, half and half and sugar.
Use on Chocolate Speckled Cake.

title: zucchini-tomato soup
directions: Combine zucchini and water in Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat and simmer until zucchini is crisp-tender.
In small skillet, melt butter; add onion and cook until tender.
Add to zucchini mixture with tomatoes, bouillon cubes, garlic and seasonings.
Return to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; simmer until zucchini is tender.
Makes 8 servings.
Freezes well.

title: old-fashioned sorghum cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sorghum and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture along with the hot water.
Add more flour, if needed, to make a stiff cookie dough.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased baking sheet 1-inch or more apart.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 10 minutes.
Makes about 100 drop cookies.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries with water and boil until cranberries pop. Add sugar and gelatine (soften in a little cold water).
Mix well. Heat again until sugar dissolves.
After cools, add celery, nuts and apples.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate.
Needs time to gel.

title: easy salad
directions: Mix in the order given.
Refrigerate.
May be made 1 day ahead.
Can be used as salad or dessert.

title: pollo con pimientos y almendras(chicken with red pimientos and almonds)
directions: Sprinkle the chicken with salt and pepper.
Dip the pieces in flour and shake them to remove the excess.
In a heavy skillet, heat the olive oil over high heat.
Put the pieces of chicken, skin side down, and brown them, turning them with tongs and regulating the heat so the pieces color quickly and evenly without burning.
Transfer them to a heavy casserole.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of fat and add the onions, stirring frequently.
Cook them for 5 minutes.
Spread the onion over the chicken in the casserole and add the parsley, mashed with the almonds, garlic and bouillon (diluted in 1/2 cup of liquid from the casserole).
Add the bay leaf and the red pimientos, wine and water.
Let it simmer.
Cover for 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.
You can serve it with rice.

title: roman apple cake
directions: Combine Crisco, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add soda, baking powder, salt and flour.
Then add nuts and apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Mix brown sugar, flour, cinnamon and butter.
Put on top.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine sour cream, mayonnaise, cream cheese and seasonings. Mix well. Then stir in cheddar cheese and crab. Cover & chill 2 hours. Serve over triscuits.

title: lyn and leola's enchiladas
directions: *Buy more than one can of Old El Paso mild enchilada sauce.

title: crock-pot brunswick stew
directions: In a 3 1/2 to 4-quart or 5 to 6-quart crock-pot, stir together undrained tomatoes and tomato paste.
Add chicken, frozen succotash or okra, onion, bay leaf, salt, rosemary, pepper and cloves.
Stir in chicken broth.
Cover; cook on low for 10 to 12 hours or on high for 5 to 6 hours.
Remove bay leaf.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: spiced maple cider(makes about 2 quarts)
directions: In large saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer uncovered for 20 minutes.
Remove orange and spices.
Serve warm.
Garnish as desired.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Chop banana and apple.
Add grapes, orange sections and orange juice (concentrated).
Mix.

title: blonde chocolate chip brownies
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in all ingredients except chips.
Put in greased and floured 9 x 15-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chips.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix uncooked rice with hamburger meat, salt, pepper and onion. Shape into balls the size of walnuts.
Brown on all sides in cooking oil.
Use covered pan.
After browning, add tomatoes, cover and cook slow for about 30 minutes or until rice is tender and meatball is almost doubled in size.

title: simple cordon bleu
directions: Top each breast with a slice of ham and a slice of cheese. Secure with toothpicks.
Cover; heat on low for 20 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 3 to 6.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix egg yolks, oleo, milk and salt together.
Mix cornstarch and sugar; add to milk mixture.
Stir until desired thickness, add coconut.
Makes 2 pies.
Pour into 2 baked shells.
Top with following meringue.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit and juices with pudding mix.
Fold in Reddi-Wip and chill.

title: garden salad
directions: Mix sugar, oil, vinegar and bean juice and bring to a boil. Place the first 9 items listed in a large bowl and pour hot liquid over them.
Allow this to stand overnight in the refrigerator after it cools.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Put in bananas.
Add eggs and vanilla. Then add Bisquick and nuts.
Bake at 350° until done.
There is no liquid in this.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Wash and pack cucumbers in a quart jar.
Add the salt, pickling spices, alum and vinegar, then finish filling jar with cold water.
Put lid on tight enough so that it won't leak, but do not seal.
Shake it up and down 3 times to dissolve salt and alum. Store for 3 months.

title: sweet potato surprise
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Heat potatoes, thoroughly drain and mash. Add pineapple, butter, sugar, pecans, nutmeg, cinnamon and 1/2 c. marshmallows.
Mix thoroughly and pour into baking dish or casserole dish.
Top with remaining marshmallows.
Bake for 15 minutes or until marshmallows start to brown.

title: buttermilk bass
directions: Cut bass fillets into finger-size strips.
Salt and put enough buttermilk over strips to completely cover.
Soak overnight.
Roll strips in salt (depending on your taste) and self-rising flour. Keep strips separated until placed in deep fryer.
Cook until golden brown, being careful not to overcook.

title: rhubarb nut bread
directions: Mix the 1 1/2 cups brown sugar, oil, egg, vanilla and sour milk.
Add the flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Fold in the rhubarb and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pans. Sprinkle on 1/2 cup brown sugar mixed with the cinnamon for topping.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar, baking cocoa, margarine and evaporated milk in heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook, uncovered, to 234° to 240° on candy thermometer, soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla; beat until thickened.
Fold in walnuts.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square dish.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Yield:
48 servings.

title: bird nests
directions: Melt peanut butter
and
butterscotch morsels in top of double boiler.
Add chow
mein
noodles.
Drop on cookie sheet and cool until hardened.

title: veal parmigiana with vermicelli
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In shallow dish, combine 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, bread crumbs, oregano and pepper; mix well.
Coat each cutlet with flour; dip in eggs.
Coat with Parmesan cheese mixture.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat; cook cutlets about 6 to 7 minutes, until golden brown on both sides.
Remove from skillet.
Arrange cutlets in ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with mushrooms.
Spoon spaghetti sauce over mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix together.
Press 1/2 the mixture in bottom of shallow baking dish.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix flour, melted oleo and powdered sugar.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch or large cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: spudnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water until yeast starts to work.
Mix warm milk, shortening, potatoes, salt, baking powder and vanilla; beat until there are no lumps. Mix in yeast mixture.
Add flour and knead until dough is light and elastic.
Place in greased bowl; let rise 2 hours.
Knead down and let rise again.
Roll out on lightly floured board to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with tuna can and poke hole in center of dough with finger.
Place on floured towel, let rise. Fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Drop doughnut top side down to fry.

title: seafood quiche
directions: In large bowl, mix ingredients except cheese. Line pie shells with cheese and pour all ingredients into pie shells. Heat oven to 425° and bake for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350°.

Bake until knife comes out clean (approximately 45 minutes). To keep edges of crust from burning, cover crust with foil (just the edges). When rinsing seafood, pat dry with paper towels. Excess water will make quiche watery. Yields 2 quiche.

title: barbecued beef brisket
directions: Mix ingredients in a bowl and then spread on the brisket and wrap the brisket in heavy foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cook at 250° for 5 hours.
Open foil and pour off grease and cover with 1 cup of barbecue sauce.
Cook open for 1 more hour.
Heat any extra barbecue sauce.

title: hot chili
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients in large saucepan and simmer slowly.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Place dough on a cookie sheet or pizza pan, pinching perforations together.
Bake according to directions.
Cool. Blend the softened cream cheese with mayonnaise and seasonings. Spread on crust.
Top with veggies and cheese.
Refrigerate.

title: easy roast turkey
directions: Turkey:
Put turkey or hen in pot.
Cover with water; salt to taste.
Cook on medium heat until tender.

title: golden glow casserole
directions: Mix and bake 45 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 9-inch greased pan. Cover with foil; last 10 minutes uncover.

title: make ahead fruit salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, whipped cream and lemon juice; mix until well blended.
Fold in remaining ingredients; chill.
You can make this salad hours ahead; tastes even better when the fruit flavors mingle longer with marshmallows and whipped cream.

title: chocolate tofu pie
directions: Blend tofu until smooth.
Melt chocolate chips and add to tofu, blend.
Add honey (if used) and blend.
Fill baked crust. Chill overnight.
Enjoy.

title: spinach balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Stir together all ingredients in large bowl until well blended.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until firm.
Serve with heated spaghetti sauce, if desired.
Makes approximately 3 1/2 dozen.

title: no bake lemon pie
directions: Mix together and pour into your favorite graham cracker pie crust.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Shape into meatballs.
Brown in skillet on medium heat for 20 minutes.
For sauce use three jars Prego (48 ounces).
Use 4 pounds spaghetti.
Serves 20 people.

title: onion beef macaroni casserole
directions: Brown macaroni and add all remaining ingredients except for cheese.
Place in baking dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serves 6 people.

title: poor man's cookies
directions: Combine all dry ingredients, except soda.
Combine soda with hot water; stir into oat mixture along with shortening and vanilla.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden brown. Allow to stand on cookie sheets for 2 minutes before removing to wire rack.

title: rhubarb-strawberry jam
directions: Cook the rhubarb and sugar until mushy.
Stir in the jello. Put in jars.

title: quick dumplings
directions: Add salt to biscuit mix.
Combine egg and milk.
Add to mixture.
Stir with fork to form soft dough.
Drop on top of boiling soup or stew by tablespoonfuls.
Simmer uncovered about 12 to 15 minutes.
Then cover and simmer 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 1 dozen.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Add soup, milk and cheese; heat until cheese is melted.
Fold in rice and broccoli (thawed enough to pull apart).

title: sweet and sour party meatballs
directions: Put in small round balls on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° about 15 minutes.
Drain and put in sauce.
Makes about 150.

title: edible play dough
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well.
Let your child make their own snack creatures.

title: stir-fried broccoli and bacon
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan.
Add vegetables to bacon drippings.
Fry and stir for 1 minute on high.
Add water, cover and cook 2 minutes.
Uncover, add bacon and serve.
Salt to taste.

title: easy enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion and drain.
Add undiluted soups, taco sauce, enchilada sauce and green chilies.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer 5 tortillas, thin layer of meat sauce, 5 tortillas and remaining meat sauce.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: unleavened bread
directions: Blend honey, oil and milk.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Knead lightly.
Roll on floured board.
Place over rolling pin and place on cookie sheet.
Cut in squares.
Make a few holes in each piece with a fork.
Salt lightly if desired.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
One to 2 cups of wheat germ may be added.
Adjust the flour accordingly.

title: vegetable-beef soup
directions: Combine soup bones and water in a large Dutch oven or large pot, bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Add beef cubes, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add cubed potatoes and next 5 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes.
Add corn and peas.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.

title: pineapple stuffing(great with ham)
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in pineapple. Fold in bread cubes.
Turn into 1-quart greased casserole dish and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: marlene's meat loaf & tomato gravy
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bacon.
Shape meat into a loaf and place bacon on top of meat loaf before baking.
Make the gravy and pour over top of meat loaf and bake at 350° or 400° for 1 hour.
When meat loaf is done, drain off tomato mixture and thicken with flour and water.
This sauce may be used as a topping for your potatoes or noodles.

title: rice krispies strawberry dessert
directions: Mix Rice Krispies, coconut, brown sugar, butter and pecans together. Broil mixture 20 to 30 seconds in oven on cookie sheet until light brown. Spread 2/3 of mixture on bottom of 9 by 13 inch dish. Pour 1/2 gal. melted vanilla ice cream over Rice Krispies mix. Then top with remaining mix. Cover with foil and freeze until set. Serve with sliced strawberries and whipping cream.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Mix all of the ingredients, except the cheese, in a glass baking dish.
Shape into a firm loaf.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Spike the meat loaf with the cheese cubes.
Continue to bake for 1/2 hour or until center is completely done.
While the meat loaf is still hot, cover with shredded cheese.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cut, chop, dice beef and onions.
Mix with cream cheese.
Put in milk and Worcestershire sauce and knead together.
Make into a ball.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: three-fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit and serve with dressing.

title: slow cooker stuffed bell peppers
directions: Combine all ingredients except peppers and cheese. Gently pack mixture into peppers which have been capped and seeded. Place in greased slow cooker. Cover and cook on low 9-10 hours, or on high for 5-6 hours or until done.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute rice in oil until light brown.
Add onion and saute a few minutes more.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Stir and boil 3 minutes.
Turn down heat and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tempting shrimp spread
directions: Cut pimento peppers (small sweet red pepper) in sections as it has grown.
Rinse well to eliminate seeds.
Drop into boiling water and cover.
Stem about 8 minutes, or until you can slip skin off. Remove from boiling water to cold water.
With fingers or small knife, remove all skin.
Place sections in small sealable jar or jars; pack tight.
Drain off all juice and add small pinch of salt and seal.
Place jars in boiling water bath and process for 35 minutes, just simmering.
Remove from heat and let set until cool. Pimentos will be covered with juice in jars.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients. If needed, add more broth. Bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: cherokee indian crusty cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place 1/2 stick of butter in skillet. Place in oven to melt.
In bowl, mix flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and corn meal.
Add milk and egg.
Beat 1 minute by hand. Pour into hot pan of butter.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mandarin orange slush
directions: Dissolve orange gelatin in 2 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add undrained pineapple and orange juice.
Set the bowl in cool water to cool.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.
Chill in refrigerator until partially set.
Place in oranges throughout gelatin.
Chill until firm.
Beat pudding mix with milk until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spread over gelatin and chill.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for 3/4 cup pecans.
Roll into a ball.
Roll ball in remaining pecans.

title: banana split brownie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare brownie mix in large bowl, according to package directions.
Pour batter into 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool to room temperature.
Mix cream cheese and sugar until smooth. Spread over brownie "crust."
Top with fruit slices and nuts. Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: chicken in white wine
directions: Remove giblets from cavity of chicken and reserve for another recipe.
Rinse chicken with cold water and pat dry.
Lift wing tips up and over back so they are tucked under bird.
Truss chicken and place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine wine, soup, mushrooms and peppers; stir well and pour over chicken. Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until drumsticks are easy to move up and down.
Place chicken on a bed of rice; keep warm.
Pour pan juices into a saucepan; stir in sour cream.
Cook over low heat until thoroughly heated; do not boil. Serve gravy with chicken and hot rice.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: sausage pie
directions: Fry sausage; drain.
Put into pie pan.
Mix together eggs and cheese; pour over sausage.
Mix lightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Beat eggs slowly and add sugar, flour and baking powder.
Heat milk and butter to boiling and add to mixture.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2 5/8-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and immediately spread with topping.

title: rice-broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine.
Add frozen broccoli. Cover and steam until tender, stirring occasionally to separate. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle extra cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling salted water until barely tender. Drain well.
Saute beef with onion until meat is lightly browned. Add rice and seasonings.
Place 1/2 of zucchini on bottom of 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cover with meat.
Add remaining zucchini, then soup.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, 3/4 cup sugar, margarine and 1/2 cup nuts together and press in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Then combine cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar and 1/2 Cool Whip, spread on crust.
Mix instant pudding with milk until thick; spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut and chopped nuts; refrigerate.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Roll into balls.
Melt wax and chocolate in double boiler.
Dips balls in chocolate mixture.

title: apple pie
directions: Place a layer of apples on 9 inch pie crust.
Cover with part of sugar.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Repeat.
Cover with butter and cover with a crust.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: my mother's whole wheat bread
directions: Scald milk. Combine with shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm with one cup water.
Add yeast and mix well.
Blend in eggs and whole wheat flour.
Gradually add enriched flour.
Mix well until blended.
Place dough in greased bowl.
Cover and store in refrigerator for 2 hours or until needed.

title: orange salad(good!)
directions: Mix mandarin oranges and box of jello together.
Stir; mix well.
Add Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Refrigerate.

title: barbecued venison tenderloin
directions: Cut tenderloin into slices 1 3/4-inch thick (about 6).
Trim off any strong fat or tough membrane.
Heat butter in a skillet and brown slices of deer quickly.
Meanwhile, combine remaining ingredients and pour over hot meat.
Place, uncovered, in a moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Baste meat occasionally with the barbecue sauce and turn once during the baking.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy quick roast
directions: Place roast in a large piece of foil on cookie sheet.
Pour soup over roast; seal completely.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Good Sunday dinner.
Can cook while at church.

title: fruit "kale" salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bananas, which are added just before serving.
Can be used as a salad or as a dessert.
Serves approximately 6.

title: nell's potato casserole
directions: Defrost
potatoes.
Mix with everything but corn flakes and butter.
Put
corn	flakes	and butter on top, using large casserole.	Bake at 250° for 45 minutes.

title: nell carmichael's egg bread
directions: Mix well and bake until brown. Cool and crumble.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Divide into 4 parts.
Layer ingredients in punch bowl in the following order:

1/4 cake, 1/2 can blueberry filling, Cool Whip, 1/4 cake, 1/2 can cherry pie filling, Cool Whip, bananas, pineapple, 1/4 cake, 1/2 can blueberry filling, Cool Whip, 1/2 cherry, etc., until all ingredients are used.
Garnish with nuts and coconut.
Make ahead and refrigerate.
Tasty and beautiful.
Serves 24+.

title: company potatoes
directions: Boil, cool and shred potatoes (medium shredder).
Stir in sour cream, onions and 1 cup of the cheese. Pour into greased casserole dish and top with remaining cheese.

title: homemade salad dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Use on your favorite green salad.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, water, onion, garlic salt, oregano and black pepper.
Bring to boil; lower heat and simmer 5 minutes. Place clean fresh mushrooms in large stainless steel container or gallon jar.
Pour hot mixture over; cover tightly.
Let stand 2 days; drain.
Reserve marinade.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Combine flour, oatmeal, salt and baking powder.
With spoon, slowly beat in milk, egg and butter.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased griddle until browned on both sides.
Makes 12 to 16 pancakes.

title: orange dump salad
directions: Dump gelatin and cottage cheese into large bowl and mix well. Add drained
fruit,
dump
in
whipped topping and fold well. Chill 1 hour or overnight.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken in large pot.
Add peppers, carrots, soup, tomatoes, lemon juice and chicken stock.
Cook slowly until carrots are done and sauce is thick.
Add mushrooms and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti.
Makes enough for a family of 8.

title: frosty peach cooler
directions: Whirl peach slices, lime juice, water, orange juice concentrate and crushed ice in blender until smooth and frosty.
Pour over ice cubes in tall glass until half full.
Fill with carbonated beverage and stir gently.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: In medium saucepan, stir cider, corn syrup, cinnamon sticks, cloves and lemon slices.
Bring to boil over medium-high heat. Reduce heat; simmer 15 minutes.
Remove spices.
If desired, garnish each serving with a cinnamon sticks and lemon slice. Makes 10 servings.

title: ostriche alla luigi(oyster luigi)
directions: Scrub shells and rinse.
Place on shallow pan.
Rub shells with garlic and add meat and oil to shell.
Mix basil, parsley, cheese, crumbs and oregano.
Sprinkle over oysters.
Cook under broiler until mixture browns, about 5 minutes.
Serves many.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine and serve with raw vegetable plate.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pie filling and drained pineapple in bowl.
Add sugar. Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, add sliced fresh strawberries and bananas.
Mix well.

title: pink party punch
directions: Add boiling water to Jell-O. Then add cold water, sugar and juices. Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Thaw lemonade.
Beat together lemonade and Eagle Brand milk. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour mixture into graham cracker shell.
Top with sprinkles of graham crackers and refrigerate.

title: best yeast rolls
directions: Combine sugar and salt with 2 cups lukewarm water in a large mixing bowl.
Dissolve yeast in sugar mixture.
Stir in egg.
Add shortening.
Add 1/2 the flour.
Stir well.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Remove tops from peppers.
Boil in salted water 5 minutes. Brown meat and onion; drain off grease.
Add all other ingredients using 1/2 can soup.
Let simmer.
Stuff peppers.
Dilute remaining soup with 1/4 can water.
Place peppers in baking dish.
Pour soup over and around peppers in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Layer tortillas, onion and cheese and pour soup over.
Cover to bake 30 minutes and uncover last 5 minutes.
Set out for 10 minutes before serving.

title: wafer surprise cookies
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and beat well.
Add water and beat.
Chill 1 hour.
Wrap dough completely around a chocolate mint wafer.
Place pecan or walnut half on top.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Yield:
30 cookies.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bean pot.
Place in 225° oven for 12 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Debone chicken and cut in half. Lay chicken flat.
Place 1 slice of ham and 1 slice of cheese on each piece of chicken.
Roll up and place in a baking dish, seam side down.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours, uncovered. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Season pork chops with salt and pepper and brown.
Mix soup with one can water and onion flakes.
Put pork chops in casserole dish and pour soup mix over.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Mix instant pudding mix according to package directions. Combine chopped fruits and shredded coconut.
Add pudding and mix well.
This is delicious by itself or served over angel food cake.

title: cheese muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in greased muffin tins at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: teriyaki chicken and potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into thin wedges.
Microwave 10-12 minutes or until tender.
While potatoes cook, in a large skillet or wok toss and brown chicken in oil and Mrs. Dash over high heat for 5 minutes or until chicken juices run clear.
Add potatoes; saute and toss until potatoes are lightly browned. Add onions and teriyaki sauce; toss until heated through. Yields 4 servings.

title: french toast
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Blend cheese and butter.
Work in flour.
Add Rice Krispies. Roll into small balls and flatten with fork.
Sprinkle with paprika or cayenne pepper and bake at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes on ungreased sheet.
Yields 10 to 12 dozen.

title: three bean salad
directions: Cook sugar, oil, vinegar, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce until sugar dissolves completely.

title: easy microwave chicken
directions: Place chicken in an 8 x 8-inch microwave-safe baking dish. Sprinkle seasoning salt over chicken.
Melt margarine and pour over chicken.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High 8 to 10 1/2 minutes.
Move a half turn at 5 minutes.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Slice apples up in a pie plate.
Mix together 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
In a bowl, melt butter; add flour, 1 cup sugar, salt, walnuts and egg.
Mix well.
Pour over apples; spread around.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: egg salad
directions: Use a potato masher to mash eggs.
Add rest of ingredients to eggs and the secret to this delicious salad is chopped celery and pickles as fine and small as you can.
Then use Kraft mayonnaise as desired and stir well.
Serve on toasted bread.
Makes 8 to 10 sandwiches.

title: pound cake
directions: Put in mixing bowl, one at a time.
Beat 15 minutes on medium speed. Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 1 hour.

title: rolled chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken pieces on cutting board.
Pound with mallet until 1/4-inch thick.
Place ham slice and cheese stick on each cutlet.
Tuck insides and roll up as for a jelly roll.
Skewer with a toothpick.
Roll in flour.
Brown in skillet with butter. Remove to a baking dish.

title: creamy pineapple cheese cake
directions: In microwavable bowl, combine the pineapple and cornstarch. Microwave on High (100%), stirring once, 1 minute or until boiling; boil 1 minute. Cool, then top the cheese cake with this. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: percolator punch
directions: Place first four ingredients in bottom of percolator.
Place remaining ingredients in the percolator basket and percolate as for coffee.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and bacon pieces.
Drain off grease. Add brown sugar, white sugar, catsup, salt, dry mustard and vinegar.
Mix well.
Add beans and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or cook in crock-pot about 2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: steak san marco
directions: Brown meat in oil; then add all other ingredients and simmer for 1 1/2 hours with pan covered.
Serve over rice.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cocoa in a saucepan.
Add enough water to make a paste, then remainder of water.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 3 minutes, add vanilla. Pour at once into a jar. Cool, cover and refrigerate.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together 3 eggs, beaten until lemon colored, sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Blend in flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, baking powder and nuts or raisins.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour.

title: celebration cake(low calorie)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray a 13 x 9 pan with cooking spray. Mix the cake mix, egg whites, apple sauce and oranges (with juice). Pour into prepared pan. Bake 25-30 minutes until a toothpick comes out clean.

Cool cake completely. For the frosting, gently fold together the Cool Whip, the pudding mix and the pineapple with its own juice. Frost the cake. The frosted cake should be stored in the refrigerator. Makes 18 servings, 3 points each (I think). 12 servings would be about 4 points each.

title: rice pilaf
directions: In medium skillet, lightly brown rice, onion and nuts in butter and oil over moderate heat.
Stir often to ensure an even color.
Add stock and salt.
Cook, covered, over low heat for about 20 minutes, until rice has absorbed liquid.
Toss with minced parsley.

title: oriental salad
directions: Mix cabbage, onions, mushrooms, peas and nuts.
Add dressing. Just before serving, add chow mein noodles and toss.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Heat olive oil in heavy saucepan over medium heat.
Add garlic, onion, pepper and celery and saute until vegetables begin to soften.
Stir in chili powder and cumin.
Add remaining ingredients.
Turn heat down and simmer, stirring occasionally, about 30 minutes.
Thin with water if necessary.

title: chow-chow
directions: Combine vegetables and salt; stir well.
Cover and let stand 8 hours.
Drain well.
Stir 2 tablespoons vinegar into mustard. Combine mustard, remaining vinegar and remaining 5 ingredients in a large kettle.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes.
Add vegetables.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In baking dish, mix together all 3 soups.
Add 2 cups uncooked Minute rice.
Mix. Put chicken on top of rice mixture.
Melt butter, then pour over chicken; sprinkle with pepper.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 1/2 hours.

title: crunchy fruit dessert
directions: Combine fruit, marshmallows and salt.
Prepare whipped topping mix as directed on package.
Fold in fruit mixture.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Just before serving, stir in cereal.
Sprinkle with additional cereal, if desired.
Makes 3 cups or 6 servings.

title: wacky cake(a delicious chocolate cake from w.w.  ii; cheap)
directions: In a 9 x 9-inch baking pan, add flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and soda.
Stir these dry ingredients to mix well.
Make 3 holes in the flour mixture.
In one hole put the vinegar, in second hole, put vanilla and in the third hole, put oil.
Pour 1 cup water over all and mix well with a fork, but do not overbeat.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
If using an 8 x 8-inch pan, bake an additional 10 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: witches' brew
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 6 1/2 cups.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, and peanut butter.
Roll into balls and chill.

title: st. patrick's day cupcakes
directions: Line muffin tin with paper baking cups.
In a large bowl, stir together flour, pudding mix, chocolate chips, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In a small bowl, combine eggs, milk, oil and vanilla. Stir both together.
Bake in 375° oven for 18 to 20 minutes. Cool.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: refrigerator pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Put pie filling on top.
Refrigerate for one day.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and jello in powdered form.
Add chopped rhubarb.
Put mixture in lined pie pan.
Top with crust.
Bake at 400° until crust browns, then 350° for about 60 minutes or until the rhubarb is tender.

title: light lemon cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine dry cake mix, lemon pudding mix, water and egg whites.
Beat on low speed for one minute.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan coated with non-stick cooking spray.
Bake at 350 for 23-28 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool.
In a mixing bowl, combine milk, lemon extract and vanilla pudding mix.
Beat on low speed for 2 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread over cake.
Store in the refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sherbet; stir until all melted.
Add drained fruit and chill.

title: stuffed burgers
directions: Make 12 thin hamburger patties.
Combine other ingredients and place in
the center of 6 patties.
Place 6 remaining patties on top and pinch edges together.
Broil, turning once.

title: cherry eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip with mixer until thick. Layer a 13 x 9-inch cake pan with a layer of graham crackers, a layer of pudding and a layer of cherry pie filling; repeat until all of the pudding and pie filling are used. Refrigerate overnight.

title: picnic salad bowl
directions: Drain beans, corn, peas and mushrooms and place in a large bowl, along with the bean sprouts, celery, green onions, pimento, bacon, salt and tomato.
Toss lightly.
Combine spices with oil, vinegar and lemon juice.
Shake well to blend.
Pour dressing over the vegetables and toss gently.
Chill until ready to serve.
Toss in lettuce.

title: apple cake in a jar
