directions: Mix together ingredients in order given. Sterilize 7 to 9 wide-mouth pint jars and lids. Grease them with shortening. Fill the jars half full. Bake on the middle wire rack in the oven for 45 minutes at 325°. As soon as cake is done, remove jars one at a time from oven. Wipe the rim of the jar clean with a damp cloth and put on the hot sterilized lid. Screw down bands and let cool. Do not use small-mouth jars. Do not add any other ingredients. As the cake cools in the sealed jar, it will pull away from the sides of the jar and come out easily when ready to serve. Cakes have a one-year shelf life.

title: baked herbed artichokes
directions: Drain 1 can artichokes.
Place in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix together in a bowl the margarine, chives, dill weed, lemon juice, garlic salt and pepper.
Pour over artichokes.
Bake, uncovered, in 400° oven until crisp and tender, about 20 minutes. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top and broil for a few minutes. Serves 4.

title: scalloped sliced tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Overlap slices in rows in a buttered 12 x 9-inch baking dish; set aside.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and chill overnight.

title: marinated cole slaw
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well and set aside.
Boil remaining ingredients for 3 minutes, pour over cabbage mixture, mix well. Store in refrigerator overnight.
Can be frozen or will last 2 weeks.

title: mock kentucky colonel's seasoned flour
directions: Mix up and store in a container for use as needed.

title: buns
directions: Combine water and yeast.
Add rest of ingredients.
Rise 1 hour.
Form buns, rise 20 to 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken, debone and cut in small pieces.
In bowl mix chicken, soup and sour cream with spoon.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove and add crushed crackers on top.
Bake 15 more minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Butter 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer chicken, layer broccoli. Mix soup, sour cream, mayonnaise and grated cheese.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Add
cup
saltine
cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mom's fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or more.

title: cheddary scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook onion in margarine in skillet over medium heat until tender.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Add potatoes.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes or until hot and bubbling, stirring occasionally.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add the 1/4 cup of cheese for a cheesier flavor.

title: niko's salsa verde
directions: Mix all ingredients, but the pickling spice, in a pan and simmer 5 minutes.
Fill your jars with washed hot peppers to within 1-inch of the top.
Pour 1 1/2 teaspoons of pickling spice into each jar.
Pour 10 ounces of hot mixture over the peppers, then fill the jar to 1/4-inch from the top with tap water.
Put lid on and twist tight.
Repeat the twisting 10 minutes later. You do not have to water bath these peppers.
They'll be ready in 4 to 6 weeks.

title: rhubarb torte
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in rhubarb and water.
Cook until thickened.
Reduce heat and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add food color.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° about 12 minutes.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut potatoes in large chunks.
Add oil and mix potatoes in large bag.
Shake well.
Potatoes should be evenly coated.
Put in shallow baking dish. Bake 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: watermelon drink
directions: Scoop out the pulp from watermelon.
Drain off the juices and put pulp in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar and cover with ginger ale.
Refrigerate 30 minutes, then drain off the liquid. Serve over ice as a beverage.

title: chicken squares
directions: Blend cream cheese and margarine until smooth.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk, onion and pimento.
Mix well.
Separate rolls and form into squares.
Spoon about 1/4 chicken mixture into center of square and seal edges.
Brush tops with melted margarine.
Roll in crushed croutons.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown at 350°.

title: turtle bars
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
(Can be done in microwave or over double boiler.)
Mix together dry cake mix, margarine, remaining milk and 1/2 cup nuts.
Press half of cake mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Sprinkle chocolate chips over baked cake mixture.
Pour caramel mixture over and sprinkle rest of nuts.
Dab remaining cake dough over caramel layer.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ragu bolognese(serves 6)
directions: Fry bacon crisp and drain.
Drain fat from skillet; add olive oil and saute garlic, onion and celery until translucent, about 5 minutes.
Add wine and cook another 5 minutes until almost all the wine has evaporated.
Add carrots, thyme and tomatoes and reduce heat to low.
Simmer, stirring every once in a while, until the liquid has almost completely evaporated.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve small amounts of Ragu with hot cooked pasta.
Pass grated Parmesan separately.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Spread refried beans in bottom of 9 X 13 inch glass baking dish or other serving dish.
Spread sour cream and guacamole on top of refried beans.
Sprinkle lettuce over all.
With back of spoon, spread salsa on top of lettuce.
Sprinkle cheese over lettuce.
Sprinkle green onions and black olives over top.
Cover and refrigerate until serving.
Serve chilled with tortilla chips.

title: chicken or steak with teriyaki sauce
directions: Marinating 1 to 2 hours (if longer, use the larger amount of water) after pouring over the meat, remove and cook on grill (white coals).
Steak cut in strips will cook 3 to 5 minutes on each side. Chicken quarters about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: bean meal
directions: Cook hamburger.
Also cook and crumble bacon.
Mix with other ingredients and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: old fashioned cocoa cake
directions: Combine butter or margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat on high speed of mixer for 3 minutes.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt; add alternately with water to creamed mixture.
Blend just until combined.
Pour into 2 greased and cocoa dusted 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans.
Frost with Cocoa Fudge Frosting.

title: noodle kugel
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Combine eggs and cottage cheese.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix egg and cheese mix with cooked noodles.
Spread in baking pan.
Spray top with cooking spray.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar; set aside.
Mix and bring to boil margarine, cocoa and water.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture. Add the rest of the ingredients; mix well.
Bake on a cookie sheet (with sides) for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: mother's best pickles
directions: Wash beets, leaving about 2 inches of stem. Cook beets until tender. Dip into cold water and peel off skins.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; set aside. In another bowl, beat eggs. Blend in milk, butter, nutmeg and vanilla. Pour into dry ingredients and mix just until moistened. Fold in blueberries. Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 375 degrees for 20-25 minutes.
If desired, brush tops with additional melted butter and sprinkle with sugar. Makes 1 dozen.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip ingredients together.
Chill and serve with fresh fruit tray.

title: corned beef hot dish
directions: Mix soup and milk.
Add cheese, uncooked macaroni, eggs and corned beef.
Let stand overnight, covered.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Serve with chow mein noodles if desired.

title: raisin bread
directions: Mix with mixer until blended.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts.
Bake in Bundt pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Can also be served as cake with whipped cream.

title: butter pecan-banana cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in large bowl.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly pressed and pulls away from sides of pan.
Do not underbake. Cool in pan for 15 minutes; remove and cool on rack.
Top with confectioners sugar glaze and additional banana slices.

title: champagne salad
directions: Blend cheese and sugar, then add all other ingredients.
Slice bananas and fold in.
Serve lightly thawed.
Top with fresh strawberries and chocolate syrup.

title: applesauce
directions: Cut each apple into at least 4 pieces.
Put pieces (peels, seed and all) into a big pan.
Cook over medium heat; stir from time to time until they are squishy.
Add a little water, if needed.
Put apples through food mill to smooth mixture and strain.
Add a little honey to sweeten, a little lemon juice to bring out flavor. Sprinkle a bit of cinnamon and nutmeg; stir and eat warm or cool.

title: baked pumpkin
directions: Place pumpkin in cubes in baking dish.
Combine sugars and cinnamon.
Dot with butter.
Cover with foil and bake until soft. Sprinkle more cinnamon over pumpkin and serve.

title: soy-sauced salmon steaks
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
Sprinkle steaks with salt; let stand for 10 minutes.
In large skillet, cook fish in hot oil about 5 minutes or until browned on one side.
Turn fish and add one slice of lemon atop each steak.
Cook fish about 5 minutes more or until browned on other side.
Discard cooked lemon slices.
Combine soy sauce with mirin or dry sherry.
Pour over fish steaks.
Cook over low heat for 1 to 2 minutes, turning steaks frequently.
Remove fish to platter.
Pour pan juices over steaks; top with remaining lemon slices.
Garnish with pickled ginger or cucumber.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cottage maple pudding
directions: Bring maple syrup to boiling.
Pour into loaf pan.
Mix all other ingredients with electric mixer until very smooth.
Pour batter over maple syrup.
Bake at 400° about 25 minutes.
Turn upside down on platter after cooling about 10 minutes.
Slice and serve with whipped cream, nuts or ice cream.

title: pat's pot roast
directions: Combine flour, tomatoes, soup mix and pepper. Mix well and put in bottom of roasting pan with lid.
Place roast in pan and turn to coat all sides.
Place vegetables around roast.
Cover and bake at 325° until tender, 1 1/2 to 2 1/4 hours.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
If you do not have a roasting pan with a lid, you can use a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with an oven bag.
Before cooking, poke a few holes in top of bag with steak knife.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Combine sugar and butter; cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Make a golden brown roux of oil and flour.
Add onion, green pepper and celery; cook slowly until clear, stirring frequently. Add tomato sauce and cook, covered, over low heat for 20 minutes. Add shrimp, black and red pepper and chili powder.
If mixture becomes dry, add 1/4 cup water.
Cook 10 minutes longer until shrimp turns pink.
When ready to serve, stir in parsley and onion tops.
Serve on rice.
Makes 8 servings.

title: quick broiled shrimp
directions: Shell shrimp and devein.
Heat butter with garlic.
Dip shrimp in
butter mixture.
Broil for 3 minutes on each side. Yield: about 30 appetizers.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and place in Pyrex bowl.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: three-inch layer fudge
directions: Melt margarine in a medium pan.
Add sugar, cocoa, salt and milk; stir well.
Cook until it gets thick.
Pour out in a plate or bowl.
Cool.

title: quick taco salad
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Remove from skillet.
Set aside.
In same skillet, prepare Rice-A-Roni. Mix as package directs.
Stir in meat mixture, salsa and chili powder.
Keep cooking over low heat 3 to 4 minutes or until heated through.

title: lemon bars deluxe
directions: Combine flour and 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Cut in margarine. Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool slightly (grease pan).

title: sweet apple snack
directions: Slice the apples and place on paper plate.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Heat in microwave until cinnamon bubbles. Move onto serving platter.

title: mug-up chocolate cake(alaskan recipe)
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 9-inch or 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake at 350° about an hour (until toothpick comes out clean).
This cake is good plain or melt chocolate chips and spread over cake while warm.
Cool and serve.

title: split pea soup
directions: Fry bacon in 4-quart saucepan over low heat until golden brown, about 10 minutes.
Add onion and continue cooking over low heat, about 5 minutes; do not brown.
Add peas, seasonings and water.
Cover and heat to boiling.
Continue to cook over low heat, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours until peas are completely broken up and smooth.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.
Slowly add milk; reheat.
Stir constantly to just below boiling point, about 2 minutes longer.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve while hot.

title: oven porcupine
directions: Mix tomato sauce, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat oven to 350°.
Mix ground beef, uncooked rice, water, salt, celery salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Make into balls.
Place in baking dish. Pour mix over meat balls.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: potato puffs
directions: Drop by teaspoon into deep fat fryer.
Fry until golden brown. Puffs will turn themselves when done on one side.

title: butter crisp
directions: Cream sugar and butter and add rest.
Roll in ball and press down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: oriental slaw
directions: Slice cabbage and onions thin and place in large bowl.
Melt margarine in baking pan; add noodles, almonds and sunflower seeds. Bake at 350° about 15 minutes, breaking noodles apart as they bake.
When toasted, place on layers of paper towels to cool.
Mix remaining ingredients in blender for dressing.
Mix cabbage, topping and dressing just before serving.

title: potato wedges
directions: Add (according to taste) basil, oregano, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Wash potato.
Cut into wedges.
Dip thoroughly in oil and spices.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grandmother daulbert's sugar cookies
directions: Drop by small teaspoonfuls and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or less.

title: italiano rotini salad
directions: Prepare rotini according to package.
Drain.
Combine rotini and next 5 ingredients.
Blend olive oil, vinegar, Italian seasoning, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Toss dressing with salad mixture.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chess cake
directions: Press the first 4 ingredients into a 13 x 9-inch pan that has been greased and floured.

title: glorified rice
directions: Whip the Jell-O and also the cream. Add rest of ingredients and place in refrigerator.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Slice and cut the pork into small pieces (1/4-inch pieces). Put in skillet with 1 teaspoon oil.
Brown and add garlic (powder will do). Saute in soy sauce for 30 minutes (on low heat).

title: butternut squash soup
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Add squash, water, bouillon, marjoram, black pepper and red pepper.
Bring to a boil, cook 20 minutes or until squash is tender.
Puree in a blender, adding cream cheese until smooth. Return to pot and heat through.
Do not allow to boil.
Makes 4-6 servings.

title: tuna-rice capri
directions: Drain tuna, measuring 2 tablespoons of oil into a large skillet.
Saute onion in oil until tender.
Remove skillet from heat.
Add beans, water, seasonings and soup.
Break up tuna and add to skillet mixture.
Bring quickly to a boil, then stir in long-grain rice from the box.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 8 to 10 minutes or until most of liquid is absorbed, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together and mix with water.

title: banana-bread pudding
directions: In a large bowl whisk together the eggs and egg white until well blended.
Add the milk, sugar or honey, nutmeg and cinnamon. Add the bread and let stand for 5 minutes.
Add the bananas. Coat a 1 to 1 1/2-quart casserole with nonstick spray.
Add the bread mixture.
Place the dish in a larger baking pan and add enough hot water to come halfway up the sides of the inside pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Remove the casserole dish from the water and allow to cool on a wire rack for 10 to 15 minutes. Serve sprinkled with lemon rind.

title: swiss steak parmesan
directions: Combine the Parmesan cheese with the next 6 ingredients. Pound as much of the mixture as possible into both sides of the meat.
Cut the steak into serving portions and brown in 1/4 cup oil in Dutch oven. Keep meat warm while preparing the sauce. Saute the onion and mushrooms.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for 10 minutes. Return meat to Dutch oven.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Heat cranberry juice.
Add remaining ingredients, except orange juice. Simmer 10 minutes.
Add orange juice. Drain spices. Serve hot.

title: ho-ho filling
directions: Beat until smooth. Use to fill cupcakes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and peanut butter in a large mixing bowl; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer, until light and fluffy.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix and bake cake mix as directed. While warm, punch holes with handle of wooden spoon. Mix cream of coconut and condensed milk and pour over cake. Let cake cool. Put Cool Whip over cake, then sprinkle coconut and refrigerate overnight.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cover salad with potato chips or Rice Krispies that have been tossed with melted butter.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: carol's prize winning pineapple cheese cake
directions: Grease the bottom of a 10-inch glass pie pan with margarine. Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed with electric mixer.
Pour into pan.
Pat pineapple dry with a paper towel and place over batter.
Combine cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons pineapple juice.
Beat 2 minutes.
Spoon on top of fruit, leaving 1-inch from sides.
Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on top.
Bake approximately 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool and serve.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: easy shrimp jambalaya
directions: Cook and stir onion and green pepper in melted margarine in skillet until lightly browned, stirring frequently.
Add shrimp and ham.
Cook until shrimp are pink and ham is lightly browned.
Drain tomatoes, measuring liquid.
Add water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Cut up tomatoes.
Stir into shrimp mixture with tomatoes, parsley, bay leaf, salt, sugar, thyme and rice.
Cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 5 minutes longer.
Yields 6 servings.

title: egg casserole
directions: Place half the cheese in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Saute mushrooms and onion in margarine until tender.
Place over cheese. Place meat over mushrooms and top with rest of cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, flour, parsley and seasoned salt.
Pour over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together except reserved oleo and bread crumbs.
Put in well-greased casserole.
Sprinkle top with crumbs and bake 1 hour and 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: orange-pecan dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, orange juice concentrate, lemon juice, whipping cream, sugar and salt in bowl; mix well.
Stir in pecans. Spoon into serving dish.
Chill until serving time.
Serve with choice of fruit.
Yields 8 servings.

title: zucchini and so
directions: Cut sausage into bite-size chunks and cook thoroughly.
Remove sausage from pan and saute onion and zucchini in drippings for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients along with about a cup of water (or less) and sausage.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Freezes well!

title: gertrude hines' cucumbers
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers and onions.
Add sugar, salt, pepper and dill (if desired).
Heat cider vinegar to a boil.
Pour hot vinegar over other ingredients.
Let stand, covered, at room temperature overnight, then chill in icebox.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into two 9-inch pie shells. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: candied yams
directions: Boil potatoes until almost tender.
Peel and cut in half. Cook sugar, water and lemon until thickened.
Pour over potatoes. Cut butter over potatoes and add a little nutmeg.
Cook until candied.

title: pineapple coconut loaf
directions: Combine cake mix, evaporated milk, pineapple and juice, eggs and nutmeg in large mixer bowl.
Beat on lowest speed just until moistened.
Beat on highest speed 2 minutes.
Stir in coconut. Spoon into 2 buttered 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf dishes.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 45 to 50 minutes, or until golden brown and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on wire racks 15 minutes.
Remove from loaf dishes.
Cool completely.

title: corn grits
directions: Pour grits into the boiling water and stir until it comes to a good boil.
Lower fire.
Cover and boil slowly for 20 minutes. Stir frequently.
When ready to serve, put a small lump of butter into the grits and beat well for several minutes.

title: blackberry cobbler(microwave recipe)
directions: Melt butter; put blackberries in bowl and pour melted butter over.
Add sugar.
Stir and mash a few berries.
To make pie crust, stir 2/3 cup milk, 1 1/4 cups flour and juice from berries.
Pour dough into glass square baking dish, spreading out corner to corner.
Pour in blackberry mixture plus 1/2 cup leftover flour. Spread evenly and bake 15 to 18 or 20 minutes in microwave on High. Cool.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together and fry in hot oil.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and pineapple and let it sit while fixing other ingredients.

title: spotted cow-cookies
directions: Vanilla Dough: Stir together 1 1/4 cups flour, 1/2 teaspoon baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt in bowl. Beat together 6 tablespoons butter, 1/2 cup sugar, 1 egg and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla in large bowl. Beat in flour mixture until dough forms. Shape dough into flat disk and wrap in plastic wrap. Chill at least 2 hours.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat together until well blended. Pour into 3 well-greased round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix as for cake.
Put in greased loaf pan.
Let set 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: In gallon jar or container, slice cucumbers, onions and green pepper.
Pour salt over above vegetables.
Mix vinegar and sugar; pour over vegetables when sugar is all dissolved.
Store in refrigerator when cool.
Do not freeze.

title: dutch potatoes filling
directions: Mix together the potatoes and egg.
Saute onion, celery and parsley in butter until soft.
Soak bread in cold water and squeeze dry.
Fluff bread and mix gently with potato mixture. Blend in remaining ingredients and mix well.
Use for stuffing a 6 to 8 pound bird or can be baked in a greased casserole dish in 325° to 350° oven.
Serve as a side dish with any roasted, baked or fried poultry main course.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: thousand isle dip or dressing
directions: Mix in order listed, adding mayonnaise and sour cream last. May add more sour cream, if desired.
May also add more of any seasoning desired.

title: angel corn bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine eggs, milk and oil.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Bake in greased corn stick pans at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen corn sticks.
(Muffins or corn bread wedges will need to bake a little longer.)

title: grilled cheese loaf
directions: Beat cream cheese and butter. Add cheese, onions and garlic. Mix well. Spread on each side of each slice of bread. Wrap in foil and put on grill 8 to 10 minutes. Turn once. Unwrap and grill 5 more minutes. (Can bake in oven.)

title: homemade pancakes
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend on high until smooth.
Pour by 1/4 cup into hot griddle.
When bubbles on top pop, turn and cook until brown.

title: candy krunchies
directions: Mix together and drop on wax paper.
Cool.

title: turkey burgers deluxe
directions: Mix turkey, salt, pepper, onion and garlic.
Shape into 4 large patties.
Melt butter in skillet.
Brown patties on both sides.
Cover until cooked through.
Remove from pan and keep warm.
Stir sour cream into pan to incorporate brown particles and chives.
Spoon over patties and serve.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain. Place meat in pot; add tomato soup, 1/2 can water, tomato puree and beans (drained). Salt and pepper. Also add onion and celery or celery salt, if desired. Also garlic powder if desired. Add chili powder, sprinkled over entire top of sauce. Stir well. Add A.1.
Steak sauce (shake 3 to 4 times), small shakes of Worcestershire sauce (shake 3 to 4 times) and sugar. Stir well. Simmer for 1 hour. Better if let simmer longer.

title: cream filling
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Set aside.
Bring cream to a boil and stir in other ingredients and boil 5 minutes.
Let cool; beat until creamy.
Spread between layers and on top of cake.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together in a large bowl and roll in chopped pecans. Yields 1 ball.

title: marinated christmas tree
directions: Okay now.
This is how it goes you put 'em in a pan.
Then you set them in there for 5 minutes.
Then you put 'em still in there for 5 minutes.
Then you take them out.
Then you start eating them.
Then if you don't want them you can save them.

title: spinach linguine
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil until brown, then set aside.
Drain spinach well; set aside.
Cook spaghetti.
When spaghetti is done, toss in olive oil and spinach.
Drain tuna fish and add to spaghetti.
Then if you like them, add anchovy fillets on your own dish of spaghetti.
Enjoy.

title: sour cream chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg and then add vanilla and chocolate; mix well.
Add flour, soda and sour cream and mix well.
Mix in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: tofu-stuffed zucchini
directions: Wrap the tofu in absorbent toweling.
Place a heavy weight on top for 10 minutes to squeeze out the excess moisture.
Wash thoroughly and trim ends from zucchini.
Slice zucchini in half lengthwise.
Scoop out the pulp, leaving a 1/4-inch shell.
Chop the zucchini pulp and reserve for later use.
Saute the onion and garlic in little water until softened.
Add the chopped zucchini pulp and spices.
Simmer over low heat about 10 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Take the tofu and, using your hands, squeeze out any remaining moisture.
Crumble the tofu and add to the zucchini mixture and blend.
Remove from heat and spoon into the reserved zucchini shells.
Using a small baking dish (preferably glass), pour in enough tomato sauce to cover bottom of pan.
Add stuffed zucchini and pour the remaining sauce on top.
If desired, sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover dish and bake an additional 10 minutes or until zucchini is tender.

title: party peas
directions: Mix all.
Put in casserole and sprinkle cracker crumbs on top. Put in oven and let cook until it begins to boil (400°).

title: lo-cal cheese ball
directions: Dice scallions and dried beef.
Combine with the rest of the ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Shape into a ball and chill. Serve with crackers or raw veggies!

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add soup, carrots, onion and sour cream. Place layer of crumbs in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour mixture over crumbs.
Spread a layer of crumbs over top.
Dot with butter. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken pot pie(serves 6)
directions: Place chicken sprinkled with salt and pepper into a Dutch oven or kettle; add chicken broth.
Cover and simmer gently for 40 to 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken pieces and set aside.
Cool.
Add vegetables to broth.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir in half and half and poultry seasoning.

title: pizza mac
directions: Prepare macaroni according to directions; drain.
In medium bowl, beat milk, egg and salt.
Add to macaroni and mix well. Spread evenly in greased 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Spoon spaghetti sauce over macaroni.
Top with beans, sausage, mushrooms, chilies, green pepper, tomato, onion, seasoning and cheese.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: strawberry delight salad
directions: Mix jello and water and then add frozen strawberries.
Break up and dissolve.
Add last two ingredients.
Put about 1/2 of mixture in a 6 x 12-inch Pyrex and chill (takes very little time). Keep remaining ingredients out of fridge.
When chilled, spread 1/2 pint sour cream over top and then add rest of mixture on top. Serves 9 to 12.

title: beef and spinach with noodle topping
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Heat 1 tablespoon of the oil in a large saucepan over moderate heat for 1 minute.
Add the onion and saute, stirring occasionally until soft 5 minutes.
Transfer the onion to an ungreased 3-quart casserole.
Add the remaining oil to the saucepan and heat for 1 minute.
Reduce the heat to low, whisk in the flour, and cook, stirring constantly, until bubbly, 3 minutes.
Stir in the milk, marjoram, salt and pepper and cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened, 3 to 5 minutes. Transfer 1/2 cup of the cream sauce to a medium-size bowl.
Add the cooked noodles, mix gently and set aside.
Add the cheese, spinach and carrots to the remaining sauce and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes.
Transfer to the casserole with the onion.
Add the beef and egg to the casserole and mix well.
Pack down lightly.
Layer the noodle mixture on top of the beef.
Cover the casserole with foil and bake for 25 minutes. Uncover and bake until the noodles are golden and the mixture is set 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: really good green beans
directions: Fry bacon and save the grease. Cut onion into rings. Add vinegar and sugar

to the bacon grease. Layer as follows, pouring the grease/vinegar/sugar mixture over each layer: green beans, almonds, bacon (crumbled) and then onion rings. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish; cover with bread.
Brown meat, then drain.
Add over top of bread.
Put on cheese.
Add beaten eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over top of cheese. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lazy day pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Heat peaches. Melt butter in 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Mix all other ingredients and pour into dish. Add peaches. Bake at 425° for about 30 minutes.

title: glory cake
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients all at once.
Mix by hand 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour into well-greased and floured pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peaches and cream delight
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add brown sugar and cinnamon.
Heat while stirring to dissolve sugar.
Remove from heat; stir in cereal and nuts.
Press into bottom of ungreased large pie tin or square pan.
Spread softened ice cream on crust.
Freeze until firm.
An hour before serving, top with peach pie filling.
Return to freezer for 1/2 hour or until ready to serve.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix all together in large bowl.
Put in crock-pot on high until hot and then cook on low for 2 to 3 hours.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper in a pan, then place in a casserole dish or pan the ground beef, onion and pepper.
Mix in a separate bowl the onion soup, sour cream, potato soup and garlic powder and place a layer of this when well mixed on top of the ground beef.
Place the Tater Tots on top of the soup mixture in rows.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, then turn heat down to 325° for 30 minutes.
Delicious and tasty.

title: cream cheesecake vanilla-brownie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and spread in greased oblong cake pan for crust.
Mix eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar well and pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cranberry cream salad
directions: Whip cream and sugar in a chilled bowl until stiff peaks form. Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into loaf pan and freeze.

title: white clam sauce and pasta
directions: Sauce:
Saute olive oil, butter and garlic for two minutes. Add drained clams, flour, black pepper and wine.
Cook for 5 to 7 minutes.
Add reserved clam juice for desired consistency.
Cook pasta to taste.
Toss with clam sauce and parsley and serve with freshly grated Parmesan cheese.

title: date pinwheel cookies
directions: Mix first
ingredients.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick and spread with
date
filling.
Cook remaining ingredients until thick; set aside
and cool.
Spread on cookie dough, roll like jelly roll and refrigerate overnight.
Slice and bake at 350°.

title: spice doughnuts
directions: Sift flour; measure and re-sift 3 times with baking powder, soda, salt and nutmeg.
Cream shortening; blend in sugar thoroughly, then add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk, in 3 or 4 portions, stirring only until well mixed.
Chill dough before rolling. Remove only part of dough from refrigerator at a time.
Roll dough out on lightly floured board or pastry cloth from 1/4 to 3/8-inch thick.
Cut out doughnuts with floured cutter.
Fry in deep fat heated to 375°.
Fry only until underside is golden brown, then turn and brown on other side.
Lift doughnuts out with slotted spoon or in a wire basket.

title: vegetable pie
directions: In large frying pan, saute eggplant, zucchini, onion and tomatoes in butter for about 12 minutes or until soft.
Add egg and Parmesan cheese; mix well.
Put cooked ingredients into a baking dish (10-inch square) and cover with Mozzarella cheese. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until browned and bubbling.
Let set about 10 minutes before serving.
Can do ahead.
Can be frozen.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Dot pieces of margarine over entire mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: all american supper
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package.
Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Cover over low heat 10 minutes until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally.
Makes 2 servings.

title: grandma toothman's ham loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fried pie pastry
directions: Combine flour and salt; cut in shortening.
Combine egg, water and vinegar.
Add to flour and stir lightly.
Shape into a ball and chill at least 1 hour.

title: strawberry cubes
directions: Mash berries and bananas.
Mix all other ingredients well. Pour in ice trays and freeze.

title: margaret's pancakes
directions: Pour batter (enough for size of pancake wanted) into lightly greased frying pan.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in water until done.
Remove from heat; add cheese, butter and salt.
Beat egg into milk; add to grits mixture when cooled enough not to cook egg.
Stir well.
Pour into a baking dish and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve hot.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: better than pizza casserole
directions: Line an 8-inch pan with biscuits.
Brown ground beef in skillet with green pepper and spices.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Pour over biscuits.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
